es R 98 Expenses for household help or comparable services R 99 R 100 Lump sums for the disabled, surviving dependents and carers R 101 Child care costs R 102 Income from remuneration for a multi-year activity R 103 Contributions to political parties R 104 Tax deduction from wages R 104 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Income of wages R 105 Employer's withholding obligation R 106 Wage payment by third parties, tips R 107 Marital status R 108 Procedure for issuing the wage tax card R 109 Changes and additions to the wage tax card R 110 Subsequent issuance of wage tax cards R 111 Procedure for entering an allowance on the wage tax card R 112 Exemption due to negative income R 113 Exemption for spouses R 113a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Exemption certificate for part-time employment R 114 Keeping the income tax card R 115 Current wages and other emoluments R 116 Pension allowance R 117 Retirement allowance R 118 Withholding wage tax from current wages R 119 Withholding wage tax from other emoluments R 120 Use of general and special wage tax tables R. 121 Automatic wage accounting and wage tax calculation according to the annual wage tax table R 122 Taxation of net wages R 123 Application of double taxation agreements R 124 Failure to present wage tax card R 124a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Implementation of wage tax deduction for extended unlimited income tax liability R 125 Implementation of wage tax deduction for employees subject to limited income tax R 126 Assessment of wage tax according to special flat tax rates (Section 40 (1) EStG) R 127 Assessment of wage tax according to a fixed flat rate tax (Section 40 (2) EStG) R 128 Flat rate the wage tax for part-time employees R 129 Flat rate wage tax for certain future security benefits R 130 Recording relief, recording of the religious community R 131 Recording of the capital letter UR 132 Business premises R 133 Income tax registration R 134 Payment of wage tax R 135 Wage tax certificate R 136 Wage tax certificate from public coffers R 137 Change of the Income tax deduction R 138 Obligations to notify the employer R 139 Additional demand for income tax R 140 - R 142 R 143 Implementation of the annual income tax settlement by the employer R 144 R 145 Use of the Employer's R 146 Liability in the case of temporary employment R 147 Call information R 148 External wage tax audit R 149 Assessment according to \u00a7 46 Paragraph 2 No. 8 EStG R 150 Elimination of hardship in certain cases of \u00a7 46 Paragraph 2 EStG Article 2 General administrative regulation on tax deduction from wages From 29 October 1999 In accordance with Article 108 (7) of the Basic Law, the following general administrative regulation is issued: Article 1 Introduction (1) In the interest of uniform application of wage tax law by the tax authorities, the 2000 wage tax guidelines contain instructions on the interpretation of the Income Tax Act and its implementing ordinances as well as instructions on avoiding undue hardship and for administrative simplification"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The wage tax guidelines 2000 are to be applied to the withholding of taxes on wages for wage payment periods which end after December 31, 1999, and for other payments which accrue to the employee after December 31, 1999"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "With the consent of the Federal Ministry of Finance, the highest tax authorities of the federal states can change the maximum and lump sums stipulated in the wage tax guidelines if an adjustment to new legal provisions or economic developments is necessary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) Opposing letters of the Federal Ministry of Finance and decrees of the highest tax authorities of the states are no longer applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) Unless otherwise specified, these guidelines are governed by the 1997 Income Tax Act in the version published on 16 4 1997 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "821), last amended by Article 10 of the law on the new regulation of part-time employment of 24 3 1999 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "388) and by Article 1 of the Tax Relief Act 1999/20 00/2002 of 24 3 1999 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "402)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 1 Income tax liability - unoccupied - R 2 Determination of the taxable income and the income tax to be assessed - unoccupied - R 3 - unoccupied - R 4 Benefits according to the Third Book of the Social Security Code (Section 3 No. 2 EStG) (1) Unemployment benefit and partial unemployment benefit are tax-free according to the Third Book of the Social Security Code (SGB III)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Any later payments by the employer to the employment office on the basis of the statutory subrogation (Section 115 SGB X) are also tax-free if insolvency proceedings have been opened against the employer's assets or one of the cases under Section 183 (1) No. 2 or 3 SGB III is present"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Hat das Arbeitsamt in den F\u00e4llen der \u00a7\u00a7 140 Abs 4 und 143 Abs 3 SGB III zun\u00e4chst Arbeitslosengeld gezahlt und zahlt der Arbeitnehmer dieses auf Grund dieser Vorschriften dem Arbeitsamt zur\u00fcck, so bleibt die R\u00fcckzahlung mit Ausnahme des Progressionsvorbehalts (&gt;R 185 EStR) ohne steuerliche Auswirkung (\u00a7 3c EStG); der dem Arbeitnehmer vom Arbeitgeber nachgezahlte Arbeitslohn ist grunds\u00e4tzlich steuerpflichtig"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) Insolvency money (Section 183 SGB III) and payments by the insolvency administrator or the former employer to the employment office on the basis of Section 187 sentence 1 SGB III or to the collection point on the basis of Section 208 (2) SGB III are also tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) The tax-free benefits according to SGB III also include the winter allowance, which is paid as additional winter allowance to compensate for the weather-related extra work and as a supplementary winter allowance to reduce the loss of income when paying the winter loss allowance in advance in the bad weather ( \u00a7 209 No. 1 SGB III)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) The maintenance allowance is also tax-free (Section 153 SGB III)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also includes the special forms of partial maintenance allowance (\u00a7 154 SGB III) and follow-up maintenance allowance (\u00a7 156 SGB III)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 5 Lump-sum payments on the basis of the civil service (pension) laws (Section 3 No. 3 EStG) - vacant - R 6 Provision of uniforms and other services to certain members of the public service (Section 3 No. 4 EStG) The tax exemption according to Section 3 No. 4 letters a and b EStG apply to all uniforms that members of the above-mentioned professional groups are obliged to wear in accordance with the relevant uniform regulations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Civil servants do not belong to the members of the Bundeswehr or the Federal Border Police within the meaning of Section 3 No. 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 7 Payments in cash and in kind for conscripts and those doing community service (Section 3 No. 5 EStG) In addition to military pay, monetary payments within the meaning of Section 1 (1) sentence 1 of the Military Wages Act include special allowances, service payments and dismissal payments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 35 of the Civil Service Act, those doing civil service are entitled to the same remuneration in cash and in kind as a soldier of the lowest rank in the team who is doing military service on the basis of compulsory military service"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of community service providers who cannot be assigned business accommodation and are therefore granted a \"home sleep permit\", the fare paid instead of the provision of accommodation for the journeys between home and work is a tax-free payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 8 Legal remuneration of military and civil service disabled, war invalids, their surviving dependents and persons treated as such (Section 3 No. 6 EStG) (1) Tax-free payments according to Section 3 No. 6 EStG are the benefits under the Federal Pension Act regardless of whether they are directly from this or from laws that declare it to be applicable, further benefits according to \u00a7\u00a7 41 Paragraph 2 63 63a, 85 and 86 of the Soldiers' Welfare Act as well as \u00a7 35 Paragraph 5 and \u00a7 50 of the Civilian Service Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The laws that declare the Federal Supply Act to be applicable include the Soldiers Supply Act (cf. Section 80 of the Act), the Civil Service Act (cf. Section 47 of the Act), the Prisoner Assistance Act (cf. Sections 4 and 5 of the Act) and the Act on Maintenance Allowance for relatives of prisoners of war (see Section 3 of the Act), the Federal Border Guard Act (see Section 59, Paragraph 1 of the Act in conjunction with the Soldiers' Supply Act), (repealed) the Act regulating the legal relationships of persons falling under Article 131 of the Basic Law ( see Sections 66 66a of the Act), the Act introducing the Federal Supply Act in Saarland of 16 August 1961 (cf. Section 5 Paragraph 1 of the Act), the Act on Compensation for Victims of Violent Acts (cf. Section 1 of the Act), the Federal Government - Disease Act (see Section 51 of the Act), the Criminal Rehabilitation Act (see Sections 21 22 of the Act), the Administrative Rehabilitation Act (see Sections 3 4 of the Act)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The remuneration paid for pension purposes in accordance with Section 3 No. 6 EStG, which is not granted on the basis of the length of service, also includes remuneration of professional soldiers in the former Wehrmacht, members of the enforcement service of the police, the former Reich water protection officers, the officers of the former protection police L\u00e4nder as well as the former members of the regional police and their surviving dependents, the accident welfare benefits to civil servants on the basis of Sections 32 to 35 and Section 38 of the Civil Service Insurance Act (BeamtVG), maintenance contributions in accordance with sections 40 41 of the BeamtVG and benefits under Section 82 of the BeamtVG in conjunction with Section 181 a Paragraph 2 BBG or corresponding state law provisions; the full service damage pensions and the service damage partial pensions according to the pension regulations of the National People's Army (VSO-NVA), the People's Police, the fire brigade and the penal system of the Ministry of the Interior (VSO-MdI), the GDR customs administration (VSO-Zoll) and the Ministry of State Security / Office for National Security (VSO-MfS / AfNS) as well as the compensation for service damages, which from 1 1 1997 according to the law on compensation for service injuries in the acceding area of \u200b\u200b11 November 1996 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "1676) is paid instead of the aforementioned pensions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 9 Severance pay due to termination of the employment relationship (Section 3 No. 9 EStG) Severance payment (1) Severance payments are compensation that the employee receives as compensation for the disadvantages associated with the termination of the employment relationship, in particular for the loss of the job"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The severance payments do not include any other remuneration that is only paid on the occasion of the termination of an employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant on what legal basis the severance payment is based; Severance payments to which the employee is not entitled are also tax-free under the conditions set out in Section 3 No. 9 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Section 3 No. 9 EStG is also applicable to employees whose wages are tax-free according to Section 3 No. 39 EStG or are taxed at a flat rate according to Section 40a EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Termination of the employment relationship (2) The termination is initiated by the employer if the employer has set the decisive causes for the termination"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A judicially pronounced dissolution need not be initiated by the employer; This does not exist if a court judgment or court settlement merely confirms a termination issued by a contracting party"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A notice of amendment only results in the termination of the employment relationship if it leads to a departure from the employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Scope of the tax relief (3) The exemption is based on the age and length of service of the employee at the point in time at which the employment relationship was terminated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Each employee from the same employment relationship is entitled to it only once"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the severance payment is paid out in partial amounts or in continuous amounts, the individual installments are tax-free until the tax-free amount applicable to the employee has been exhausted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A distribution of the exemption according to the term of the severance payment is not permitted; rather, the exemption is to be taken into account in the installments first drawn"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the deduction of the exemption is partially omitted, although the amount of the severance payment would have allowed the deduction, the exemption can no longer be taken into account in installments in subsequent years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The fact that the tax exemption is not taken into account in the wage tax deduction procedure will be made up for in the income tax assessment for the inflow year, provided that the requirements for this are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the severance payment exceeds the tax-exempt amount, it is subject to wage tax deduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the taxable part of the severance payment is a tariff-favored compensation within the meaning of Section 34 (1) EStG, the wage tax for this other payment must be determined in accordance with Section 39b (3) sentence 9 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Regardless of this, the tariff reduction in accordance with Section 34 Paragraph 1 EStG can be taken into account when assessing income tax (Section 46 Paragraph 2 No. 5 or 8 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Determination of the length of service (4) The following applies to the determination of the length of service: Is an employment relationship for reasons for which the employee is not responsible, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "in the construction industry in bad weather, and the employee was subsequently unemployed, then when determining the relevant tax allowance, service times that the employee spent with the employer before becoming unemployed must also be taken into account if he starts again immediately after becoming unemployed Has entered into an employment relationship with the same employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of employment within a group, periods in which the employee previously worked for other legally independent companies in the group are generally not taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, if severance payments have not been made to the employee in earlier implementations within the group because the group has considered this implementation to be a continuation of a uniform employment relationship, a total length of employment for the group is to be assumed for the determination of the exemption if the employment contract provides important information such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "contains the calculation of the employee's pension entitlement, vacation entitlement or anniversary of service"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If workers in the construction industry are posted to joint ventures, the duration of the employment relationship according to Section 3 No. 9 EStG is calculated from the sum of the times in the main company and on the construction sites of the joint ventures"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies if the employee has established an independent employment relationship with the consortium and has been released from the parent company, provided that the employment relationship with the parent company is only suspended during employment with the consortium and the employee continues to have rights vis-\u00e0-vis the parent company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "As far as according to legal regulations, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Dismissal Protection Act, the law on a miners' benefit certificate, periods of service with previous employers are to be taken into account, this also applies when determining the duration of employment as defined in Section 3 No. 9 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Employment times previously spent with the employer can only be taken into account if no severance payment within the meaning of Section 3 No. 9 EStG has been paid due to the earlier termination of the employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 10 transitional payments, transitional grants (Section 3 No. 10 EStG) (1) Tax-free transitional payments and transitional grants according to Section 3 No. 10 EStG are z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": ": the transitional allowance in accordance with Section 47 of the Civil Service Insurance Act in conjunction with its Section 67 (4) and corresponding benefits based on the civil service laws of the federal states, if the benefits are not paid due to a scheduled termination of a fixed-term employment relationship, the transitional allowance in accordance with Articles 12 and 13 and the transitional allowance according to \u00a7 37 of the Soldiers Supply Act, the discharge allowance according to \u00a7\u00a7 52 c, 54 para 4 54b, 55 70 para 5 and 71 G 131 (2) On the other hand, the taxable wages include: the compensation payments according to \u00a7 11 a of the Soldiers Supply Act, the transitional allowance according to \u00a7 14 of the Federal Ministers Act and corresponding services based on the laws of the federal states"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 11 Aid and support granted because of need (Section 3 No. 11 EStG) Aid and support from public funds (1) Aid in cases of illness, birth and death according to the state aid regulations of the federal government and the federal states as well as special support are tax-free Emergencies paid from public purse; Aid in cases of illness, birth and death and support in special emergencies to employees of corporations, institutions and foundations under public law on the basis of state aid regulations (aid principles) and support regulations (support principles) of the federal or state governments or corresponding regulations; Aid and support to employees of administrations, companies or companies that are predominantly in the public domain, if a) the administrations, companies or companies are subject to state or municipal supervision and financial management with regard to the remuneration and the granting of the aid, and b) the remuneration as well as the granting of grants and support for the employees concerned are regulated exclusively in accordance with the regulations and agreements applicable to employees in the public sector; Aid and support to employees of companies that are not predominantly publicly owned, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "State-recognized private schools, if a) with regard to remuneration, travel expense allowances and the granting of subsidies and subsidies, the regulations that apply to the public service are followed, b) the regulations governing budgetary and treasury funds that are relevant for the federal administration or a state administration - and accounting and auditing are observed and c) the company is subject to auditing by the Federal Audit Office or a State Audit Office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Support and recovery allowances for employees in the private sector (2) Supports that are paid by private employers to individual employees are tax-free if the support is justified on the basis of the cause, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "in case of illness or accident"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for tax exemption is that the support comes from an institution created with the employer's own resources but independent of the employer and equipped with sufficient independence, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A support fund or auxiliary fund for cases of need and unemployment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This applies not only to civil and legally independent relief funds, but also to tax-independent relief funds without legal personality, over whose administration the employer has no decisive influence; are paid from amounts that the employer transfers to the works council or other employee representatives for the purpose of granting support to the employees from these amounts without the employer having any decisive influence; granted by the employer himself only after hearing the works council or other employee representatives or approved in accordance with uniform principles that have been approved by the works council or other employee representatives"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisites of numbers 1 to 3 need not be met if the company employs fewer than five employees"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The grants are tax-free up to an amount of DM 1,000 per calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The amount exceeding 1000 DM does not belong to the taxable wages only if it is granted on the occasion of a special emergency"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When assessing whether such an emergency exists, the employee's income and marital status must also be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Services provided by the employer to maintain and fulfill a claim under civil service law as well as to compensate for aid expenses by previous employers in the event of leave of absence or the provision of employees or the transfer of the public service relationship to the private employer are also tax-free, if freedom from insurance in the statutory health insurance Section 6 Paragraph 1 No. 2 SGB V exists"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 12 Aid from public funds for the purposes of education, training, research, science or art (Section 3 No. 11 and 44 EStG) - unoccupied - R 13 Expense allowances from public funds (Section 3 No. 12 EStG) (1) Public services generally provide all persons who are in the service of a legal person under public law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, no public services within the meaning of this provision are provided by persons who work in fiscal administration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The prerequisite for recognition as a tax-free expense allowance according to Section 3 No. 12 Sentence 2 EStG is that the amounts paid are intended to compensate for expenses that would be tax deductible as business expenses or business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "There is therefore no tax-free allowance if the compensation for loss of earnings or loss of time or to compensate for a liability risk is paid or if the recipient does not incur expenses or apparently not in the amount of the compensation granted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax office has the right and the duty to check whether the amounts paid as an expense allowance are actually required to cover a deductible expense"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is not necessary for the taxpayer to provide evidence of all his business expenses down to the smallest detail"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is also not decisive which expenses a single taxpayer actually incurs in a single year, but whether people in the same official position incur expenses in the amount of the allowance on average over the years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A re-examination is only necessary if there is reason to do so"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If remuneration is paid to volunteer people in the municipal area under the designation expense allowance, they are not tax-exempt under Section 3 No. 12 EStG, provided that they also compensate for the time and work effort as well as the lost earnings and the liability risk or clearly exceed the effort"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) To make it easier to determine the extent to which it is a tax-free expense allowance in the cases of \u00a7 3 No. 12 sentence 2 EStG, the following should be done: Are the beneficiaries and the amount or a maximum amount granted from a public fund Expense allowance is determined by law or ordinance, the expense allowance is tax-free in full for full-time employees, and in the case of volunteers in the amount of 1/3 of the granted expense allowance, at least DM 50 per month tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the beneficiaries and the amount or a maximum amount are not determined by law or ordinance, tax-deductible expenses for full-time employees up to the amount of DM 300 per month for full-time employees and in the amount of 1 / 3 of the allowance granted, a minimum of 50 DM and a maximum of 300 DM per month"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the allowance is lower than DM 50 per month, only the amount actually paid remains tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For people who work for several corporations under public law, the tax-free minimum and maximum amounts of 50 or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "300 DM per month to be based on the compensation paid to these persons by the individual public corporation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Expense reimbursements for several activities at one corporation must be added together for the application of the minimum and maximum amounts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of occasional voluntary work, the tax-free minimum and maximum amounts of 50 and"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "300 DM not to be converted to a period of less than a month of voluntary work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If expense allowances are paid in different amounts per month or if the activity for the corporation does not extend over the entire calendar year, the tax-free minimum and maximum amounts of 50 or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "300 DM are to be regarded as absolute monthly amounts if the corporation in question pays certain amounts for certain months"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, a conversion to longer periods is not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The supreme state authority responsible for financial management can, in consultation with the Federal Ministry of Finance and the supreme financial authorities of the other states, make adjustments to the circumstances in the state"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) The recipients of expense allowances can credibly demonstrate to the tax office a higher tax-deductible expense; the expenses exceeding the allowance are deductible as income-related expenses or business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a full-time employee incurs other work-related expenses in addition to the expenses to be reimbursed by the expense allowance, these are deductible as business expenses regardless of the expense allowance; in this case, however, paragraph 3 does not apply, but rather paragraph 2 sentences 3 to 6"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of voluntary workers, all expenses caused by the activity are to be regarded as being replaced by the tax-free allowance so that only expenses in excess of the allowance are deductible as business expenses or business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(5) Lump-sum compensation paid by municipalities or other legal entities under public law for occasional voluntary work, an amount of up to DM 10 per day may be recognized as tax-free without further examination"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of higher lump-sum compensation, the tax office has to check whether an expenditure of time and work performance as well as lost earnings have been compensated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Paragraph 3 can also be used instead of this rule"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 14 Travel expense allowances, relocation allowances and separation allowances from public coffers (\u00a7 3 No. 13 EStG) (1) According to \u00a7 3 No. 13 EStG, payments that are paid as travel expenses, relocation allowances or separation allowances from a public fund are tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax exemption of remuneration for additional meal expenses for business trips within the meaning of R 37 (3) is limited to the amounts according to R 39 and for secondments that are not business trips within the meaning of R 37 (3) to the amounts according to R 43; R 16 sentences 2 and 3 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) Travel expense reimbursements are the reimbursements designated as such, which are paid in terms of reason and amount directly in accordance with the travel expenses regulations of the federal or state governments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Travel expense reimbursements are also provided insofar as they are paid in terms of reason and amount on the basis of collective bargaining agreements or other agreements that comply with federal or state travel expense regulations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) If the travel expense regulations are not or only partially applied to travel expense reimbursements from public coffers, the administrative regulations issued under Section 3 No. 16 EStG can be applied to these reimbursements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Im \u00fcbrigen kann auch eine Steuerbefreiung nach \u00a7 3 Nr 12 oder Nr 26 EStG in Betracht kommen; &gt;R 13 und 17 (4)Abs\u00e4tze 2 und 3 gelten sinngem\u00e4\u00df f\u00fcr Umzugskostenverg\u00fctungen und Trennungsgelder nach Ma\u00dfgabe der umzugskosten- und reisekostenrechtlichen Vorschriften des Bundes und der L\u00e4nder"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If additional expenses for meals are reimbursed for the days of relocation in accordance with the Federal Moving Costs Act, the reimbursement is only tax-free within the framework of the time requirements of Section 4 (5) sentence 1 no.5 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Separation allowance, which is paid on the daily return to the place of residence, is only tax-free in accordance with R 21b, 37 to 39"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 14a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Public coffers - unoccupied - R 15 marriage allowances and childbirth allowances (\u00a7 3 No. 15 EStG) marriage and childbirth allowances are one-off or ongoing payments in money or monetary value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If an employee receives a marriage or childbirth allowance from several employment relationships, he can claim the exemption for each of the allowances"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If parents who both receive wages both receive an allowance, each parent is entitled to the exemption, even if they are employed by the same employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of multiple births, the birth grant remains tax-free, provided it does not exceed DM 700 per child"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 16 Erstattung von Reisekosten, Umzugskosten und Mehraufwendungen bei doppelter Haushaltsf\u00fchrung au\u00dferhalb des \u00f6ffentlichen Dienstes (\u00a7 3 Nr 16 EStG) Wegen der Steuerfreiheit der Erstattung von Reisekosten, Umzugskosten und Mehraufwendungen bei doppelter Haushaltsf\u00fchrung au\u00dferhalb des \u00f6ffentlichen Dienstes &gt;R 37 bis 41 und 43 Bei der Erstattung von Reisekosten d\u00fcrfen die einzelnen Aufwendungsarten zusammengefa\u00dft werden; in diesem Fall ist die Erstattung steuerfrei, soweit sie die Summe der nach R 38 bis 40a zul\u00e4ssigen Einzelerstattungen nicht \u00fcbersteigt"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This applies mutatis mutandis to the reimbursement of moving costs and additional expenses in the case of double housekeeping"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 17 Expense allowances for part-time activities (Section 3 No. 26 EStG) Beneficiary activities (1) The beneficiary activities include e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the activity of a sports trainer, a choir director or orchestra conductor, teaching and lecturing activities in the context of general education and training, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Courses and lectures at schools and adult education centers, mother counseling, first aid courses, swimming lessons, or vocational training and further education, but not the training of animals, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "from race horses or service dogs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In addition to long-term care, the care of old, sick or handicapped people also includes auxiliary services for home care by outpatient care services, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Support with basic and treatment care, with household chores and purchases, with correspondence, with care for the elderly in accordance with Section 75 of the Federal Social Welfare Act, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Help with the procurement of apartments and homes, in questions of the use of age-appropriate services, and with immediate measures against seriously ill and accident victims, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "by paramedics and first aiders"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An activity that by its nature is not an exercise-guiding, training, educational or artistic activity and does not care for the elderly, sick or disabled is not a beneficiary activity, even if it meets the other requirements of \u00a7 3 No. 26 EStG, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Worked as a board member, as a club cashier, or as an equipment manager at a sports club"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Secondary occupation (2) An activity is exercised as a secondary occupation if it does not take up more than a third of the working hours of a comparable full-time employment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is therefore also possible for people to work part-time who do not have a main occupation in terms of tax law, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Housewives, landlords, students, retirees or the unemployed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a taxpayer exercises several different types of activities within the meaning of Section 3 No. 26 EStG, the secondary occupation must be assessed separately for each activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Several activities of the same kind are to be grouped together if, according to the general public, they represent the exercise of a single main occupation, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Lessons less than the third part of the full-time workload in several schools"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An activity is not carried out on a part-time basis if it is to be regarded as part of the main activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Promotion of charitable, benevolent and church purposes (3) The terms charitable, charitable and church purposes result from Sections 52 to 54 AO and Annex 7 to R 111 EStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An activity also serves the selfless promotion of favored purposes if it only indirectly benefits these purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) If the activity is carried out within the framework of the fulfillment of the statutory purposes of a legal person who is tax-privileged for promoting charitable, charitable or church purposes, it is generally to be assumed that the activity also serves the promotion of these tax-privileged purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the part-time activity is carried out in a so-called special-purpose company within the meaning of Sections 65 to 68 AO, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Part-time trainer at sporting events according to \u00a7 67a Paragraph 1 AO, part-time educator in an institution for welfare education or voluntary educational assistance according to \u00a7 68 No. 5 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An activity in a taxable commercial business of an otherwise tax-privileged legal person (\u00a7\u00a7 64 14 AO) does not, on the other hand, meet the criteria of promoting charitable, charitable or church purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(5) An activity for a legal entity under public law can also serve to promote beneficiary purposes, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "part-time teaching activity at a university, part-time training activity in the fire brigade, part-time training activity for a bar or medical association"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This does not preclude the fact that the activity can fall under the jurisdiction of the legal person under public law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Limitation of the tax exemption (6) If an expense allowance is paid partly for an activity falling under Section 3 No. 26 EStG and partly for another activity, only the corresponding portion according to Section 3 No. 26 EStG is tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax exemption of payments according to other regulations, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "according to \u00a7 3 No. 9 12 16 39 EStG, remains unaffected; if both \u00a7 3 No. 26 EStG and other tax exemption regulations are applicable to certain payments, the regulations are to be applied in the order that is most favorable for the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Income tax procedure (7) When deducting income tax, it is not necessary to split the tax-free maximum amount of DM 2,400 annually on a pro rata basis; this also applies if it is certain that the employment relationship does not exist until the end of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, the employee must confirm to the employer in writing that the tax exemption has not already been taken into account in another employment or contract relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This declaration must be added to the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(8) Business expenses incurred by the employee through a part-time activity within the meaning of Section 3 No. 26 EStG are only to be taken into account insofar as they include the tax-free annual amount of DM 2,400 and - possibly together with the business expenses for other professional activities - the employee Exceed the lump sum of DM 2000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 18 Benefits according to the Partial Retirement Act (\u00a7 3 No. 28 EStG) top-up amounts and additional contributions to the statutory pension insurance within the meaning of \u00a7 3 Paragraph 1 No. 1 as well as expenses within the meaning of \u00a7 4 Paragraph 2 Partial Retirement Act are tax-free if the requirements of \u00a7 2 Partial Retirement Act, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Completion of the age of 55, reduction of the regular weekly working hours according to the collective agreement by half"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The agreement on the reduction of working hours must at least cover the period until the employee can claim an old-age pension"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This does not require that this pension be undiminished"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The earliest possible point in time at which an old-age pension can be claimed is the age of 60"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Top-up amounts and additional contributions to the statutory pension insurance are tax-free, even if they exceed the minimum amounts specified in the Partial Retirement Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The benefits are also tax-free if the employer's entitlement to funding to the Federal Employment Agency according to Section 5 Paragraph 1 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "if the vacated full or partial job is not filled again"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax exemption, on the other hand, no longer comes into consideration at the end of the calendar month in which the employee ended the partial retirement or reached the age of 65 (Section 5 (1) No. 1 Old Age Part-Time Work)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The top-up amounts in accordance with Section 3 Paragraph 1 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Zur Aufzeichnung und Bescheinigung der steuerfreien Leistungen &gt; \u00a7 41 Abs 1 und \u00a7 41b Abs 1 Satz 2 Nr 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 19 Tool money (\u00a7 3 No. 30 EStG) The tax exemption is limited to the reimbursement of expenses incurred by the employee through the operational use of his own tools"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In general, only hand tools that are used for easier handling, for manufacturing or for processing an object are to be regarded as tools; Musical instruments and their individual parts belong as well as typewriters and personal computers etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "not to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tools are also used for operational purposes if the tools are used within the scope of the employment relationship outside the employer's premises, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "on a construction site"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Without individual proof of the actual expenses, lump-sum compensation is tax-free, provided that it covers the regular deductions for tool wear, the usual operating, maintenance and repair costs for the tools and the costs of transporting the tools between the home and the place of use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "To the extent that compensation is paid for the employee's time, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "for the cleaning and maintenance of the tools incumbent on him, they are part of the taxable wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 20 Provision of typical work clothing (\u00a7 3 No. 31 EStG) (1) According to \u00a7 3 No. 31 first half-sentence EStG, not only the provision, but also the transfer of typical work clothing by the employer is tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Erh\u00e4lt der Arbeitnehmer die Berufsbekleidung von seinem Arbeitgeber zus\u00e4tzlich zum ohnehin geschuldeten Arbeitslohn (&gt;R 21c), so ist anzunehmen, da\u00df es sich um typische Berufskleidung handelt, wenn nicht das Gegenteil offensichtlich ist"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Typical work clothing includes items of clothing that are tailored as protective clothing to the respective occupation or according to their z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "uniform quality or permanently affixed identification by means of a company emblem can objectively fulfill a professional function if their private use is as good as impossible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Normal shoes and underwear are e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "no typical work clothes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The tax exemption according to \u00a7 3 No. 31 second half sentence EStG is limited to the reimbursement of the expenses incurred by the employee through the professional use of typical work clothing in cases in which the employee z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "according to accident prevention regulations, collective bargaining agreement or works agreement has a right to the provision of work clothes, which is replaced by cash remuneration for operational reasons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The cash redemption of an obligation to provide typical work clothing is z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "operationally justified if the procurement of the garments by the employee is more advantageous for the employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Flat-rate cash redemptions are tax-free as long as they compensate for the regular deductions for wear and tear and the usual maintenance and repair costs of typical work clothing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 21 Collective transport of employees between home and work (Section 3 No. 32 EStG) Free or discounted transport of an employee between home and work in a bus or minibus used by the employer or a third party on his behalf is tax-free provided passenger vehicles, if this transport is necessary for the operational use of the employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The need for collective transport is z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "to be accepted in cases in which the transport by public transport could not be carried out or only with a disproportionately high expenditure of time, the employees are deployed in constantly changing places of work or different positions in a spacious work area or the work process requires the workers transported to start work at the same time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 21a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Accommodation and care for children not required to attend school (Section 3 No. 33 EStG) (1) Additional employer benefits for housing, including board and lodging, and care for children of the employee not required to attend school in kindergartens or comparable institutions are tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Services for the mediation of accommodation and care by third parties are not tax-exempt"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Contributions by the employer to a kindergarten or comparable institution through which he acquires the right to occupy the children of his employees without an application process and waiting time are not attributed to the employees as a pecuniary benefit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) It is irrelevant whether the placement and care takes place in company or external kindergartens"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Similar facilities are z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "School kindergartens, day care centers, day nurseries, child minders, maternity mothers and all-day care centers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The facility must be suitable for the accommodation and care of children at the same time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The sole care in the household, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "by nannies, housemaids or family members is not sufficient"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as employer benefits also enable a child to be taught, they are not tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to services that are not directly used to care for a child, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "transportation between home and kindergarten"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) Only benefits for the accommodation and care of children who are not of school age are eligible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "These are children who have not yet reached the age of 6 or who have reached the age of 6 after June 30 in the current calendar year, unless they started school earlier or who reached the age of 6 before July 1 in the current calendar year, in the months of January to July of this year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "School-age children are on an equal footing with children who are not of school age, as long as they are postponed from attending school because they are not ready for school"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) Benefits in kind to the employee that go beyond the tax-free area according to \u00a7 3 No. 33 EStG are to be added to the wages with the value according to \u00a7 8 Paragraph 2 Sentence 1 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Cash benefits to the employee are only tax-free if the employee has proven to the employer that they have been used for the intended purpose"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer must keep the original evidence as evidence for the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 21b"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Travel allowances (Section 3 No. 34 EStG) (1) In addition to the wages owed anyway, any allowances made by the employer for the employee's expenses for journeys between home and work place are tax-exempt under the following conditions: Scheduled services"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Expenses for the use of private transport or taxis are not subsidized"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The driving authorization must be valid for at least part of the route between home and work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Any further driving authorization is irrelevant if its value is of relatively little importance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to other advantages that are associated with driving authorization, for example"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The extent to which the employee actually uses his driving authorization to drive between home and work is irrelevant; R 42 remains unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Private use of the driving license by the employee or his family members is irrelevant if its scope is of relatively minor importance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Any additional use granted by the employer, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the use of the ticket as a parking permit for the company premises"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer's subsidies may not exceed the employee's expenses in the relevant period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The relevant period is the duration of the employment relationship in the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The free or discounted granting of a driving license on public transport in regular service by the employer is also tax-free, provided that this service is provided in addition to the wages owed anyway"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Paragraph 1 No. 2 and 3 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) As proof of the requirements within the meaning of Paragraph 1 Nos. 1 and 4, the employer must be presented with the tickets used or a declaration by the employee stating that journeys between home and work with public transport in a regular service are just as high or higher is than the subsidy granted by the employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, the requirements within the meaning of Paragraph 1 No. 2 and 3 are to be regarded as fulfilled, unless the contrary is obvious"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee must notify the employer of any circumstance that affects the tax exemption of the travel allowance or the driver's license"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer must keep the tickets, declarations and notifications presented to him as proof of the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 21c"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Employer benefits provided in addition to the wages owed anyway The additionality requirement requires that the intended performance be added to the wages owed by the employer if the relevant purpose is not met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An earmarked service is only provided in addition to the wages owed anyway if the employee would not receive the service without earmarking"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is therefore crucial that only the employee who uses it for the beneficiary purpose can receive the service"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a specific service is provided with crediting the agreed wages or by converting (reallocating) the agreed wages, there is no additional service; the agreed wages remain unchanged"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This applies even if the conversion takes place on the basis of a collective agreement opening clause"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "There is also no additional benefit if it is offset against a voluntary special payment, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Christmas bonus, is provided"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the additional benefit is owed by the employer on your part or whether it is granted voluntarily"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, it is harmless if the employer offers a variety of specific services to choose from"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 21d"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Arbeitslohn aus geringf\u00fcgigen Besch\u00e4ftigungsverh\u00e4ltnissen (\u00a7 3 Nr 39 EStG) (1)Der Arbeitslohn (&gt;R 70) aus geringf\u00fcgigen Besch\u00e4ftigungsverh\u00e4ltnissen ist steuerfrei, wenn der Arbeitgeber f\u00fcr den jeweiligen Lohnzahlungszeitraum einen pauschalen Arbeitgeberbeitrag zur Rentenversicherung in H\u00f6he von 12 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of the wages and the total of the other income of the employee is not positive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The definition of income in Section 2 (1) EStG is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also includes income from other or former employment relationships, interest income, insofar as it exceeds the income-related expenses and the saver's allowance, the income share for pensions after deduction of income-related expenses and maintenance payments of the divorced spouse, insofar as he can claim the special expenses deduction for this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter whether taxes are actually payable on the additional income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Tax-free income (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "according to \u00a7 3 No. 26 EStG) and flat-rate taxed wages are excluded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Income of the spouse is not to be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2)Die Steuerfreiheit im Lohnsteuerabzugsverfahren setzt neben der Pflicht zur Entrichtung des pauschalen Arbeitgeberbeitrags zur Rentenversicherung die Vorlage einer Freistellungsbescheinigung (&gt;R 113a) durch den Arbeitnehmer voraus"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Die Steuerfreiheit kann auch noch im Veranlagungsverfahren beantragt werden (&gt; \u00a7 46 Abs 2 Nr 8 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 22 Transit monies, reimbursement of expenses (Section 3 No. 50 EStG) (1) Passing monies or reimbursement of expenses exist if the employee makes the expenses for the account of the employer, regardless of whether this is done in the name of the employer or in his own name and the expenses are billed individually"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee's expenses are to be assessed as if the employer had made them himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Die Steuerfreiheit der durchlaufenden Gelder oder des Auslagenersatzes nach \u00a7 3 Nr 50 EStG ist hiernach stets dann ausgeschlossen, wenn die Ausgaben durch das Dienstverh\u00e4ltnis des Arbeitnehmers veranla\u00dft sind (&gt;R70)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) Flat-rate reimbursement of expenses regularly leads to wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "As an exception, the flat-rate reimbursement of expenses can remain tax-free if it recurs regularly and the employee provides detailed evidence of the expenses incurred for a period of 12 months"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The flat-rate reimbursement of expenses remains tax-free until the circumstances change significantly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 23 - unoccupied - R 23a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Tax-free rental benefits (\u00a7 3 No. 59) Tax-free are rental benefits that are granted within the framework of an employment relationship and that are based on funding under the Second Housing Act or the Housing Act for Saarland"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Rental advantages resulting from the use of housing welfare funds from public budgets are also tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of an apartment that was built without funds from public budgets, the following applies: The rental benefits in the context of an employment relationship are tax-free if the apartment would have been eligible for funding from public budgets at the time the employee moved into it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Section 3 No. 59 EStG is therefore only applicable to apartments that were built during the period of validity of the above-mentioned housing construction laws, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "for year of construction from 1957 onwards It does not have to be checked whether the employee is eligible as a tenant of a subsidized apartment based on his income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The amount of the tax exemption is limited to the rental benefits that would result from the subsidy under the above-mentioned housing construction laws"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Section 3 No. 59 EStG is therefore not applicable to apartments for which the funding period has already expired"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the funding period has not yet expired at the time the employee moves into the apartment, a rental advantage is tax-free up to the amount that the employer would have to waive compared to the comparable rent if the construction of the apartment had been subsidized according to the housing construction laws"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax-free partial amount is reduced to the extent that the employer could demand a higher rent according to the funding regulations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When the rental period expires, the tax exemption also expires"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "As far as later permissible rent increases z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "after the end of the funding period with regard to the employment relationship, they must be included in the taxable rental advantage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 24 Future security benefits (\u00a7 3 No. 62 EStG, \u00a7 2 Paragraph 2 No. 3 LStDV) Benefits based on legal obligations (1) In addition to the employer's tax-exempt expenses according to \u00a7 3 No. 62 EStG for securing the future of the employee (\u00a7 2 Paragraph 2 No. 3 Clauses 1 and 2 LStDV) include, in particular, the employer's contribution to the overall social security contribution (pension insurance, health insurance, long-term care insurance, unemployment insurance), employer contributions according to Section 172 (2) SGB VI to a professional pension scheme for employees who, according to Section 6 (1) sentence 1 no 1 SGB VI are exempt from compulsory insurance in the statutory pension insurance, and contributions from the employer according to Section 249b SGB V and Sections 168 (1) no.1b, 172 (3) SGB VI for marginal employees"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to those contribution shares that are paid to foreign social insurance carriers that are comparable to domestic social insurance carriers on the basis of an obligation under foreign law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 3 No. 62 EStG, employee shares in the total social security contribution assumed by the employer in accordance with Section 6 Paragraph 3 Clause 3 of the Payment in Kind Ordinance as well as health insurance contributions that the employer reimburses in accordance with Section 5 Paragraph 2 of the Parental Leave Ordinance or according to the relevant legal provisions of the federal states are also tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, future security payments based on a collective agreement obligation are not tax-exempt under Section 3 No. 62 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When it comes to the question of whether the employer's expenses for securing the future of the employee are based on a legal obligation, for reasons of simplification, the decision of the employee's responsible social insurance agency must be followed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, the tax authorities are not legally bound to this decision"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The following applies to the employer's expenses for the employee's health and long-term care insurance: The employer's contribution parts and grants to health insurance and to the social or private long-term care insurance of an employee who is subject to health insurance are tax-free up to half of the respective contribution rate of the health and long-term care insurance company the employee is insured, in the case of private long-term care insurance up to a maximum of half of the actual long-term care insurance contribution"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Subsidies from the employer for health insurance and for social or private long-term care insurance of an employee who is not subject to health insurance and who is voluntarily insured in the statutory health insurance are tax-free according to Section 3 No. SGB \u200b\u200bXI is obliged to provide a grant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Half of the contributions to health insurance and social long-term care insurance that would have to be paid for an employee subject to health insurance with the health insurance company with which the voluntary membership exists and with the long-term care insurance company established with this health insurance company are therefore tax-free, but no more than half the actual health and long-term care insurance contributions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as fictitious remuneration is decisive for recipients of short-time work allowance or winter absence allowance, the employer's subsidies remain fully tax-free (Section 257 (2) sentence 2 SGB V in conjunction with Section 249 (2) no.3 SGB V)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the wage only exceeds the annual wage limit due to a one-off wage paid and the employee therefore has to pay the maximum contributions to the health and long-term care insurance fund for each month, the employer subsidies are tax-free for reasons of simplification up to half of the maximum contributions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the remuneration paid in the event of illness falls below the monthly income threshold and the employee still has to pay the maximum contributions to the health and care insurance fund for the duration of the continued remuneration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the health and long-term care insurance contributions applicable in accordance with sentence 2 are rounded up to the next full DM amount in accordance with the statutes, then for reasons of simplification, the employer subsidies remain tax-free up to half of the rounded up health and long-term care insurance contributions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Subsidies from the employer to the health and long-term care insurance contributions of an employee who is not subject to health insurance and who has taken out private health and long-term care insurance are also tax-free under Section 3 No. 62 EStG, provided that the employer under Section 257 (2) SGB V and Section 61 (2) SGB \u200b\u200bXI is obliged to provide a grant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Der Anspruch auf den Arbeitgeberzuschu\u00df an den bei einem privaten Krankenversicherungsunternehmen versicherten Arbeitnehmer setzt voraus, da\u00df der private Krankenversicherungsschutz Leistungen zum Inhalt hat, die ihrer Art nach auch im F\u00fcnften Buch Sozialgesetzbuch bestehen (&gt; \u00a7 11 Abs 1 SGB V)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite is not that the private health insurance cover has a certain minimum scope, i.e. extends to all benefits of the fifth book of the Social Security Code; Insofar as private health insurance cover includes other benefits that do not belong to the benefits of the fifth book of the Social Security Code, the part of the contribution attributable to them is not taken into account when calculating the employer's allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Half of the amount resulting from the application of the average general contribution rate of the health insurance funds and the contribution assessment basis is tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the wage only exceeds the annual wage limit due to a one-off wage, or if the wages continued to be paid in the event of illness fall below the monthly contribution assessment limit and the employee still has to pay the maximum contributions, half of the average maximum contributions for statutory health insurance and social long-term care insurance are tax-free for reasons of simplification"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax exemption is subject to sentence 3 in number 2, which applies accordingly, limited to half of the actual contributions, insofar as they are paid for those services that correspond to the services of the fifth and eleventh books of the Social Code"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer may only allow subsidies for private health insurance and private long-term care insurance for the employee to be tax-free if the employee presents a certificate from the insurance company confirming that the requirements of Section 257 (2) a SGB V and Section 61 (1) 6 SGB XI are present and that the contractual benefits are benefits within the meaning of the fifth and eleventh book of the social code"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The certificate must also contain information on the amount of the insurance contribution to be paid for the contractual benefits within the meaning of the fifth and eleventh books of the Social Security Code"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer must keep the certificate as a document for the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer pays the tax-free subsidies directly to the employee, the employee must provide evidence of the appropriate use by means of a certificate from the insurance company stating the actual health and long-term care insurance contributions at the end of each calendar year; the employer must keep this certificate as a document for the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The certificate can be combined with the certificate according to sentences 7 and 8"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Subsidies equivalent to statutory compulsory contributions (3) Pursuant to Section 3 No. 62 Clause 2 EStG, the employer's expenses for securing the future of the employee, which are made on the basis of a statutory obligation, are equivalent to the employer's subsidies that are equivalent to the employee's contributions to life insurance - also for the life insurance taken out with a company pension fund - for voluntary insurance in the statutory pension insurance or for a public-law insurance or pension institution of the occupational group if the employee exempts from the compulsory insurance in the statutory pension insurance according to one of the following provisions has been exempted at his own request: Section 18 (3) of the Act on Raising Income Limits in Social Insurance and Unemployment Insurance and Amending the Twelfth Ordinance on the Structure of Social Insurance of 13 August 1952 (B. GBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "437), Article 2 \u00a7 1 of the New Employee Insurance Regulation Act of 23 2 1957 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "88, 1074) or Article 2 \u00a7 1 of the Miners' Pension Insurance New Regulation Act of 21 5 1957 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "533), in the version valid up to June 30, 1965, Section 7 (2) of the Employee Insurance Act in the version of Article 1 of the New Employee Insurance Regulation Act of 23 2 1957 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "88, 1074), Article 2 \u00a7 1 of the New Employee Insurance Regulation or Article 2 \u00a7 1 of the Miners' Pension Insurance New Regulation Act, each in the version of the Pension Insurance Amendment Act of 9 6 1965 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "476), Article 2 \u00a7 1 of the Second Pension Insurance Amendment Act of 23 December 1966 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "745), Article 2 \u00a7 1 of the New Employee Insurance Regulation Act or Article 2 \u00a7 1 of the Miners' Pension Insurance New Regulation Act, each in the version of the 1967 Financial Amendment Act of 21 December 1967 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "1259), Article 2 Paragraph 1 Paragraph 2 of the New Employee Insurance Regulation Act or Article 2 Paragraph 1 Paragraph 1 a of the Miners' Pension Insurance New Regulation Law, each in the version of the Third Pension Insurance Amendment Act of July 28, 1969 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "956), \u00a7 20 of the Act on Social Insurance of 28 June 1990 (Journal of Laws of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of the German Democratic Republic I No. 38 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "486) in conjunction with \u00a7 231a SGB VI in the version of the law for the establishment of legal unity in the statutory pension and accident insurance (Pension Transition Act - R\u00dcG) of 25 7 1991 (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "1606)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Subsidies from the employer within the meaning of Section 3 No. 62 Sentence 2 EStG are not available if the employee is exempt from statutory pension insurance by law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The contributions of the employee for a voluntary insurance in the statutory pension insurance of the employees are otherwise equal to contributions for the voluntary insurance in the workers pension insurance or in the miners' pension insurance or for self-insurance in the statutory pension insurance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Amount of tax-exempt subsidies, evidence (4) The tax-exemption of subsidies is limited in principle to the amount that the employer would have to spend as employer's contribution to the statutory pension insurance if the employee was not exempted from statutory insurance would"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as the employer pays the tax-free subsidies directly to the employee, the employee has to prove the appropriate use by means of a corresponding certificate from the insurance company by April 30 of the following calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The certificate must be kept as a document for the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 25 - vacant - R 26 purchasing power compensation (Section 3 No. 64 EStG) (1) If a domestic employer grants a purchasing power compensation to an employee outside the public service, he remains tax-free within the framework of paragraph 2 if the employee is in an area outside of Germany is posted and has a domicile within the meaning of \u00a7 8 AO or habitual residence within the meaning of \u00a7 9 AO for a limited period of time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A posting for a limited period of time is to be assumed if the employee is expected to return after the work has ended"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter whether the employee actually returns or not"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The extent of the tax exemption of the purchasing power equalization is determined by the rates of the purchasing power surcharge on the foreign service salary in the public service"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The purchasing power surcharges applicable for the individual countries are published in Part I of the Federal Tax Gazette"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) The surcharges relate to the foreign duty station of a representation of the Federal Republic of Germany and apply, unless other surcharges have been specified, to the entire consular district of the representation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The consular districts of the representations can be found in the list of representations of the Federal Republic of Germany abroad, subject to subsequent changes that will be published in the Federal Gazette"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) The regional limitation of the surcharge rates also applies to the tax exemption according to \u00a7 3 No. 64 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For a country that is not covered by a representation of the Federal Republic of Germany, however, the surcharge rate can be applied that has been set for a comparable consular district of a neighboring country"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(5) The surcharge rates are set to 60 per cent in the public service"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the remuneration that is due for use in Germany and the remuneration abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Since there is usually no comparable assessment basis outside the public service, the tax-free part of the purchasing power equalization is to be determined by applying a corresponding discount rate to the total remuneration including the purchasing power equalization"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter whether the salaries are paid in Germany or abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The discount rate is calculated using the following formula: surcharge rate x 600 1000 + 6 x surcharge rate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the application of the discount rate results in a higher amount than the purchasing power compensation actually granted, only the lower amount is tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The total remuneration to which the discount rate is to be applied includes non-tax-free travel expense allowances and tax-free allowances for additional expenses in the case of double housekeeping"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(6) If a surcharge rate is increased retrospectively, the employer is entitled to reopen the pay slips that have already been completed and to reimburse any excess wage tax with the next following wage payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In doing so, Section 41c (2) and (3) EStG must be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The reduction of a surcharge rate is to be taken into account for the first time in the wage accounting of the wages that are paid for a wage payment period beginning after the publication of the reduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 27 Insolvency insurance (\u00a7 3 No. 65 EStG) (1) The tax exemption only applies to any contributions made by the insolvency insurance provider to a pension fund or to a life insurance company to insure its obligations in the event of a claim"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The funds for the implementation of the insolvency insurance are raised on the basis of public law obligations through contributions from all employers who have directly promised company pension benefits or who carry out a company pension through a relief fund or direct insurance (Section 10 of the Act to Improve the company pension scheme)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The contributions to the insolvency insurance agency, as expenses of the employer for securing the future of the employee, which are made on the basis of a legal obligation, are tax-exempt income within the meaning of Section 3 No. 62 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) The insolvency insurance of the company pension scheme does not create new or higher claims, but only protects existing claims against insolvency"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The pension services to be provided in insolvency cases by the insolvency insurance company or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "in the case of reinsurance, the pension fund or the life insurance company therefore generally retain their tax character, as if the insolvency case had not occurred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "That means z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "that pension benefits to an employee that are based on a pension commitment or that should be carried out through a relief fund, even after the occurrence of insolvency and the assumption of the benefits by an insurance company, belong to the income from employment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 28 Interest savings and interest subsidies (Section 3 No. 68 EStG 1987, Section 52 EStG) Insofar as Section 3 No. 68 EStG continues to apply after the transitional provision in Section 52 (8) EStG, the instructions in Section 28 LStR 1996 continue to apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 29 Tax exemptions according to other laws and contracts - unoccupied - R 30 Tax exemption for surcharges for Sunday, holiday or night work (\u00a7 3b EStG) Holiday or night work is paid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Such a surcharge can be regulated in a law, a statutory ordinance, a collective agreement, a works agreement or an individual employment contract"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is harmless if, in addition to a surcharge for Sunday, public holiday or night work, which is also overtime, no separate overtime remuneration or a basic wage is paid to compensate for the overtime"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The designation of the wage supplements is irrelevant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Cash compensation for a time-off entitlement or excess free time or surcharges for overtime or for difficulties or allowances other than working hours that are only calculated according to certain periods of time are not subsidized wage surcharges"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Section 3b EStG is also applicable to employees whose wages are taxed at a flat rate according to Section 40a EStG or are tax-free according to Section 3 No. 39 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Basic wage (2) According to Section 3b (2) EStG, the basic wage is the entitlement to regular wages for one working hour that the employee earns for the respective wage payment period on the basis of his regular working hours"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The following applies in detail: Definition of the basic wage a) According to R 115, the entitlement to regular wages must be distinguished from the entitlement to other payments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as back payments or advance payments are part of the current wages, they increase the current wages of the wage payment periods for which they are paid in arrears or in advance; Section 41c of the Income Tax Act applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "b) Entitlements to remuneration in kind, expense allowances and capital-forming benefits are part of the basic wage if they are ongoing wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to claims for supplements and allowances that are paid during regular working hours due to the special nature of the work, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Difficulty allowances or shift supplements, as well as wage supplements for work in the period not favored by Section 3b EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Regular working hours are the normal working hours agreed for the respective employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "c) The basic wage does not include claims to remuneration for overtime (overtime remuneration), surcharges for work on Sundays, public holidays or night work in the time favored in accordance with Section 3b of the Income Tax Act, also to the extent that they are taxable because the surcharge rates specified therein are exceeded Tax-free payments and payments that are taxed at a flat rate according to \u00a7 40 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Determination of the basic wage entitlement for the respective wage payment period a) The basic wage agreed for the respective wage payment period within the meaning of number 1 is to be determined (basic basic wage)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the wage supplements to be paid for the wage payment period are based on the circumstances of an earlier wage payment period, the earlier wage payment period must also be used to determine the basic basic wage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the surcharges are based on the work performed in an earlier wage payment period but based on the basic wage for the current wage payment period, the basic basic wage for the current wage payment period is to be used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the wage agreement relates to periods other than the wage payment period, the basic basic wage is to be determined by copying the agreed hourly wage with the number of hours of regular working hours in the wage payment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "With a monthly wage payment period, the number of hours of regular working time is 435 times the weekly working time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Loss of working hours, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "due to vacation or illness, are not considered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "b) In addition, the part of the basic wage due for the respective wage payment period within the meaning of number 1 is to be determined, the amount of which does not depend on circumstances that can be determined in advance (basic wage supplements), e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the entitlement to hardship allowances or late work supplements that only exist for individual hours of work or the entitlement to travel allowance depending on the number of actual working days"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "These basic wage supplements are to be set at the amounts that the employee is actually entitled to for the respective wage payment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Conversion of the basic wage entitlement Basic basic wage (number 2 letter a) and basic wage supplements (number 2 letter b) must be added together and divided by the number of hours of regular working hours in the respective wage payment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a monthly wage payment period, the divisor is to be set at 435 times the weekly working time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The result is the basic wage, which is decisive for the limitation of the tax-free portion of the surcharges for Sunday, public holiday and night work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If no regular working hours have been agreed, the calculation of the basic wage is based on the hours actually worked in the wage payment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of piece wage recipients, the conversion of the piece wage to an hourly wage can be omitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a surcharge for Sunday, public holiday or night work of less than one hour is paid, the basic wage must be reduced accordingly when determining the tax-free surcharge for this period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Night work on Sundays and public holidays (3) If night work is performed on Sundays and public holidays or during the time belonging to these days in accordance with Section 3b Paragraph 3 No. 2 EStG, the tax exemption according to Section 3b Paragraph 1 No. 3b para 1 no 1 EStG can be claimed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax-free surcharge rate for night work must be added together with the tax-free surcharge rate for Sunday or holiday work, even if only one surcharge is paid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Public holidays within the meaning of Section 3b (1) No. 3 EStG include Easter and Pentecost Sundays even if they are not expressly mentioned as holidays in the regulations applicable at the place of work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a surcharge for Sunday or holiday work is paid for night work that follows or precedes a Sunday or public holiday, this is to be treated as a supplement for night work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Work on public holidays on Sundays (4) If a Sunday is also a public holiday, a surcharge can only be paid tax-free up to the amount of the relevant holiday surcharge"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if only a Sunday surcharge is paid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Coincidence with overtime bonuses (5) If the employee is entitled under labor law to bonuses for Sunday, public holiday or night work and to bonuses for overtime and overtime is performed as Sunday, public holiday or night work, a distinction must be made between the following cases: Considered surcharges paid for Sunday, public holiday or night work as well as for overtime; only the applicable supplement for Sunday, public holiday or night work is paid, which is the same as or higher than the supplement for overtime; only the overtime allowance is paid; A uniform surcharge (mixed surcharge) is paid that is higher than the surcharges in question, but lower than their total; A uniform surcharge (mixed surcharge) is paid which is higher than the sum of the surcharges in question"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the cases of numbers 1 and 2, the amount of the surcharges paid is to be treated as a surcharge for Sunday, public holiday or night work that corresponds to the surcharge that is considered under labor law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of number 3, there is no surcharge within the meaning of \u00a7 3b EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the cases of numbers 4 and 5, the mixed surcharge is to be divided in the ratio of the individual surcharges in question into a portion that is favored according to \u00a7 3b EStG and a portion that is not favored"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If no surcharge has been agreed for work on Sundays, public holidays or night work, because e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Porters or night watchmen regularly perform their work at the privileged times, no part of the overtime allowance paid for these activities remains tax-free according to Section 3b of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Proof of preferential working hours (6) Only supplements that are paid for work actually performed on Sundays, public holidays or night work are exempt from tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Washing times, shift handover times and breaks belonging to the agreed and remunerated working hours are considered to be privileged working hours within the meaning of Section 3b EStG, insofar as they fall within the privileged period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Evidence of the work actually performed on Sundays, public holidays or night work must be provided in each individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Is a uniform remuneration for the basic wage and the supplements for Sunday, public holiday or night work, possibly including overtime and overtime, paid because Sunday, public holiday or night work is usually performed, and is therefore the Sunday, public holiday or night hours actually worked are not recorded, the surcharges for Sunday, public holiday or night work included in the standard remuneration are generally not tax-free according to Section 3b of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Zu einem erleichterten Nachweis &gt; Absatz 7 Sind die Einzelanschreibung und die Einzelbezahlung der geleisteten Sonntags-, Feiertags- oder Nachtarbeit wegen der Besonderheiten der Arbeit und der Lohnzahlungen nicht m\u00f6glich, so darf das Betriebsst\u00e4ttenfinanzamt den Teil der Verg\u00fctung, der als steuerfreier Zuschlag f\u00fcr Sonntags-, Feiertags- oder Nachtarbeit anzuerkennen ist, von Fall zu Fall feststellen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the interest of a uniform treatment of employees in the same professional branch, the establishment tax office may only make the determination on the instructions of the regional tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The instruction is reserved to the highest state tax authority if the relevant regulation for the occupational branch in question does not only apply in the district of the regional tax office responsible for the permanent establishment tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A determination according to sentence 6 does not come into consideration for those regulations that do not set flat-rate surcharges, but rather declare certain parts of a current wage measured according to time periods as surcharges for Sunday, holiday or night work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Lump-sum installments (7) If surcharges for work on Sundays, public holidays or night work are made as an ongoing lump sum, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Monthly flat rate is paid and if the surcharges that would have to be paid for the individually documented times for Sunday, holiday or night work on the basis of individual calculations are made later, the current flat rate or part of it can be left tax-free, if the tax-free amount is not calculated according to percentages higher than the percentages specified in \u00a7 3b EStG, the tax-free amount is calculated according to the average basic wage and the average Sunday, holiday or night work actually incurred in the period of the calendar year, offset against the individually determined Surcharges are made before the wage tax certificate is drawn up and therefore regularly at the latest at the end of the calendar year or when the employee leaves the employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "To determine the surcharges to be proven in detail, the respective wage payment period must be used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax-free part of the individually determined surcharges must also be determined and the too little or too much withheld wage tax due to the lump-sum payment is to be compensated; in the lump-sum payment, it can be seen which surcharges are to be settled individually - separately according to surcharges for Sunday, holiday or night work and according to which percentages of the basic wage the surcharges have been calculated, the lump sum payment is actually a surcharge that is paid in addition to the basic wage; a flat-rate payment calculated from the wages is not a surcharge"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the individual determination shows that the surcharge due to the employee due to the work actually performed on Sundays, public holidays or night work is higher than the lump sum payment, a higher amount can only be tax-free if and to the extent that the surcharge is actually paid additionally; a mere reduction of the taxable wages by the excess tax exemption is not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "These regulations apply mutatis mutandis if only the exact determination of the tax-free amount at the time of payment of the surcharge is difficult and it can only be made up at a later point in time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 31 Bewertung der Sachbez\u00fcge (\u00a7 8 Abs 2 EStG) Allgemeines (1)Flie\u00dft dem Arbeitnehmer Arbeitslohn in Form von Sachbez\u00fcgen zu, so sind diese ebenso wie Barlohnzahlungen entweder dem laufenden Arbeitslohn oder den sonstigen Bez\u00fcgen zuzuordnen (&gt;R 115)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The monetary value is decisive for the taxation of benefits in kind"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee does not receive the remuneration in kind free of charge, the difference between the monetary value of the remuneration in kind and the actual remuneration is taxable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Der Geldwert ist entweder durch Einzelbewertung zu ermitteln (&gt; Absatz 2) oder mit einem amtlichen Sachbezugswert anzusetzen (&gt; Absatz 4)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Besondere Bewertungsvorschriften gelten nach \u00a7 8 Abs 3 EStG f\u00fcr den Bezug von Waren oder Dienstleistungen, die vom Arbeitgeber nicht \u00fcberwiegend f\u00fcr den Bedarf seiner Arbeitnehmer hergestellt, vertrieben oder erbracht werden, soweit diese Sachbez\u00fcge nicht nach \u00a7 40 EStG pauschal versteuert werden (&gt;R 32), sowie nach \u00a7 19a Abs 8 EStG f\u00fcr den Bezug f\u00fcr Verm\u00f6gensbeteiligungen (&gt;R 77)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Einzelbewertung von Sachbez\u00fcgen (2)Sachbez\u00fcge, f\u00fcr die keine amtlichen Sachbezugswerte (&gt; Absatz 4) festgesetzt sind und die nicht nach \u00a7 8 Abs 3 EStG (&gt;R 32) zu bewerten sind, sind nach \u00a7 8 Abs 2 Satz 1 EStG mit den um \u00fcbliche Preisnachl\u00e4sse geminderten \u00fcblichen Endpreisen am Abgabeort im Zeitpunkt der Abgabe anzusetzen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This is the price that is actually paid in general business transactions by end consumers in the majority of sales cases at the point of delivery for similar goods or services"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It includes sales tax and other price components"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer offers the goods or services to be valued under comparable conditions to a not inconsiderable extent to third-party end consumers at a price lower than the usual price, this price is to be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of an extensive range of goods from which third-party end consumers are excluded, the usual price of a product can also be determined on the basis of representative surveys of the relative price difference for the most common individual items in each product group"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The place where the employer offers the employee the benefit in kind is decisive for the price determination"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the usual price cannot be determined at this location, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "because goods of the same type are not given to third-party end consumers there, the usual price must be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the order and delivery days are different, the conditions on the order day are decisive for the price determination"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee receives a product or service that is to be valued in accordance with Section 8 (2) sentence 1 of the Income Tax Act (EStG), for reasons of simplification it can be assessed at 96%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "des Endpreises (&gt;R 32 Abs 2) bewertet werden, zu dem sie der Abgebende oder dessen Abnehmer fremden Letztverbrauchern im allgemeinen Gesch\u00e4ftsverkehr anbietet"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "DM 50 exemption limit (3) When checking the DM 50 exemption limit, the benefits to be assessed in accordance with Section 8 (2) sentence 1 EStG, which are taxed at a flat rate according to Section 40 EStG, are excluded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The exemption limit does not apply to future security payments by the employer within the meaning of Section 2 (2) No. 3 LStDV, which are also available if the employer as the policyholder provides the employee with insurance protection"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Official non-cash benefits (4) Official non-cash benefits are determined by the non-cash benefits ordinance, by paragraph 10 sentence 3, the announcement of the value of the food in shipping and fishing or by decrees of the highest state tax authorities according to \u00a7 8 paragraph 2 sentence 8 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Unless the provisions of Section 8 (3) of the Income Tax Act (EStG) are to be applied, the official non-cash benefits shall apply without exception to the non-cash benefits for which they are intended"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The official non-cash benefits also apply if higher or lower values \u200b\u200bhave been set for benefits in kind in a collective agreement, a works agreement or in an employment contract"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Exceptionally, they also apply to cash payments if they are only paid occasionally or temporarily, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "in the case of daily external employment, for the duration of an illness or a vacation, and if the cash remuneration does not compensate more than the actual value of the remuneration in kind; If the cash remuneration exceeds the actual value of the remuneration in kind, the cash remuneration is to be used as a basis for taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Unterkunft oder Wohnung (5)F\u00fcr die Bewertung einer Unterkunft, die keine Wohnung ist (&gt; Absatz 65 Satz 2 bis 4), ist der amtliche Sachbezugswert nach der Sachbezugsverordnung ma\u00dfgebend"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In principle, the official non-cash payment value is to be applied even if the employer has rented the accommodation provided to the employee and, if necessary, furnished it with furnishings"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Shared accommodation exists if the accommodation has the character of a dormitory, for example through shared washrooms or shared kitchens, or is subject to access restrictions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(6) Unless the provisions of Section 8 (3) EStG are applicable, the rental value customary in the location is decisive for the valuation of an apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An apartment is a self-contained unit of rooms in which an independent household can be run"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is essential that there is a water supply and disposal system, at least a cooking facility comparable to a kitchen, and a toilet"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Then z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A one-room apartment with a kitchenette and toilet as an adjoining room is an apartment, whereas a living room is accommodation if the bathroom, toilet and kitchen are shared"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The rent that is customary for a comparable apartment in terms of year of construction, type, size, equipment, condition and location (comparative rent) is to be set as the local rental value."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In cases in which the employer rents comparable apartments to a not inconsiderable extent to third parties at a lower rent than the usual rent, the lower rent is to be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The comparative rent applies regardless of whether the apartment is z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "is available as a work or service apartment owned by the employer or has been rented by the employer on the basis of a right of occupancy"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Legal rental price restrictions must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, if these preclude a rent increase request, this only applies if the relevant starting rent has not fallen below the rental value customary in the location or the legally permissible maximum rent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer gives the employee an apartment abroad as part of a foreign activity, the local rent is 18%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of wages without purchasing power compensation, this apartment is 18 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of wages without purchasing power compensation plus 10 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the usual local rent beyond that"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Canteen meals and meal vouchers (7) The following applies to the evaluation of meals that are given to employees on working days: Meals that are given by a canteen, restaurant or comparable facility operated by the employer must have the relevant official remuneration value according to the non-cash benefits ordinance to rate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 8 (3) of the Income Tax Act (EStG), this only applies if the majority of the meals are not prepared for the employees"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Meals that the employees receive in a canteen, restaurant or comparable facility not operated by the employer must, subject to number 4, also be valued at the relevant official remuneration value if the employer provides cash grants or other payments to the meals based on a contractual agreement distributing entity, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "contributes to cheaper meals through the use of rooms, energy or furnishings"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is not necessary that the meals are first given to the employer as part of a chain transaction and then by him to the employees"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the cases of numbers 1 and 2, a pecuniary benefit is to be recorded as wages if and to the extent that the price paid by the employee for a meal (including sales tax) falls below the relevant official value in kind"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If, in the case of number 2, the employer's benefits consist of cash grants in the form of meal vouchers (meal vouchers, restaurant checks) that are distributed by the employer to the employees and taken in payment by a restaurant or comparable facility (acceptance point) when a meal is served, so The following applies: a) It is not the meal ticket with its offset value, but, subject to letter b, the meal with the relevant value in kind, if aa) a meal is actually served"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Food is only to be recognized as a meal if it is suitable for immediate consumption or intended for consumption during the meal breaks, bb) only one meal token is accepted in payment per day for each meal, cc) the offset value of the meal token does not exceed the official value in kind of a lunch exceeds more than 6 DM and dd) the meal ticket is not issued to employees who are on a business trip or who are changing jobs or who are driving"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if there are no direct contractual relationships between the employer and the acceptance point because a company is involved that issues the food tokens"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In order to meet the requirements of the double letter bb, the employer must specify the days of absence for each employee, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "as a result of business trips, vacation or illness and to reclaim the food stamps issued for these days or to reduce the number of food stamps to be issued in the following month by the number of days of absence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The obligation to determine the days of absence and to adjust the number of food stamps in the following month does not apply to employees who travel on an average of no more than three working days per calendar month in the calendar year if none of these employees receives more than 15 food stamps in the calendar month"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "b) If the employer's services consist exclusively of the surrender of food tokens, the set-off value of the food tokens must also be set as wages under the conditions of letter a, if this value falls below the monetary benefit according to number 3"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "c) If the employment contract is changed so that the employee receives food tokens instead of cash, the cash wages are reduced accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The food stamps are to be set at the value that results from the letters a or b"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Without changing the employment contract, the exchange of cash wages for food stamps does not lead to a reduction in the taxable cash wage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the amount by which the cash wages paid is reduced is to be regarded as payment for the meal or meal ticket and to be deducted from the value according to number 5 letters a or b"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "d) The food tokens redeemed by acceptance points do not need to be returned to the employer and do not need to be kept by him if the employer receives a statement showing how many food tokens have been redeemed with what offset value and keeps them"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies if a food stamp issuer is involved and the employer receives and stores a corresponding statement from it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer provides employees with different meals at different prices, either partially or free of charge, or provides services according to number 2 to make meals cheaper and collects wage tax at a flat rate according to Section 40 (2) of the Income Tax Act, the monetary benefit can be based on the average value of flat rate taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Average taxation does not have to be carried out on a daily basis; it can extend over the entire wage payment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Does the employer only offer certain meals to some of its employees, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "in a boardroom, these meals are not included in the average"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer has several canteens, the average value must be determined for each individual canteen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the determination of the average value is particularly complex because of the amount of data to be recorded, the determination of the average value can be carried out for a representative period of time and, in the case of a large number of canteens, for a representative selection of the canteens"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In principle, the employer must provide evidence of the payment made by the employee in a verifiable form"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The individual proof of the payments is only not required a) if it is guaranteed that aa) the employee's payment for a meal does not fall below the proportionate official remuneration value or bb) according to number 4 the value of the meal ticket is to be recorded as wages or b) if the employer uses the average calculation according to number 5"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Meals for special occasions (8) The following applies to the tax registration and evaluation of meals that the employer or a third party at his instigation gives to employees for special occasions: Meals that are given to employees in the overwhelming operational interest of the employer , are not part of wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This applies to meals as part of conventional company events in accordance with R 72 for a so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Work lunches within the meaning of R 73, Paragraph 2, as well as for the participation of employees in business-related entertainment within the meaning of Section 4, Paragraph 5, Clause 1, No. 2 of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Meals that are used for the usual meals for employees on the occasion of or during a business trip, driving activity, job change activity within the meaning of R 37 Paragraph 3 to 5 or in the context of double housekeeping within the meaning of Section 9 Paragraph 1 Sentence 3 No. 5 EStG or R 43 Paragraph 5 are to be set at the relevant official value in kind according to the non-cash benefits ordinance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer arranges for a meal to be served if he has determined the day and place of the meal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "To do this, he must contact the company that is to provide the employee with meals in writing before the employee starts working outside the country"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is not sufficient for the employer to authorize the employee to eat at one or - for example with the involvement of a voucher organization - at several contract restaurants on his own account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Do business trips require due to their special character (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Conferences) require special organizational preparation, the provision of meals by third parties is also considered to have been initiated by the employer if the employer has commissioned a third party to organize the business trip, including catering"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer has arranged for the delivery of meals, it is irrelevant how the bill is settled"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Sentences 1 to 6 also apply to the serving of meals during an educational measure within the meaning of R 74 Paragraph 1 R 73 Paragraph 2 remains unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Meals that the employer gives to his employees in return for making the individual work available are to be stated at their actual price"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the cases of numbers 2 and 3, a monetary benefit is to be recorded as wages if and to the extent that the price paid by the employee (including sales tax) falls below the relevant value of the meal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A remuneration agreed between the employer and the employee must also be offset against the payment in kind if this remuneration is withheld from the tax-free travel expense allowance to which the employee is entitled or from the net wage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The amount of the travel expense allowance and the wages to be certified on the income tax card are not changed by the payment offset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer or a third party at his instigation provides only a meal but no drink, the remuneration that the employee pays for a drink at the meal does not count towards the value in kind for the meal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Provision of motor vehicles (9) If the employer or, due to the employment relationship, a third party provides the employee with a motor vehicle free of charge for private use, the following applies: The employer has the private use value of 1% per month"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of the domestic list price of the motor vehicle"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the motor vehicle can also be used for journeys between home and work, this possibility of use is independent of the use of the vehicle for private journeys in addition to 003 percent per month"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of the domestic list price of the motor vehicle for every kilometer of the distance between home and place of work and to be added to wages, unless the employee's expenses according to R 38 Paragraph 3 are to be taken into account as business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the motor vehicle is used to drive home as part of a double household, the value according to sentence 1 increases by 0002 percent for every kilometer of the distance between the place of employment and the place of one's own household"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the domestic list price for each trip for which the deduction of income-related expenses according to Section 9 Paragraph 1 Clause 3 No. 5 Clause 3 and 4 EStG is excluded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The monthly values \u200b\u200baccording to sentences 1 and 2 are also to be applied if the motor vehicle is only available to the employee at times during the calendar month"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Reductions in values, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "because of a lettering of the vehicle, because of a private second vehicle or because the employee has to pay the fuel or garage costs are not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "List price within the meaning of sentences 1 to 3 is - even for second-hand purchased or leased vehicles - the manufacturer's recommended retail price rounded to the nearest hundred DM for the vehicle used at the time of its first registration, including surcharges for special equipment and sales tax; the value of a car phone is left out of consideration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a motor vehicle that is armored for safety reasons, the list price of the less powerful vehicle that would be made available to the employee if his safety were not at risk can be used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In deviation from number 1, the employer can apply the private value in use to the expenses for the motor vehicle that are attributable to the private journeys to be recorded in accordance with number 1 if the total expenses incurred for the motor vehicle are based on receipts and the ratio of private to other journeys a proper logbook can be proven"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The journeys made for business and private purposes must be documented separately and continuously in the logbook"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The following information is required for business trips: a) Date and mileage at the beginning and at the end of each individual external activity (business trip, change of assignment, driving activity), b) Travel destination and, in the event of detours, also the travel route, c) Purpose of the trip and business partners visited"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Kilometers are sufficient for private trips; A short note in the logbook is sufficient for journeys between home and work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The keeping of the logbook cannot be limited to a representative period, even if the usage conditions are not subject to major fluctuations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A tachograph can be used instead of the logbook if the same information can be obtained from it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The private use value is the proportion of the total costs of the vehicle that corresponds to the ratio of private trips to the total distance traveled"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The total costs are to be determined as the sum of the net expenses (including all accident costs) plus sales tax and deductions for wear and tear"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The deductions for wear and tear are based on the actual acquisition or production costs including sales tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer must, in consultation with the employee, determine the application of one of the procedures according to numbers 1 and 2 for each calendar year; the procedure may not be changed for the same vehicle during the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If it is not possible to precisely record the private value in use according to number 2 on a monthly basis, the monthly wage tax can be based on one twelfth of the previous year's amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "After the end of the calendar year or after the end of the employment relationship, the actual taxable value in use must be determined and any wage tax difference settled in accordance with \u00a7\u00a7 41c, 42b EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When assessing income tax, the employee is not bound by the procedure chosen for collecting wage tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee pays the employer a fee for the use of the motor vehicle, this reduces the value in use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter whether the usage fee is calculated as a flat rate or according to the actual use of the vehicle"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Contributions from the employee to the acquisition costs can also be offset against the private value in use in the payment year; in the cases of number 2, this only applies if the acquisition costs relevant for the depreciation calculation have not been reduced by the subsidies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Grant repayments are wages insofar as the grants have reduced the private use value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as the motor vehicle is used to travel between home and work, disabled employees within the meaning of Section 9 (2) EStG can pay their actual expenses including the value in use for these journeys and all other employees can pay the kilometer flat rate according to Section 9 (1) sentence 3 No. 4 EStG claim for the trips actually made as business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies if the amount applicable in accordance with Section 9 Paragraph 1 Clause 3 No. 4 EStG exceeds the taxed usage benefit for journeys between home and work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The deduction of income-related expenses does not apply if flat-rate taxation is carried out in accordance with Section 40 (2) sentence 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Provision of a motor vehicle with a driver (10) If a motor vehicle with a driver is made available, the following applies: If the employer provides the employee with a motor vehicle with a driver for journeys between home and work, the driver for these journeys according to Paragraph 7 No. 1 or 2 determined value in use of the motor vehicle by 50%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "to increase"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer provides the employee with a motor vehicle with a driver for other private journeys, the corresponding private use value of the motor vehicle must be increased as follows: a) by 50%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "if the driver is predominantly used, b) by 40 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "if the employee frequently drives the vehicle himself, c) by 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "if the employee largely controls the motor vehicle himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If, for safety reasons, a specially protected (armored) motor vehicle, which is not suitable for self-driving, is made available to an employee with a driver, the driver provision must not be recorded for tax purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant in which hazard level the employee is classified"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Interest savings (11) If the employer or, due to the employment relationship, a third party grants the employee interest-free or low-interest loans, the following principles must be followed for reasons of simplification, unless the interest advantages are to be assessed in accordance with Section 8 (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The interest benefits are to be taxed as benefits in kind if the sum of the loans that have not yet been repaid exceeds DM 5000 at the end of the wage payment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Interest advantages are to be assumed if the effective interest rate for a loan is 55 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "falls below; Several loans are to be assessed separately even if they are used to finance a property and have the same term"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 32 Purchase of goods and services (Section 8 (3) EStG) (1) The tax benefits of certain remuneration in kind for employees in accordance with Section 8 (3) EStG requires the following: The employee must receive the remuneration in kind on the basis of his employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee has several employment relationships one after the other or next to each other in the calendar year, the remuneration in kind from each employment relationship must be assessed independently of one another"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Section 8 (3) EStG does not apply to benefits in kind that the employee does not receive directly from the employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The remuneration in kind must consist of the provision of goods or services"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The goods include all economic goods that are treated like things (\u00a7 90 BGB) in commercial transactions, including electricity and heat"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "All other services that are usually provided for a fee are considered as services"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The preferential treatment applies to raw materials, ingredients and semi-finished products if these are predominantly used in the company's products"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Operating and auxiliary materials that are largely not given to third parties in terms of quantity are not favored"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For each individual payment in kind, for which the requirements of Section 8 (3) and Section 40 (1) or (2) No. 1 or 2 EStG apply at the same time, you can choose between flat-rate taxation and the application of Section 8 (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The benefit applies to both partially paid and free benefits in kind"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It therefore applies z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "for home drinks in the brewery industry, for free tobacco products in the tobacco industry and for deputies in mining as well as in agriculture and forestry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Subsequent credits are to be assessed as a reduction in pay if the conditions are already established at the time at which the employee receives the remuneration in kind"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Subsidies from a third party are not to be regarded as a reduction in price, but, if necessary, to be taxed as wage payments by third parties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The tax assessment of the remuneration in kind that meet the requirements of paragraph 1 shall be based on the final prices (including sales tax) at which the employer offers the goods or services to third-party end consumers in general business transactions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When granting insurance protection, it is the contributions that the employer, as the insurer, demands from third-party policyholders for this insurance protection"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a written price offer is missing, the first quotation from the provider is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer does not enter into business relationships with end consumers outside the employee's area, the final prices are to be taken as a basis, at which the customer closest to the place of delivery of the employer offers the goods or services to third-party end consumers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies in cases in which the employer only acts as a commission agent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 31 para 2 sentence 5 is to be applied accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the price determination, the calendar day on which the goods or services are delivered to the employee is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the order and delivery days are different, the conditions on the order day are decisive for determining the offer price"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The around 4 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the reduced final price is the monetary value of the benefit in kind; the difference between this monetary value and the remuneration paid by the employee is to be set as wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Wages of this kind from the same employment relationship remain tax-free as long as they do not exceed the total discount exempt amount of DM 2,400 per calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 33 Business expenses (1) Business expenses include all expenses caused by the job"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Business expenses that affect the lifestyle of the employee or other persons are not deductible in accordance with Section 9 (5) in conjunction with Section 4 (5) sentence 1 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This prohibition of deduction only applies to rare exceptional cases; the advertising costs must have considerable weight and exceed the limit of appropriateness considerably, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Expenses for the use of a private plane for a business trip"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) Expenses for food, clothing and housing as well as representation expenses are usually expenses for lifestyle within the meaning of Section 12 No. 1 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If these expenses are related to the employee's professional activity, it must be checked whether and to what extent the expenses are professional"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The following applies here: Are the expenses almost exclusively professional, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Aufwendungen f\u00fcr typische Berufskleidung (&gt;R 20), so sind sie in voller H\u00f6he als Werbungskosten abziehbar"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the expenses are only partly due to professional reasons and if this part of the expenses can be separated easily and properly from the expenses which wholly or partly serve the private life, then this part of the expenses is deductible as business expenses; it can be estimated if necessary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the expenses cannot be easily and clearly separated according to their professional cause (business expenses) and according to their private cause (expenses for lifestyle) according to objective characteristics, or if the private cause is not only of subordinate importance, then they belong to the total according to \u00a7 12 No. 1 EStG non-deductible expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In principle, expenses for food belong to the non-deductible expenses for lifestyle according to \u00a7 12 No. 1 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, the prohibition of deductions according to \u00a7 12 No. 1 EStG does not apply to additional meal expenses, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "als Reisekosten (&gt;R 39) oder wegen einer aus beruflichem Anla\u00df begr\u00fcndeten doppelten Haushaltsf\u00fchrung (&gt;R 43) so gut wie ausschlie\u00dflich durch die berufliche T\u00e4tigkeit veranla\u00dft sind"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) The acceptance of business expenses does not require that wages accrue in the same calendar year in which the expenses are paid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) Savings for work-related expenses, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Contributions to a clothing fund for the purchase of typical work clothing are not yet advertising costs; Amounts saved can only be deducted when they have been spent as income-related expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If an employee has saved work-related expenses by receiving corresponding benefits in kind, the value of the benefits in kind is equal to the corresponding expenses; The remuneration in kind is subject to the deduction restrictions according to \u00a7 9 Paragraph 1 Clause 3 No. 4 5 7 and Paragraph 5 EStG deductible at the value as income-related expenses with which it was recorded as taxable wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Tax-free payments exclude corresponding income-related expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 34 Expenses for basic and advanced training The acquisition of knowledge that is necessary as a basis for professional practice takes place in the area of \u200b\u200btraining"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Hierdurch entstehende Aufwendungen geh\u00f6ren grunds\u00e4tzlich als Ausbildungskosten zu den Aufwendungen f\u00fcr die Lebensf\u00fchrung und sind nur als Sonderausgaben im Rahmen des \u00a7 10 Abs 1 Nr 7 EStG steuerlich abziehbar (&gt;R 103 EStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In contrast to the training costs, which can be deducted as special expenses, further training costs, i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Expenses that an employee makes in order to maintain or expand their knowledge and skills in the current job or to adapt them to changing requirements represent business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a training is split up by partial qualifications, this does not lead to further training costs being incurred in some cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The expenses incurred through participation in a training event can, if necessary, be taken into account as income-related expenses in analogous application of R 37 to 43"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 35 Study trips, specialist congresses - unoccupied - R 36 Expenses in connection with professional associations (1) Expenses at events of the profession, the professional association, the professional association or the union of an employee that serve to promote the general knowledge of the participants are not advertising costs, but expenses for lifestyle"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In particular, non-deductible expenses for the conduct of life are always those expenses that the employee has made on the occasion of social events of the specified organization, even if the social events are in connection with a purely technical or professional conference or meeting stood"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) Certain events organized by professions and professional associations serve the purpose of training participants in the profession, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Lectures at administrative academies or adult education centers, advanced training courses, specialist courses, specialist lectures"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Expenses incurred by the participant at such events can be advertising expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 37 Reisekosten Reisekostenbegriff (1)Reisekosten sind Fahrtkosten (&gt;R 38), Verpflegungsmehraufwendungen (&gt;R 39), \u00dcbernachtungskosten (&gt;R 40) und Reisenebenkosten (&gt;R 40a), wenn diese so gut wie ausschlie\u00dflich durch die berufliche T\u00e4tigkeit des Arbeitnehmers au\u00dferhalb seiner Wohnung und einer ortsgebundenen regelm\u00e4\u00dfigen Arbeitsst\u00e4tte (Absatz 2) veranla\u00dft sind"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The professional activity of an employee is equivalent to an interview by a job applicant, even if he does not have a regular place of work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee deals with private matters in connection with his professional activity to a more than insignificant extent, then the professionally induced expenses are to be separated from the privately induced expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If this is not easily and flawlessly possible - not even through an estimate - then the total expenses belong to the non-deductible expenses for lifestyle according to \u00a7 12 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Expenses that are not almost exclusively caused by the professional activity, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Clothing costs and expenses for the purchase of suitcases and other travel equipment are not travel expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the tax consideration of travel expenses, a distinction must be made between: Business trip (Paragraph 3) Driving activity (Paragraph 4) Change of assignment (Paragraph 5) The reason and type of professional activity, the duration of the journey and the travel route must be recorded by the employee and based on suitable documents, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Fahrtenbuch (&gt;R 31 Abs 9 Nr 2 Satz 3), Tankquittungen, Hotelrechnungen, Schriftverkehr, nachzuweisen oder glaubhaft zu machen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Regular place of work (2) A regular place of work is the location-specific center of the employee's permanent professional activity, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Company or branch"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee must perform at least part of the total work assigned to him at this center"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of an employee who works outside the company, the company can be recognized as a regular place of work without further investigation if he regularly works at least 20% per week"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "his contractual working hours or an average of one working day per working week in the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Business trip (3) A business trip is a change of location including the outward and return journey on the occasion of a temporary external activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An external activity exists when the employee works outside his home and his regular place of work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of longer-term, temporary external work at the same place of work, a business trip is only recognized for the first three months; after the three-month period has expired, the external place of work is to be regarded as a new regular place of work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the following applies: An interruption of external work due to vacation or illness at the same place of work has no influence on the expiry of the three-month period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Other interruptions, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Temporary work at the regular workplace only leads to a new start of the three-month period if the interruption lasted at least four weeks"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of external workplaces that constantly change locally due to the nature of the work, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the three-month period does not apply to the construction of a motorway or the installation of high-voltage lines"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It also does not apply to employees who carry out external activities over a longer period of time at work sites within a municipality or its surroundings that change several times a day, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Travel agent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the consideration of travel costs, journeys between several regular workplaces in the same employment relationship or within a spacious work area from one place of work to the next also count as business trips"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Driving activity (4) A driving activity is given to employees who carry out their activity on a vehicle, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Professional drivers, co-drivers, garbage truck drivers, concrete and gravel drivers, train drivers and train attendants"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee temporarily performs an atypical activity (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Participation in a training event), the vehicle is considered a regular place of work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Police officers on patrol duty, customs officers in the border inspection service, drivers in the delivery service, sales drivers, customer service technicians and driving instructors as well as inland waterwaymen and seafarers who have accommodation on the ship are not regularly driving"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Change of assignment (5) Employment change occurs in the case of employees who, in their individual professional activity, are typically only assigned to constantly changing places of work; this also applies to temporary workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Paragraph 4 sentence 2 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The number of places of work reached during a calendar year is irrelevant for the recognition of a change of assignment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 38 Travel expenses as travel expenses General (1) Travel expenses are the actual expenses incurred by the employee through personal use of a means of transport"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of public transport, the fare paid including any surcharges must be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee uses his vehicle, the partial amount of the annual total costs of this vehicle is to be applied, which corresponds to the proportion of the journeys to be taken into account in the annual mileage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "On the basis of the total costs determined for a period of twelve months, the employee can calculate a kilometer rate for the vehicle provided by him, which may be applied until the circumstances change significantly, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "until the end of the depreciation period or until the occurrence of changed leasing charges"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 44 sentence 3 is to be applied mutatis mutandis for the application of the deductions for wear and tear"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Notwithstanding sentence 3, the travel costs can also be set at flat-rate kilometer rates, which the Federal Ministry of Finance sets in agreement with the highest tax authorities of the federal states according to the highest mileage and transport allowance under the Federal Travel Expenses Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Driving activity (2) In the case of driving activity, the expenses for journeys between home and company, location, vehicle depot or place of use are either, if the place of use does not change constantly, as expenditure for journeys between home and work place according to R 42, or if the place of use changes constantly , to be taken into account as expenses for journeys in the event of a change of assignment according to paragraph 3"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Change of assignment activity (3) In the case of an assignment change activity, travel costs can only be recognized as travel expenses if the distance between home and assignment location is more than 30 km"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If several deployment sites are visited on one working day, the total travel costs can be taken into account as travel expenses if at least one of the deployment sites is more than 30 km away from the home"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee has several apartments, the distance requirement must be met for all apartments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When using public transport, the distance to be traveled, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the tariff distance, in other cases the shortest usable road connection is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When using your own motor vehicle, another, obviously more traffic-friendly road connection can also be used as a basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a large work area, the point at which the work area is left is decisive for the distance calculation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Reimbursement by the employer (4) The employee must present his employer with documents from which the prerequisites for the tax exemption of the reimbursement and, insofar as the travel costs when using a private vehicle are not reimbursed with the flat rate per kilometer according to paragraph 1 sentence 6, also the actual ones The total cost of the vehicle must be apparent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer must keep these documents as receipts for the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Erstattet der Arbeitgeber die &gt; pauschalen Kilometers\u00e4tze, hat er nicht zu pr\u00fcfen, ob dies zu einer unzutreffenden Besteuerung f\u00fchrt"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 39 Additional meal expenses as travel expenses General (1) Under the prerequisites of Section 4 (5) sentence 1 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The individual proof of additional meal expenses does not entitle to deduct higher amounts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Die Pauschbetr\u00e4ge sind auch dann anzuwenden, wenn der Arbeitnehmer Mahlzeiten vom Arbeitgeber oder auf dessen Veranlassung von einem Dritten unentgeltlich oder teilentgeltlich erhalten hat (&gt;R 31 Abs 8); beh\u00e4lt der Arbeitgeber in diesen F\u00e4llen f\u00fcr die Mahlzeiten Betr\u00e4ge ein, die \u00fcber den amtlichen Sachbezugswerten liegen, so ist der Differenzbetrag nicht als Werbungskosten abziehbar"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If an employee works away from home several times on one day, the periods of absence within the meaning of Section 4 Paragraph 5 Sentence 1 No. 5 EStG must be added together"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The three-month period of Section 4 (5) sentence 1 no.5 sentence 5 EStG does not apply to driving or changing assignments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Konkurrenzregelung (2)Soweit f\u00fcr denselben Kalendertag Verpflegungsmehraufwendungen wegen einer Dienstreise, Fahrt\u00e4tigkeit oder Einsatzwechselt\u00e4tigkeit oder wegen einer doppelten Haushaltsf\u00fchrung (&gt;R 43 Abs 8) anzuerkennen sind, ist jeweils der h\u00f6chste Pauschbetrag anzusetzen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Special features of foreign activities (3) For the assessment of additional meal expenses for business trips abroad, assignment change activities or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Driving abroad, different lump sums apply in different countries (daily allowances), which are announced by the Federal Ministry of Finance in agreement with the highest tax authorities of the federal states on the basis of the highest daily allowances according to the Federal Travel Expenses Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the countries not included in the notice, the lump sum applicable for Luxembourg is decisive; for the overseas and external areas of a country not included in the notice, the flat rate applicable for the mother country is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If an international and a domestic business trip are carried out on a calendar day, the corresponding international daily allowance is decisive for this day, even if the majority of the time is spent in Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the following should be noted when applying the international per diem: In the case of air travel, a country is considered to have been reached at the time the aircraft lands there; Stopovers are not taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a flight extends over more than two calendar days, the daily allowance applicable for Austria is decisive for the days between the day of departure and the day of landing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of boat trips, the daily allowance applicable for Luxembourg and the daily allowance applicable for the port location for the days of embarkation and disembarkation are decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 40 Accommodation costs General (1) Accommodation costs are the actual expenses incurred by the employee for the personal use of accommodation for overnight stays"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee uses a shared room with people who are not employed by his employer, the expenses that would have been incurred if a single room had been used in the same house are decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the other person also goes on a business trip, the actual accommodation costs are to be divided equally"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If payment receipts only show a total price for accommodation and breakfast and the price for breakfast cannot be determined, the total price must be reduced as follows to determine the accommodation costs: for an overnight stay in Germany by 9 DM, for an overnight stay abroad by DM 20 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the lump sum applicable to the place of accommodation for additional meal expenses for a business trip with an absence of at least 24 hours"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Deduction of income-related expenses (2) In the case of a business trip and driving activity, accommodation costs can be set as travel expenses and deducted as income-related expenses, unless they have been reimbursed tax-free by the employer in accordance with Paragraph 3 or Section 3 No. 13 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of overnight stays abroad, the accommodation costs may be set at lump sums (accommodation allowances) without individual proof of the actual expenses; Paragraph 3 sentence 2 applies"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The lump sums are announced by the Federal Ministry of Finance in agreement with the highest tax authorities of the federal states on the basis of the highest foreign accommodation allowances according to the Federal Travel Expenses Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "They are based on the location that is relevant according to R 39 Paragraph 3 Clause 4 Numbers 1 and 2"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the countries and areas not included in the notice, R 39 Paragraph 3 Clause 2 shall apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "No overnight accommodation allowance may be charged for the duration of the use of means of transport"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Reimbursement by the employer (3) For each overnight stay in Germany, the employer may pay a lump sum of 39 DM tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply if the employee has received accommodation from the employer or, due to his employment relationship, from a third party free of charge or partially"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When using a sleeping car or a ship's cabin, the lump sum may only be paid tax-free if the overnight stay in another accommodation has started or ended"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax-free payment of the lump sum for an overnight stay in the vehicle is not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A change between the reimbursement of the actual accommodation costs and the lump sum reimbursement is not permitted during a business trip or driving activity lasting several days"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 40a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Additional travel costs General (1) Additional travel costs are, under the conditions of R 37 Paragraph 1, the actual expenses z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "for the transport and storage of luggage, long-distance calls and correspondence of professional content with the employer or his business partner, road use and parking space as well as compensation payments as a result of traffic accidents, if the associated travel costs according to R 38 are to be recognized as travel expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Deduction of income-related expenses (2) The incidental travel expenses can be deducted in their actual amount as income-related expenses, unless they are reimbursed tax-free by the employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Tax exemption for employer reimbursements (3) The reimbursement of incidental travel expenses by the employer is tax-free according to Section 3 No. 16 EStG, provided that it does not exceed the actual expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee must submit documents to his employer from which the actual expenses must be evident"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer must keep these documents as receipts for the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 41 Relocation costs General (1) Costs that an employee incurs as a result of a job-related change of residence are advertising expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Amount of moving costs (2) In the event of a job-related change of residence, the actual moving costs can generally be deducted as income-related expenses up to the amount that could be paid at most as compensation for moving costs according to the Federal Moving Costs Act (BUKG) and the Foreign Moving Costs Ordinance (AUV) in the currently applicable version ; The lump sums for additional meal expenses in accordance with Section 4 Paragraph 5 Clause 1 No. 5 EStG must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the limits stipulated by moving costs are adhered to, it is not necessary to check whether the moving costs represent advertising costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If higher moving costs are proven in detail, it must be checked whether and to what extent the expenses are business expenses or non-deductible costs of living, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "for expenses for the purchase of new furnishings"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Instead of the flat-rate moving costs set out in \u00a7 10 BUKG, the higher moving costs documented in individual cases can also be deducted as business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "No business expenses are deducted if the relocation costs have been reimbursed tax-free by the employer (\u00a7 3c EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Reimbursement by the employer (3) The reimbursement of relocation costs by the employer is tax-free according to Section 3 No. 16 EStG, provided that no higher amounts are reimbursed than would be deductible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee must submit documents to his employer from which the actual expenses must be evident"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer must keep these documents as receipts for the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 42 Expenses for journeys between home and work place Relevant home (1) Any home of the employee that he regularly uses for overnight stays and from which he visits his work place comes into consideration as the starting point for the journeys"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "As an apartment is z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "also look at a furnished room, a ship's cabin, a summer house, a caravan parked for a certain period of time or a place to sleep in a mass accommodation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If an employee has several apartments, trips to and from the apartment further away from the place of work can only be taken into account in accordance with Section 9 Paragraph 1 Clause 3 No. 4 Clause 3 EStG if the focus of the employee's life interests is there and they are not is only visited occasionally"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a married employee, the center of vital interests is usually at the actual place of residence of his family"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The apartment can only be considered if the employee visits it at least six times in a calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For other employees, the center of vital interests is in the place of residence with which the closer personal relationships exist"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The personal relationships can be expressed particularly in bonds with people, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Parents, fianc\u00e9s, friends and acquaintances can be found, but also in club membership and other activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee visits this apartment on average at least twice a month, it can be assumed that the center of his vital interests is located there"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Sentences 4 to 8 also apply to journeys home in the case of work-related double housekeeping, which can be recognized as journeys between home and work after the two-year period, regardless of whether the center of life is in Germany or abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Fahrten mit einem zur Nutzung \u00fcberlassenen Kraftfahrzeug (2)Ein Kraftfahrzeug ist dem Arbeitnehmer zur Nutzung \u00fcberlassen, wenn es dem Arbeitnehmer vom Arbeitgeber unentgeltlich oder teilentgeltlich \u00fcberlassen worden (&gt;R 31 Abs 9) ist oder wenn es der Arbeitnehmer von dritter Seite geliehen, gemietet oder geleast hat"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Fahrten mit \u00f6ffentlichen Verkehrsmitteln (3)Bei Fahrten zwischen Wohnung und Arbeitsst\u00e4tte mit \u00f6ffentlichen Verkehrsmitteln k\u00f6nnen die tats\u00e4chlichen Aufwendungen, gek\u00fcrzt um steuerfreie Ersatzleistungen des Arbeitgebers nach \u00a7 3 Nr 34 EStG (&gt;R 21 b), als Werbungskosten angesetzt werden"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to monthly or annual tickets - including so-called job tickets - for which possible private shared use is regularly of minor importance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is not detrimental for the deduction of advertising expenses that a monthly or annual ticket is also valid for other routes or for secondary uses, if this does not increase the expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If an employee who has received or acquired a job ticket from the employer proves or makes credible that he also drove to work with his own motor vehicle, the lump-sum kilometer amount according to Section 9 Paragraph 1 Clause 3 No. 4 EStG is also applicable to be considered as income-related expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Trips with other vehicles (4) Without individual proof of the actual expenses, the travel costs when using a moped or moped can be set at 028 DM and when using a bicycle at 014 DM per kilometer of the distance between home and work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Carpool with spouse (5) The inclusion of a detour is possible when carpooling with the spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The travel costs for the working days on which the spouses drove together can only be taken into account in total for one spouse or, if the spouses jointly choose, for each spouse separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The following applies to separate consideration: If half of the number of kilometers actually traveled by motor vehicle for journeys between the home and the place of work each working day is less than the sum of the distances to be calculated separately for each spouse, the lower number of kilometers is in the ratio of the for the spouses to divide the relevant distances and to this extent apply to the individual spouses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Multiple employment relationships (6) In the case of employees who have multiple employment relationships and who therefore incur expenses for professional trips to several spatially separated workplaces, journeys between home and workplace with their own motor vehicle can be permitted within the framework of Section 9 Paragraph 1 Clause 3 No. 4 and Paragraph 2 EStG are taken into account as follows: If the employee returns to the apartment in the meantime, each trip must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If two workplaces are visited immediately one after the other - without returning to the home in the meantime - the trip to the first place of work is to be considered as a detour to the trip to the second place of work; in this case, however, a maximum of half of the total distance can be taken into account when applying the kilometer flat rates"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Disabled persons within the meaning of Section 9 (2) EStG (7) Without individual proof of the actual expenses, travel costs can be set according to the regulations in R 38 Paragraph 1 Clause 6 and R 40 a Paragraph 1 No. 3"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a disabled employee is in his own vehicle or a vehicle made available to him for use by a third party, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the spouse is driven to his place of work and picked up again, the vehicle costs incurred as a result of the driver's departure and arrival - the so-called empty journeys - can be deducted as income-related expenses in the actual amount or in analogous application of R 38 (1)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the proof of the requirements of \u00a7 9 Abs 2 EStG \u00a7 65 EStDV is to be applied accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the recognition of the actual expenses or the kilometer rates from R 38 Paragraph 1 and for the consideration of empty trips, R 194 EStR is to be applied accordingly if the degree of disability is retrospectively determined or changed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 43 Additional expenses in the case of double housekeeping Double housekeeping (1) Double housekeeping exists if the employee spends the night at the place of employment while working outside the company; the number of overnight stays is irrelevant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "There is no double housekeeping as long as the external employment is recognized as a business trip according to R 37, Paragraph 3"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Professional cause (2) Moving to a second home is usually due to a change of place of employment due to a transfer, change or the first establishment of an employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If working spouses on both sides move into a joint second home at the same place of employment, there is also a professional reason"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Even taking the non-working spouse with you to the place of employment does not conflict with the professional induction of double housekeeping"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When moving from abroad, the move to a second home can also be a job if the employee applies for or receives political asylum"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Own household (3) Own household requires that the employee has an apartment that is furnished and appropriate to the living needs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee has to maintain a household in this apartment, that is, he has to determine or have a significant say in household management"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is not necessary that domestic life prevails in the apartment at the place of one's own household, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "if the employee takes his non-working spouse with him to the external place of employment or the employee is not married"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Die Wohnung mu\u00df au\u00dferdem der Mittelpunkt der Lebensinteressen des Arbeitnehmers sein (&gt;R 42 Abs 1 Satz 4 bis 8)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the distance between this home and the second home is greater, especially if the home is abroad, one trip home in the calendar year is sufficient to recognize this as the center of life if the home is home to household chores even when the employee is absent significantly involved through personal involvement as well as financially"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For employees with an apartment in distant countries, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Australia, India, Japan, Korea, the Philippines, sentence 5 applies with the proviso that at least one trip home is made within the two-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Location of the second home (4) A second home close to the place of employment is equivalent to a second home at the place of employment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Doppelte Haushaltsf\u00fchrung bei Arbeitnehmern ohne eigenen Hausstand (5)Bei Arbeitnehmern ohne eigenen Hausstand gilt ein Wohnungswechsel an den Besch\u00e4ftigungsort oder in dessen N\u00e4he, wenn er den Mittelpunkt seiner Lebensinteressen (&gt;R 42 Abs 1 Satz 6 bis 8) in seiner Wohnung am bisherigen Wohnort beibeh\u00e4lt, f\u00fcr folgende Zeitr\u00e4ume als doppelte Haushaltsf\u00fchrung: f\u00fcr eine \u00dcbergangszeit von drei Monaten nach Bezug der Wohnung am neuen Besch\u00e4ftigungsort, f\u00fcr die Folgezeit nur, wenn a)der Arbeitnehmer f\u00fcr eine verh\u00e4ltnism\u00e4\u00dfig kurze Dauer am selben Ort besch\u00e4ftigt wird oder b)der Arbeitnehmer l\u00e4ngerfristig oder auf Dauer an einem Ort besch\u00e4ftigt wird und umzugsbereit ist, aber noch keine angemessene Wohnung gefunden hat"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the expiry of the three-month period according to number 1, the regulations in R 37 Paragraph 3 apply with the proviso that the new start of the three-month period also requires the second home to be changed to the new place of employment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Notwendige Mehraufwendungen (6)Als notwendige Mehraufwendungen wegen einer doppelten Haushaltsf\u00fchrung kommen in Betracht: die Fahrtkosten aus Anla\u00df der Wohnungswechsel zu Beginn und am Ende der doppelten Haushaltsf\u00fchrung sowie f\u00fcr w\u00f6chentliche Heimfahrten an den Ort des eigenen Hausstands oder in den F\u00e4llen des Absatzes 5 an den bisherigen Wohnort (&gt; Absatz 7) oder Aufwendungen f\u00fcr w\u00f6chentliche Familien-Ferngespr\u00e4che, Verpflegungsmehraufwendungen (&gt; Absatz 8), Aufwendungen f\u00fcr die Zweitwohnung (&gt; Absatz 9) und Umzugskosten (&gt; Absatz 10)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee makes more than one trip home a week, he can choose whether he wants to claim the additional expenses in accordance with sentence 1 due to double housekeeping or the travel expenses as expenses for trips between home and work place according to R 42"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee can only exercise the right to vote once for the same double housekeeping for each calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer has made the second home available free of charge or partially, the deductible travel costs are to be reduced by this benefit in kind with the value according to R 31 Paragraph 5 and 6"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Necessary travel expenses (7) Necessary travel expenses are to be recognized as the actual expenses incurred for travel when moving house at the beginning and at the end of double housekeeping"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 38 Paragraph 1 is to be used to determine travel costs; In addition, any ancillary costs can be taken into account in accordance with R 40 a, the expenses for an actual trip home each week"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of expenses by the employee for journeys with his own vehicle or one made available to him outside of his employment relationship, R 42 Paragraph 2 5 to 7 shall apply mutatis mutandis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Aufwendungen f\u00fcr Fahrten mit einem im Rahmen des Dienstverh\u00e4ltnisses zur Nutzung \u00fcberlassenen Kraftfahrzeug k\u00f6nnen nicht angesetzt werden (&gt; Absatz 11 Satz 15 Nr 1)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Nach Ablauf der Zweijahresfrist sind die letzte Fahrt zur Beendigung der doppelten Haushaltsf\u00fchrung und die Fahrten vom Besch\u00e4ftigungsort zum Ort des eigenen Hausstands und zur\u00fcck (Familienheimfahrten) als Fahrten zwischen Wohnung und Arbeitsst\u00e4tte nach \u00a7 9 Abs 1 Satz 3 Nr 4 EStG zu behandeln (&gt;R 42 Abs 1 Satz 4 bis 8)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Necessary additional meal expenses (8) For a period of three months after moving into the apartment at the new place of employment for each calendar day on which the employee is absent from his apartment at the center of his life within the meaning of paragraphs 3 or 5, the lump sums applicable to business trips are considered to be necessary additional meal expenses to recognize; The only decisive factor here is the duration of the absence from the apartment at the center of one's life"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the activity at the place of employment was immediately preceded by a business trip to this place of employment, its duration is to be counted towards the three-month period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the expiry of the three-month period, paragraph 5 sentence 2 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 39 paragraph 2 must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Necessary expenses for the second home (9) The actual costs are to be recognized as necessary expenses for the second home"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The necessary expenses for the second home also include the second home tax to be paid for this home"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the second home is owned by the employee, the expenses are to be regarded as necessary in the amount that the employee would have to bear as a tenant for an apartment that is appropriate in terms of size, equipment and location"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the place of employment is abroad, the necessary expenses for the second home abroad can be increased without individual evidence for the transition period within the meaning of paragraph 8 with the lump sum according to R 40 paragraph 2 and for the subsequent period with 40%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "this lump sum per overnight stay; A change between the individual statement of the expenses and the application of the lump sums is not permitted in the same double household within a calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Moving costs (10) Proof of moving costs within the meaning of \u00a7 10 BUKG is necessary for a move on the occasion of the establishment, termination or change of a double housekeeping, because the flat rate does not apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to the other relocation expenses within the meaning of \u00a7 10 AUV in the event of the end of double housekeeping due to the return of an employee abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Costs for moving to the family home (moving back) are not deductible after the two-year period (Section 9 (1), sentence 3, no. 5 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Deduction of business expenses or remuneration by the employer (11) The necessary additional expenses according to paragraphs 6 to 10 can be deducted as business expenses, unless they are reimbursed tax-free by the employer according to the following regulations; R 39 para 2 is to be applied accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the additional expenses according to paragraphs 7 9 and 10, the deduction of income-related expenses according to \u00a7 9 paragraph 1 sentence 3 number 5 sentence 3 EStG is limited to the first two years of employment in the same location"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The two-year period begins when the employee has changed his place of employment or has taken up employment for the first time and has moved into a second home in the vicinity of the new place of employment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee drove there every working day before moving into the second home at the external place of employment, this period does not count towards the two-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the activity at the external place of employment was immediately preceded by a business trip to this place, the duration of the business trip is also not counted towards the two-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If both working spouses move their family residence to the place of residence of the spouse who has previously worked abroad and the other spouse keeps the previous family home as a second home for professional reasons, no new two-year period begins for this second home; For this double household, the other spouse can deduct income-related expenses for the remaining period of the two-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Aufwendungen f\u00fcr Heimfahrten k\u00f6nnen jedoch nach Ablauf der Zweijahresfrist nach \u00a7 9 Abs 1 Satz 3 Nr 4 EStG (&gt;R 42) als Werbungskosten abgezogen werden"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An interruption of employment at the same location due to vacation or illness has no influence on the expiry of the two-year period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, interruptions due to termination of employment or temporary work at another place of employment lead to a new start of the two-year period if the interruption lasted at least eight months"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The reimbursement of additional expenses in the case of double housekeeping by the employer is tax-free according to \u00a7 3 No. 13 or 16 EStG, provided that no higher amounts are reimbursed than can be deducted as income-related expenses according to sentences 1 and 2"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer can assume that employees in tax classes III, IV or V have their own household"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of other employees, the employer may only recognize their own household if they declare in writing that they have their own household in addition to a second home at the place of employment outside of the place of employment and confirm the accuracy of this declaration by signature"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This declaration must be kept as a receipt for the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer does not have to observe the employee's right to choose under paragraph 6"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the following applies: If the employer or a third party on behalf of the employee has provided the employee with a vehicle free of charge to carry out the journeys home, a deduction for business expenses and reimbursement of travel expenses are not possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Additional meal expenses may only be reimbursed tax-free up to the lump sum according to paragraph 8"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The necessary expenses for the second home at a place of employment in Germany may be reimbursed tax-free for a period of three months with a lump sum of up to DM 39 and for the subsequent period of up to 21 months with a lump sum of up to DM 8 per overnight stay, if The second home was not made available to the employee free of charge or partially"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a second home abroad, the necessary expenses can be paid for a period of three months with the foreign overnight flat rate applicable for a business trip and for the subsequent period of up to 21 months with 40%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "this lump sum can be reimbursed tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 44 Work equipment The acquisition or production costs of work equipment including sales tax can be deducted in full as income-related expenses in the year of acquisition or manufacture if they do not exceed the sales tax for the individual work equipment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Acquisition or production costs of more than DM 800 are to be distributed over the calendar years of the total expected useful life of the work equipment and to be taken into account proportionately as income-related expenses in each of these years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, the full annual amount can be deducted in the year of acquisition or manufacture for work equipment acquired or manufactured in the first half of the year and half the annual amount for work equipment acquired or manufactured in the second half of the year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If an asset that is used as work equipment is sold, any sales proceeds that may result are not to be included in the income from employment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 45 Home office - unoccupied - R 46 Advertising expenses for homeworkers (1) For homeworkers within the meaning of the Home Work Act, expenses that are directly caused by home work, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Rent and expenses for heating and lighting the work rooms, expenses for work equipment and ingredients as well as for the transport of the material and the finished goods are recognized as income-related expenses insofar as they exceed the home worker surcharges according to paragraph 2"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) Wage surcharges that are paid to homeworkers to compensate for the expenses associated with home work in addition to the basic wage are overall tax-free for reasons of simplification according to \u00a7 3 No. 30 and 50 EStG, insofar as they are 10 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "do not exceed the basic wage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The highest financial authority of a country can, with the consent of the Federal Ministry of Finance, adjust the percentage for certain groups of homeworkers to the actual circumstances"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 47 - unoccupied - R 48 lump sums for income-related expenses - unoccupied - R 49 special expenses - unoccupied - R 50 - R 59 - unoccupied - R 60 reduction of the advance deduction - unoccupied - R 61 deduction of expenses for tax-privileged purposes - unoccupied - R 62 - R 63 - Unoccupied - R 64 Calculation of the flat rate pension for spouses - Unoccupied - R 65 Inflow of income and outflow of expenses - Unoccupied - R 66 Employer In addition to the cases mentioned in Section 1 (2) LStDV, a natural or legal person also comes as an employer an association of persons or assets into consideration if the labor is owed to it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The successor companies of the Deutsche Bundespost are employers of those who work for them"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An employer is also someone who pays wages from previous or future employment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In principle, an employer is also someone who leaves an employee (temporary worker) to a third party (hirer) for work (lender)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Zahlt im Fall unerlaubter Arbeitnehmer\u00fcberlassung der Entleiher anstelle des Verleihers den Arbeitslohn an den Arbeitnehmer, so ist der Entleiher regelm\u00e4\u00dfig nicht Dritter, sondern Arbeitgeber im Sinne von \u00a7 38 Abs 1 Satz 1 Nr 1 EStG (&gt;R 146 Abs 1)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Im \u00fcbrigen kommt es nicht darauf an, ob derjenige, dem die Arbeitskraft geschuldet wird, oder ein Dritter Arbeitslohn zahlt (&gt;R 106)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 67 Employee - unoccupied - R 68 Secondary job and temporary job In the case of part-time teaching at a school or a course with a generally fixed curriculum that is not only set up on a case-by-case basis, the part-time teaching staff are usually employees, unless they are not firmly integrated in the school or course operation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the teaching activity is only small, this can be an indication that there is no permanent integration into the school or training course"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A small amount in this sense can always be assumed if the part-time teacher at the individual school or the individual course does not give an average of more than six lessons per week"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 69 Employment relationships of spouses - unoccupied - R 70 Wages (1) Wages are the consideration for providing the individual labor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wages therefore also include wage supplements for overtime and hardship supplements, such as heat supplements, water surcharges, danger surcharges, dirt allowances, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": ", Compensation paid for vacation not granted, the induction allowance paid on the basis of Section 7 (1) of the Soldiers' Supply Act, lump-sum compensation payments that are paid to employees in the cash and counting service, provided that they exceed DM 30 per month"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) Not as consideration for the provision of the individual labor and thus not as wages are u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "consider the value of the work equipment made available free of charge for professional use, which the employer based on legal obligation according to \u00a7 3 Abs 2 Nr 1 and Abs 3 ArbSchG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7 6 Abs 1 BildscharbV \u00fcbernommenen angemessenen Kosten f\u00fcr eine spezielle Sehhilfe, wenn auf Grund einer Untersuchung der Augen und des Sehverm\u00f6gens durch eine fachkundige Person im Sinne des \u00a7 6 Abs 1 BildscharbV die spezielle Sehhilfe notwendig ist, um eine ausreichende Sehf\u00e4higkeit in den Entfernungsbereichen des Bildschirmarbeitsplatzes zu gew\u00e4hrleisten, \u00fcbliche Sachleistungen des Arbeitgebers aus Anla\u00df der Diensteinf\u00fchrung, eines Amts- oder Funktionswechsels, eines runden Arbeitnehmerjubil\u00e4ums (&gt;R 72 Abs 2 Nr 3) oder der Verabschiedung eines Arbeitnehmers; betragen die Aufwendungen des Arbeitgebers einschlie\u00dflich Umsatzsteuer mehr als 200 DM je teilnehmender Person, so sind die Aufwendungen dem Arbeitslohn des Arbeitnehmers hinzuzurechnen; auch Geschenke bis zu einem Gesamtwert von 60 DM sind in die 200-DM-Grenze einzubeziehen, pauschale Zahlungen des Arbeitgebers an ein Dienstleistungsunternehmen, das sich verpflichtet, alle Arbeitnehmer des Auftraggebers kostenlos in pers\u00f6nlichen und sozialen Angelegenheiten zu beraten und zu betreuen, beispielsweise durch die \u00dcbernahme der Vermittlung von Betreuungspersonen f\u00fcr Familienangeh\u00f6rige"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) Services provided by the employer, with which he reimburses the employee's business expenses, are only tax-free insofar as this is legally stipulated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Somit sind auch steuerpflichtig Verg\u00fctungen des Arbeitgebers zum Ersatz der dem Arbeitnehmer berechneten Kontof\u00fchrungsgeb\u00fchren, Verg\u00fctungen des Arbeitgebers zum Ersatz der Aufwendungen des Arbeitnehmers f\u00fcr Fahrten zwischen Wohnung und Arbeitsst\u00e4tte, soweit die Aufwendungen nicht zu den Reisekosten (&gt;R 38) geh\u00f6ren oder nicht nach \u00a7 3 Nr 34 EStG (&gt;R 21b) steuerfrei sind"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 71 Agency commissions (1) If employees receive agency commissions from their employers, these are in principle wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to commissions that a third party pays to the employer and which the employer passes on to the employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) Commission payments by a building society or an insurance company to employees of the credit institutions for the conclusion of contracts that are brokered during working hours are to be subject to wage tax deduction as third party wage payments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee's area of \u200b\u200bresponsibility includes direct contact with the customer of the credit institution, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a customer or investment advisor, this also applies to the commissions for the conclusion of contracts outside of working hours"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 72 Benefits at company events General (1) Benefits made by the employer to employees at company events are not part of wages in the overwhelming operational interest of the employer if they are conventional (normal) company events and benefits that are usual at these events"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Concept of company event (2) Company events are events at the company level that have a social character and in which all company employees can participate, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Company outings, Christmas parties, anniversary celebrations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the event is carried out by the employer, works council or staff council"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Events that are only of interest to a limited group of employees are company events if the limitation of the group of participants does not represent a preference for certain groups of employees"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "As company events, such events are therefore also to be recognized that z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "only for one organizational unit of the company, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Department, if all employees of this organizational unit take part in the event can only be held for all retired former employees of the company (retirees' meeting), only for those employees who already have a round (10-, 20- , 25, 30, 40, 50, 60 years) have celebrated an employee anniversary or in connection with the company event (anniversary celebrations)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is harmless if, in addition to the anniversaries, a limited group of other employees, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the close employees of the anniversary is invited"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Die Ehrung eines einzelnen Jubilars oder eines einzelnen Arbeitnehmers bei dessen Ausscheiden aus dem Betrieb, auch unter Beteiligung weiterer Arbeitnehmer, ist keine Betriebsveranstaltung; zu Sachzuwendungen aus solchen Anl\u00e4ssen &gt;R 70 Abs 2 Nr 3 Auch ein sogenanntes Arbeitsessen ist keine Betriebsveranstaltung (&gt;R 73 Abs 2)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Conventionality (customary) of the company event (3) Features that distinguish the conventional (customary) are frequency, duration or special design of the company event"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In terms of duration and frequency, a company event is usual if it is a one-day event without an overnight stay and if no more than two events are held annually"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to events within the meaning of Paragraph 2 No. 2 and 3 which are to be assessed separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If there are more than two events of the same type, the employer can select the two events that are carried out as normal company events"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is harmless if an employee takes part in more than two different events, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "a jubilee who retires in the same year takes part in the jubilee celebration, a pensioners' meeting and a company outing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The participation of an employee in more than two similar company events is harmless if it serves to fulfill professional tasks, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "if the HR manager or works council members attend the events of several departments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Usual benefits (4) Usual benefits at a company event include, in particular, food, drinks, tobacco products and sweets, the assumption of travel costs, even if the journey itself is already an experience, tickets for cultural and sporting events if the company event is not in attendance exhausted at a cultural or sporting event, gifts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is also customary to subsequently present the gifts to employees who, for operational or personal reasons, were unable to attend the company event, but who did not receive a cash benefit, expenses for the external framework, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "for rooms, music, bowling alley, for artistic and artistic performances, if the performances are not the main purpose of the company event"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer's expenses, including sales tax, for the customary benefits within the meaning of numbers 1 to 5 to the individual employee total more than DM 200 per event, the expenses must be added to the wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(5) The following also applies: Benefits to the spouse or a relative of the employee, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Child, fianc\u00e9, are attributable to the employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Cash benefits that are granted instead of the benefits in kind mentioned in paragraph 4 nos. 1 to 3 are treated as such if their appropriate use is ensured"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If employees take part in a company event who work at a location other than that of the company, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the field service employee of a company, the expenses for the trip to the participation may differ from the BFH judgment of 25 5 1992 - BStBl II S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "856 are treated as travel expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Taxation of benefits (6) In the case of a non-conventional (unusual) company event, all benefits to the employees, including the expenses for the external framework (Paragraph 4 No. 5), are part of the wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The general regulations apply to the collection of wage tax; Section 40 (2) EStG is applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to gifts that are customary by their nature and for which the DM 200 limit of paragraph 4 sentence 2 is exceeded, as well as for non-customary gifts, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Gifts, the total value of which exceeds DM 60, or benefits to individual employees, on the occasion - not only on occasion - of a company event"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 73 Attentions (1) Benefits in kind by the employer, which are also usually exchanged in social interactions and do not lead to any significant enrichment of the employee, do not belong to wages as mere attentions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Attentions are gifts in kind up to a value of 60 DM, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Flowers, luxury items, a book or a sound carrier that are given to the employee or his relatives on the occasion of a special personal event"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Donations of money are always part of wages, even if their value is low"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) As gifts, drinks and semi-luxury goods that the employer leaves to the employees for consumption in the company free of charge or partially are not part of the wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to meals that the employer gives the employees on the occasion of and during an extraordinary work assignment, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "during an extraordinary company meeting or meeting, in the overwhelming interest of the company in a favorable organization of the work process, free of charge or partially paid and the value of which does not exceed 60 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 74 Further professional training or further training services by the employer (1) Professional further training or further training services by the employer do not result in wages if these training measures are carried out in the overriding operational interests of the employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter whether the training measures are carried out at the workplace, in central company facilities or in external facilities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Sentences 1 and 2 also apply to training measures by external companies that are provided for the employer's account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) In the case of a training measure, an overriding operational interest of the employer is to be assumed if it is to increase the employability of the employee in the employer's company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This requirement can be regarded as fulfilled in particular if the employer evaluates participation in the training event as work and at least partially counts it against the regular working hours"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An overriding operational interest can also be assumed for the SGB III corresponding qualification and training measures, which the employer or an intermediary employment company provides in connection with termination agreements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee does not undergo further training in the overwhelming operational interest of the employer, the value of the further training or further training service provided by the employer to be determined in accordance with Section 8 (2) EStG is part of the wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If necessary, the employee can"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "den Wert einer beruflichen Fort- und Weiterbildung im Rahmen des \u00a7 9 Abs 1 Satz 1 EStG als Werbungskosten (&gt;R 34) oder im Rahmen des \u00a7 10 Abs 1 Nr 7 EStG als Sonderausgaben geltend machen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) Even if further training or further education services according to the above regulations do not lead to wages, the employer's expenses, which are caused by the employee's participation in the training event, are, however, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Travel expenses incurred in addition to the costs for the actual training or further education service, to be treated according to R 37 to 40 a and 43"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 75 Pension payments (1) The tax-privileged pension payments according to Section 19 Paragraph 2 EStG also include: Death grants within the meaning of Section 18 Paragraph 1 Paragraph 2 No. 1 and Paragraph 3 of the Civil Service Pension Act - BeamtVG - as well as corresponding remuneration in private service"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax-privileged pension payments do not include payments that are paid as remuneration for the month of death on the basis of the employment contract; On the other hand, special benefits to surviving dependents that are granted over and above the wages owed up to the end of the employment relationship are pension payments, transitional benefits, which, according to the BAT, are paid to employees in the military air traffic control service, at the Federal Office for Air Traffic Control in the air traffic control service, in the correctional service and in the communal fire service as well as to pilots of measurement aircraft and to technical pilots, including the monthly compensation amount to be paid to surviving dependents and including the compensation that is to be paid in addition to the transitional pension taking into account the transitional allowance according to \u00a7\u00a7 62 63 BAT, as well as the transitional pension that according to \u00a7 7 of the collective agreement of 30 11 1991 on a socially acceptable downsizing in the area of \u200b\u200bthe Federal Ministry of Defense is paid, the remuneration of civil servants in temporary retirement, according to \u00a7 44 paragraph 4 of the federal civil servant ngesetzes - BBG - as well as the corresponding provisions of the civil service laws of the federal states"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Additional payments within the meaning of Section 44 (5) BBG as well as the corresponding provisions of the civil service laws of the federal states do not belong to the tax-privileged pension payments, the maintenance contributions according to Sections 15 and 26 BeamtVG as well as Section 69 BeamtVG in connection with Sections 120 130 BBG or corresponding state law Regulations, the pension payments of retired civil servants, former professional soldiers and professional RAD leaders according to Sections 35 53 to 55 G 131, the payments according to Sections 37b, 37c, 37d and 51 Paragraph 1 G 131 as well as the payments that are made according to the in Section 64 para 3 sentence 1 G 131, including the supplements granted for this purpose, the pension according to section 10 para 1 sentence 1 of the Act regulating the reparation of National Socialist injustices for members of the public service - BWG\u00f6D - including the according to section 10 para 3 Sentence 1 BWG\u00f6D increased retirement pension as well as retirement pension according to \u00a7 20 Abs 1 and according to \u00a7 21 Abs 1 in connection with \u00a7 10 BWG\u00f6D, remuneration according to \u00a7 1 1a and 31d BWG\u00f6D, the pensions of the political election officials on time, the pension and honorary pay of the former members of the government including the corresponding survivor's benefits, but not the transitional allowance according to \u00a7 14 of the Federal Ministers Act and corresponding benefits based on the laws of the federal states,"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Special allowances according to \u00a7 4 of the law on the granting of an annual special allowance as well as corresponding benefits according to the laws of the federal states if they are paid to recipients of remuneration within the meaning of \u00a7 19 para 2 EStG, disappearance payments according to \u00a7 29 para 2 BeamtVG and corresponding benefits under the civil service laws of the federal states, severance payments according to \u00a7 69 BeamtVG in connection with \u00a7 153 BBG or corresponding state law provisions, maintenance grants according to \u00a7\u00a7 5 and 6 of the Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg law for the uniform termination of the political cleansing of 13 July 1953 (Ges"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "91), honorary salary of the former honorary mayors and their surviving dependents according to \u00a7 6 of the Baden-W\u00fcrttemberg law on expense allowance for honorary mayors and honorary mayors dated June 19, 1987 (Ges"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "281), honorary salary of the former mayors and former district council presidents according to Articles 138 and 138 a of the Bavarian law on municipal electoral officers, the pension based on a reparation notice according to \u00a7 21 BWG\u00f6D according to the law on additional old-age and survivors' benefits for employees and workers the Free and Hanseatic City of Hamburg - Retirement Benefit Act - is paid, even if the recipients are not able to work or are unable to work, the retirement benefits, the former employees and workers of the Free and Hanseatic City of Hamburg, which fall under \u00a7 63 G 131 and according to the Third amendment to G 131 retired at the end of September 30, 1961, received due to their previous employment according to \u00a7 52 G 131 in connection with the Pension Act, honorary pay of the former honorary mayors and treasurers and their surviving dependents according to the Hessian law on the Expense allowances and the honorary salary of honorary mayor and the honorary treasurer of the municipalities from 7 October 1970 (GVBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "635), honorary pay of the former honorary mayors, councilors and mayors according to the Rhineland-Palatinate Honorary Pay Act of 18 December 1972 (GVBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "376), retirement pensions and pension payments that are based on Article 3 of Annex 1 of the Saar Treaty (BGBl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "1956 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "1587) are paid to persons who have been retired due to the reorganization of the Saarland, the remuneration of the mayors and administrators appointed in Saarland after August 8, 1945, which according to the law to supplement the municipal regulations of 10 July 1953 (Official Journal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "415) have been retired, honorary pay of the former honorary mayors, councilors and heads of office according to Saarland law no 987 of 6 3 1974 (Official Journal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "357), early retirement benefits, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "within the meaning of the Early Retirement Act, provided that the employee has reached the age of 62 during the wage payment period, and 60 for severely disabled persons"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) If a beneficiary receives wages from a current employment relationship and is therefore, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "according to \u00a7 53 BeamtVG, the pension payments are reduced, only the reduced pension payments according to \u00a7 19 para 2 EStG are tax-privileged; the same applies if pension payments are reduced after the divorce (Section 57 BeamtVG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Subsequent payments of pension payments to heirs of a beneficiary who are not entitled to a pension are not favored under Section 19 (2) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 76 Payment of wages to the heirs or surviving dependents of a deceased employee (1) Wages that are paid after the death of the employee may no longer be taxed according to the tax characteristics of the deceased, regardless of the legal reason for the payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of current wages that are paid in or for the month of death, for reasons of simplification, the tax withholding can still be made according to the tax characteristics of the deceased; In this case, however, the income tax certificate must also be written out on the heir's income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) If the employer pays the wages to an heir or a survivor, the wage tax withholding is to be carried out subject to paragraph 1 sentence 2 only according to its taxation criteria"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The amounts passed on to the other beneficiaries represent negative income in the calendar year in which they are passed on"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If this concerns pension payments within the meaning of Section 19 (2) EStG, the gross amount of the amounts passed on to the other beneficiaries must first be used as a basis for calculating the negative income; this gross amount must then be reduced by the difference between the pension allowance taken into account in the wage tax deduction and the pension allowance applicable to the remaining portion of the payee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The dispute payments are to be recorded by the recipients - possibly reduced by the pension allowance (Section 19 (2) EStG) - as income from non-self-employed work as part of an assessment for income tax (Section 46 (2) No. 1 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) The following applies to the tax deduction by the employer: In the case of wages that are still paid for the active work of the deceased employee, as would have been the case with a payment to the employee, between current wages, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Wages for the month of death or the previous month, and other payments, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Profit-sharing to distinguish"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wages for the month of death, if they are payable under labor law for the entire wage payment period, do not represent a pension within the meaning of Section 19 (2) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, there is an entitlement to wage payment only up to the date of death, the additional benefits to the surviving dependents are pension payments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This applies accordingly in the event that the labor law agreements only provide for the payment of survivors' benefits for the month of death or there are no contractual agreements on wages when the employment relationship is terminated during the wage payment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, too, only the part of the remuneration that falls after the date of death constitutes a pension"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the cases of paragraph 1 sentence 2, the pension allowance is not to be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The death benefit is a pension and basically represents another type of payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies in the event that several monthly salaries are paid as death grants, because this is basically only a one-off payment in installments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, the ongoing payment of widow's or surviving dependents' benefits within the meaning of Section 19 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 2 EStG by the employer is to be treated regularly as current wages (pension payments)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the payments to the heirs or surviving dependents are not pension payments, it must be checked whether the retirement benefit (Section 24a EStG) is used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This is based on the age of the respective payee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Paragraph 2 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Soweit Zahlungen an im Ausland wohnhafte Erben oder Hinterbliebene erfolgen, bei denen die Voraussetzungen des \u00a7\u00a7 1 Abs 2 oder 3 1a EStG nicht vorliegen, ist beim Steuerabzug nach den f\u00fcr Lohnzahlungen an beschr\u00e4nkt einkommensteuerpflichtige Arbeitnehmer geltenden Vorschriften zu verfahren (&gt; \u00a7 39 d EStG und R 125); Absatz 1 Satz 2 gilt auch in diesen F\u00e4llen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It should be noted, however, that on the basis of a double taxation agreement, the country of residence may be entitled to the right to tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 77 Tax-privileged transfer of asset stakes General (1) Section 19a of the Income Tax Act applies to employees who are subject to unlimited and limited income tax and who are currently employed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The transfer of asset shares to former employees of the employer is only tax-deductible if the free or discounted asset share is still left as wages for the actual work performance in the context of a settlement of the previous employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The prerequisite for tax relief is not that the employer is the legal owner of the asset participation to be transferred"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax relief therefore also applies to the pecuniary advantage that arises when the asset share is transferred by a third party, if the transfer is caused by the current employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A tax-privileged transfer of assets by third parties is z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "before, if the employee receives the asset participation directly from a representative of the employer, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "a credit institute, or a company that is affiliated with the employer's company in a group (Section 18 AktG) (issue of shares or other equity investments by a group parent company to employees of the group subsidiary or between other group companies), or by a third-party company, with whom the employer has made appropriate agreements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter whether the employer is involved in the transfer or whether the employer reimburses the third party for the price of the asset participation or the costs arising from the transfer in whole or in part"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) The tax relief only applies to the pecuniary advantage that the employee receives from the free or discounted transfer of the asset share"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, cash payments by the employer to the employee to establish or acquire the asset participation or capital-forming benefits agreed for the employee within the meaning of the VermBG, which are invested to establish or acquire the asset participation, are not tax-privileged"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The assumption of the custody fees and ancillary costs associated with the transfer of assets by the employer, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Notarial fees, entry fees in connection with business credit at a cooperative and costs for entries in the register are not considered wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Cash grants from the employer to the employee for custody fees incurred by the employee by setting the securities for the duration of the blocking period are also not wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Conversion of wages (4) The granting of an asset participation is not free or cheaper if the asset participation takes the place of wages in whole or in part, which is owed anyway at the time of the transfer of the asset participation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "With such a conversion there is therefore no pecuniary benefit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A conversion of wages into an asset participation occurs when the employee can receive a cash payment instead of the asset participation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, there is no conversion if the asset participation is transferred on the basis of a collective agreement opening clause, according to which the employee does not have a right to a corresponding cash payment in the event of an asset participation agreement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Definition of asset participations (5) The asset participations, the transfer of which is tax-privileged according to \u00a7 19a EStG, are finally listed in \u00a7 19a Paragraph 3 in conjunction with Paragraph 3 a to 7 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "According to this, investments in assets in the employer's company (company investments) as well as investments in assets in other companies (non-company investments) can be granted tax-deductible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Asset sharing can only be granted tax-privileged if its term does not end before the six-year blocking period has expired"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Value of the asset participation (6) The value of asset participation within the meaning of Section 19a Paragraph 3 EStG is based on Section 19a Paragraph 8 EStG even if the tax relief of Section 19a Paragraph 1 EStG is not used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(7) If a controlling company within the meaning of Section 18 Paragraph 1 AktG decides to transfer property investments within the meaning of Section 19a Paragraph 3 Nos. 1 to 3 in conjunction with Paragraph 3 a to 7 EStG to employees of the group, this day is deemed to be the day the passing of resolutions within the meaning of Section 19a (8) sentence 2 EStG; this also applies if the dependent company reproduces the transfer decision of the controlling company in its own resolution without acquiring the securities from it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the dependent company acquires the securities, the day on which the resolution is passed is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(8) The day of posting is deemed to be the day of booking out by the hiring party or their vicarious agents"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(9) Investments in assets within the meaning of Section 19a Paragraph 3 No. 1 to 3 Paragraph 3 a and 5 EStG, for which a price was not determined on the date of the resolution and within 30 days before the date of the resolution, either in official trading, in the regulated market or in the regulated open market are to be set at the common value on the day of transfer; If a price is determined on this day, this is the common value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a stock exchange price is not available when shares are first listed on the stock exchange, neither on the day of the resolution nor on the day of release, the fair value of the newly introduced shares is to be set at the issue price that is decisive for private investors, if this is determined on the day of the decision or on the day of release"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplicity, the value of new shares that have not yet been listed on the stock exchange but are already fully entitled to dividends can be derived from the price of the old shares on the day of the resolution"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of new shares that have not yet been listed on the stock exchange and are not yet fully entitled to dividends, a total discount of 10 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of the stock exchange price of the old shares, no more than 30%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "from the nominal value of the share, in the case of no-par shares from the pro-rata value of the share capital"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The value determined applies to all new shares that are made available to the employee within 9 months of the decision date"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "After 9 months, the price of the old shares on the day of transfer is to be used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the evaluation within a group, paragraph 7 sentences 1 and 2 are to be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(10) Whether non-securitized participations in assets within the meaning of Section 19a Paragraph 3 No. 7, 9 10 and 11 Paragraph 3a and 5 EStG are to be assessed at a higher or lower value than the nominal value due to special circumstances (Section 19a Paragraph 8 Sentence 7 EStG) is according to the principles of R 109 ErbStR to decide"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a loan claim within the meaning of Section 19a (3) No. 10 EStG, a value to be set above the nominal value is only to be set due to the fact that the debtor cannot terminate the loan if it is clearly agreed that the employer will not accept the loan claim during the six-year blocking period may terminate; this does not already result from an agreement that corresponds to the wording of Section 19a (1) sentence 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(11) The average value of capital contributions or shares in a GmbH is to be determined by a fictitious share valuation according to the principles of \u00a7 11 Paragraph 2 BewG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The determination is carried out by the company tax office responsible for the GmbH"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Capital contributions or shares in a GmbH, which did not exist at the beginning of the calendar year, are generally to be valued with the paid-in capital"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In companies that z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "have arisen through conversion from a partnership or a sole proprietorship or as part of a business split from an existing company, however, the determination of the common value must be carried out by the company tax office of the GmbH according to the principles of R 98 to 100 ErbStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The income percentage can be derived from the previous operating results of the partnership or sole proprietorship, whereby the effects of the changed legal form may be"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "durch entsprechende Korrekturen der Betriebsergebnisse zu ber\u00fccksichtigen sind (&gt;R 102 Abs 2 ErbStR)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Ermittlung des steuerfreien geldwerten Vorteils (12)Der geldwerte Vorteil ergibt sich aus dem Unterschied zwischen dem Wert der Verm\u00f6gensbeteiligung (&gt; Abs\u00e4tze 6 bis 11) und dem Preis, zu dem die Verm\u00f6gensbeteiligung dem Arbeitnehmer \u00fcberlassen wird"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(13) The maximum tax-free amount is based on the employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee has several employment relationships in succession or next to each other in the calendar year, the maximum tax-free amount can be claimed in each employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Verwahrung von Wertpapieren (14)Die Verpflichtung des Arbeitnehmers zur Vorlage der Verwahrungsbescheinigung (\u00a7 5 Abs 4 LStDV) besteht auch in den F\u00e4llen, in denen die Wertpapiere von Dritten steuerbeg\u00fcnstigt \u00fcberlassen worden sind und der Arbeitgeber in irgendeiner Form tats\u00e4chlich oder rechtlich in die \u00dcberlassung eingeschaltet war (&gt; Absatz 2 Satz 3 und 4)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Aufzeichnungs- und Anzeigepflichten (15)Der Arbeitgeber hat diese Aufzeichnungs- und Anzeigepflichten nach \u00a7 5 Abs 3 und \u00a7 6 LStDV auch in den F\u00e4llen zu erf\u00fcllen, in denen die Wertpapiere von Dritten steuerbeg\u00fcnstigt \u00fcberlassen worden sind und der Arbeitgeber in irgendeiner Form tats\u00e4chlich oder rechtlich in die \u00dcberlassung eingeschaltet war (&gt; Absatz 2 Satz 3 und 4)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Subsequent taxation (16) Subsequent taxation (Section 19a (2) sentence 2 EStG, Section 7 LStDV) is also to be carried out if the employee does not submit the safekeeping certificate (Section 5 (4) LStDV) in due time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "There is no subsequent taxation in the cases of Section 19a (2) sentence 4 EStG and in the case of a non-harmful disposition according to Section 19a (2) sentence 5 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Worthlessness within the meaning of Section 19a (2) sentence 4 EStG is to be assumed if the employee does not exceed 10 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the value of the asset participation that was used to determine the pecuniary benefit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the amounts repaid exceed the 10-percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Limit, the subsequent taxation is only omitted if the employee sets the amounts received or other investments in assets acquired with a bank for the remainder of the blocking period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 78 Altersentlastungsbetrag - unbesetzt - R 79 Zur Ber\u00fccksichtigung von Kindern und zum Kinderfreibetrag - unbesetzt - R 80 - R 89 - unbesetzt - R 90 Haushaltsfreibetrag, Zuordnung von Kindern - unbesetzt - R 91 Anwendung des Progressionsvorbehalts auf Lohn- und Einkommensersatzleistungen - unbesetzt - R 92 Au\u00dfergew\u00f6hnliche Belastungen allgemeiner Art - unbesetzt - R 93 - R 95 - unbesetzt - R 96 Aufwendungen f\u00fcr den Unterhalt und eine etwaige Berufsausbildung - unbesetzt - R 97 Ausbildungsfreibetr\u00e4ge - unbesetzt - R 98 Aufwendungen f\u00fcr eine Hilfe im Haushalt oder f\u00fcr vergleichbare Dienstleistungen - unbesetzt - R 99 - unbesetzt - R 100 Pauschbetr\u00e4ge f\u00fcr Behinderte, Hinterbliebene und Pflegepersonen - unbesetzt - R 101 Kinderbetreuungskosten - unbesetzt - R 102 Eink\u00fcnfte aus der Verg\u00fctung f\u00fcr eine mehrj\u00e4hrige T\u00e4tigkeit - unbesetzt - R 103 Zuwendungen an politische Parteien - unbesetzt - R 104 Steuerabzug vom Arbeitslohn Der Lohnsteuer unterliegt grunds\u00e4tzlich jeder von einem inl\u00e4ndischen Arbeitgeber (&gt;R 105) gezahlte Arbeitslohn"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter whether it is regular or one-off payments and in what form they are granted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer has to withhold income tax regardless of whether the employee is assessed for income tax or not"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Bei laufendem Arbeitslohn kommt es f\u00fcr die Beurteilung, ob Lohnsteuer einzubehalten ist, allein auf die Verh\u00e4ltnisse des jeweiligen Lohnzahlungszeitraums an; eine Ausnahme gilt, wenn der sogenannte permanente Lohnsteuer-Jahresausgleich nach \u00a7 39b Abs 2 Satz 7 EStG durchgef\u00fchrt wird (&gt;R 121 Abs 2)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 104 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Inflow of wages (1) The wage tax deduction presupposes the inflow of wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer has fulfilled a wage appropriation agreement made with the employee, wages have accrued if the employee can economically dispose of it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The special regulation for the time allocation of the - accrued - wages (Section 11 Paragraph 1 Clause 3 in conjunction with Section 38a Paragraph 1 Clause 2 and 3 EStG) remains unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 105 Withholding obligation of the employer (1) Every domestic employer is obliged to withhold wage tax from wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the withholding of the wage tax of its temporary workers, the foreign hirer has to fulfill the same obligations as a domestic employer according to \u00a7 38 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 2 EStG, even if he is not a domestic employer himself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) In addition to the facilities listed in \u00a7 12 sentence 2 AO, operating facilities are also landing bridges (landing stages of shipping companies), offices and other business facilities that the entrepreneur or co-entrepreneur or his permanent representative, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "an authorized signatory to exercise the trade"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) Permanent representative according to \u00a7 13 AO can be z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "also be a person who runs a branch or supervises a construction team"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, permanent representative is z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "not a single fitter who carries out assembly work in Germany on a case-by-case basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4)Bei Bauausf\u00fchrungen oder Montagen ausl\u00e4ndischer Arbeitgeber im Inland, die l\u00e4nger als sechs Monate (&gt; \u00a7 12 Satz 2 Nr 8 AO) dauern, ist der ausl\u00e4ndische Arbeitgeber zugleich als inl\u00e4ndischer Arbeitgeber im Sinne des \u00a7 38 Abs 1 Satz 1 Nr 1 EStG anzusehen, gleichg\u00fcltig ob die Bauausf\u00fchrung oder Montage nach dem DBA eine Betriebsst\u00e4tte begr\u00fcndet"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the construction or assembly does not establish a permanent establishment according to the applicable double taxation agreement, the wages paid to the foreign employees deployed in Germany are generally exempt from income tax if they are in Germany for a maximum of 183 days in a calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 106 Paying wages by third parties, tips Paying wages by third parties (1) The employer is obliged to withhold wage tax if he is actually or legally involved in the wage payment in any form"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, he also has to withhold wage tax from wages if a third party is actually or legally involved in the payment of wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the third party is domiciled in Germany or abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The employer must also withhold the wage tax and fulfill the other related obligations if the wages are paid by a third party within the framework of the employment relationship, usually and for work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "These requirements are z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "fulfilled when voluntary tips are paid by the customer in the service industry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer cannot determine these payments himself, the employee must notify him in writing for each wage payment period (Section 38 (1) sentence 2 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee must confirm the accuracy of his information by signature"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer must keep the notification as a receipt for the payroll account and subject the specified remuneration, together with the employee's remaining wages, to wage tax deduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer does not have to withhold any wage tax from earnings that are not paid as part of the employment relationship, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "from wages from a second or further employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to payments that are not usually paid by a third party or not for work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Zahlt im Fall unerlaubter Arbeitnehmer\u00fcberlassung der Entleiher anstelle des Verleihers den Arbeitslohn an die Arbeitnehmer, so ist der Entleiher regelm\u00e4\u00dfig nicht Dritter, sondern Arbeitgeber im Sinne des \u00a7 38 Abs 1 Satz 1 Nr 1 EStG (&gt;R 146 Abs 1)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Tips etc"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "with legal entitlement (3) tips, service surcharges and similar benefits to which the employee has a legal entitlement, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the service charge of 10 or 15 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "in the catering industry are subject to wage tax deduction in full"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The amount is set in an order under labor law or in an agreement between the employer and the tipper"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer has to subject the determined amount together with the other current wages of the employee to the wage tax deduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Freiwillige Trinkgelder (4)Trinkgelder, auf die der Arbeitnehmer keinen Rechtsanspruch hat (freiwillige Trinkgelder), sind zus\u00e4tzlicher Arbeitslohn soweit sie 2400 DM im Kalenderjahr \u00fcbersteigen (&gt; \u00a7 3 Nr 51 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A voluntary tip is also the amount by which the tip giver increases the tip to which the employee is legally entitled (tip over, special tip)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee must notify the employer of the voluntary tips accrued to him in accordance with paragraph 2, sentences 3 and 4, if it can be assumed that the exemption of DM 2,400 will be exceeded in the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer must keep the notification as a receipt for the payroll account and, to the extent that it exceeds DM 200 per month, DM 4670 per week or DM 670 per day, subject to wage tax deduction, together with the employee's other current wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Employer liability (5) In principle, the employer is not liable for wage tax which he has not withheld due to incomplete or incorrect information from the employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 107 Marital status - unoccupied - R 108 Procedure for issuing the income tax card Basics and conclusion of the general issuing procedure (1) The municipality has issued the income tax cards on the basis of their legal registration documents, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Register of residents or residents' register"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The surname must be clearly identifiable in the employee's address; if the family name is given first, it is separated from the first name (s) by a comma"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The entry of an artist name is possible, provided it is included in the registration documents"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wage tax cards are to be sent to the employees by their staff or by post immediately after they have been issued, together with information on wage tax, which are made available to the municipality by the tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The issuing and transmission of the tax cards must be carried out in such a way that the tax cards are in the possession of the employees by October 31 at the latest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The day on which the tax card is issued must be noted on the tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Application for change (2) Once an application for entry of a less favorable tax class or number of child allowances on the income tax card is to be taken into account when issuing the income tax cards for the following years until it is revoked"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Bescheinigung von Kindern (3)Kinder, die nicht in der Wohnung des Arbeitnehmers gemeldet sind, darf die Gemeinde nur ber\u00fccksichtigen, wenn ihr f\u00fcr dieses Kind eine steuerliche Lebensbescheinigung (&gt;R 109 Abs 6) vorgelegen hat, die nicht \u00e4lter als drei Jahre ist oder wenn der Gemeinde durch das Finanzamt die Ber\u00fccksichtigung dieses Kindes f\u00fcr das vorangegangene oder das davor liegende Kalenderjahr nach &gt;R 109 Abs 9 Nr 1 angezeigt worden ist oder wenn das Kind in den letzten zwei Jahren vor dem Beginn des Kalenderjahrs aus der inl\u00e4ndischen Wohnung eines Elternteils in die inl\u00e4ndische Wohnung des anderen Elternteils umgezogen ist und der Gemeinde eine R\u00fcckmeldung vorgelegen hat"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the municipality does not have to enter any child allowances, two dashes \"- -\" must be attached"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Certification of the religious community (4) The information on the income tax card must be used to identify the religious communities that have transferred the collection of church tax to the tax authorities and that are entitled to the church tax to be withheld in individual cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The following abbreviations are to be used: ev = evangelical (Protestant), rk = Roman Catholic, ak = Old Catholic"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The supreme state authorities responsible for financial management as well as the regional finance directorates can allow further abbreviations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If no church tax is to be withheld, two dashes \"- -\" must be entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of spouses who are not permanently separated and both are subject to unlimited income tax, the church tax code for the spouse is only to be stated for spouses of different denominations; In the case of spouses of the same denomination and of different faith, the church tax code for the spouse is not to be certified"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Entry of the municipality key and the number of the tax office. In addition to the municipality, your official municipality key (AGS) and, in addition to the name of the tax office, also its four-digit number according to the national tax office key, must be entered on the income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Registration of the lump sums for the disabled and surviving dependents (6) For the entry of the lump sums for the disabled and surviving dependents, the responsible tax office must inform the municipalities of the employees concerned and the required characteristics"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When registering, suitable precautions must be taken to prevent unauthorized changes and both the municipality and the date of registration must be indicated; a signature is not necessary if the entries are made automatically"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Issuance of income tax cards with tax classes V and VI (7) The number of child allowances is not to be indicated on income tax cards on which tax class V or VI is certified; on the other hand the religious community is to be designated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the municipality can issue an income tax card with tax class V or VI as part of the general issuing procedure if the employee was issued a tax card with tax class V or VI in the previous year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Issuance of income tax cards for prisoners and those released from prison (8) If a prisoner or person released from prison who is registered at the address of the correctional facility (JVA) wants to avoid that his income tax card contains the address of the prison, he can opt for the issue of the income tax card in the general issuing procedure dispense"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If he applies for a wage tax card after his release from prison, its subsequent issue, for which the municipality in whose district the prison is located is still responsible, must be combined with the registration with the first municipality of residence after release in such a way that the new registration address is entered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Obligation of the municipality and the employee (9) The municipality has to announce the completion of the transmission of the income tax cards with the request to apply for the issue of any missing income tax cards"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Before the beginning of the calendar year or before the start of an employment relationship, the employee must apply to the responsible municipality for an income tax card to be issued if the income tax card was not received as part of the general issuing procedure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Die Gemeinde hat einen mit einer Rechtsbehelfsbelehrung versehenen schriftlichen Bescheid zu erteilen, wenn dem Antrag des Arbeitnehmers auf Ausstellung der Lohnsteuerkarte nicht entsprochen wird (&gt; \u00a7 39 Abs 6 Satz 1 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "List of wage tax cards issued (10) The municipality must keep a list of the wage tax cards it has issued in a suitable form, which must contain the date of issue of the wage tax card and the entries made on the wage tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The register must be submitted to the locally responsible tax office on request"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Security measures (11) For security reasons, all income tax cards that are not issued with electronic data processing systems, punch card systems or addressing machines must be provided with the official seal of the issuing municipality and a signature; the imprint of an official seal and a facsimile signature on the tax card is not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The municipalities have to take special security measures for the storage of the employment tax card forms"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Any remaining stock of income tax card forms must be destroyed immediately after the end of the year for which the income tax cards are valid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 109 Changes and additions to the income tax card Changes to incorrect entries (1) Entries on the income tax card which were based on the circumstances at the beginning of the calendar year and which are incorrect must be changed upon request"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The application deadline stipulated in Section 39 (5) EStG only applies to applications for changes and additions to the income tax card that are made in the event of a change in circumstances during the course of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Change of tax brackets (2) If an employee's marriage is dissolved through divorce or annulment, or if the spouses have brought about permanent separation, entries on the income tax card may not be changed; only a change of tax class according to paragraph 5 is possible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply if, in the case of a marriage dissolved by divorce or annulment, the other spouse remarried in the same calendar year, does not live permanently separated from his new spouse and he and his new spouse are subject to unlimited income tax; In these cases, the tax class entered on the income tax card of the unmarried spouse must be changed to tax class III upon request if the requirements of Section 38b No. 3 letter c double letter aa EStG are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) If a marriage is dissolved through death, the tax class III must be certified on the income tax card of the other spouse upon application with effect from the beginning of the first calendar month following the date of death of the spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite is that the employee and his deceased spouse were subject to unlimited income tax at the beginning or in the course of the calendar year and did not live permanently apart"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) If a child is registered with both parents in the cases of Section 32 (7) sentence 2 EStG and if it is to be assigned to the father with the consent of the mother, the certificate of tax class II is with the father and any resulting change in tax class is with the mother with effect from the beginning of the calendar year or from the relevant point in time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a father is certified in tax class II at his request, the municipality or the tax office that issues the certificate must inform the municipality or the tax office that is responsible for changing tax class II to tax class I on the mother's income tax card is"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the domicile tax office (\u00a7 19 AO) of the father must be informed, unless the tax class II certificate has already been issued by this tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the mother has given her permanent consent to the assignment of children to the father and this is evident from the notification, the tax class II certificate no longer needs to be communicated in the following years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a permanent consent is withdrawn with effect for the following calendar year (Section 32 Paragraph 6 Clause 6 and Paragraph 7 EStG), the municipality or the tax office, which then certifies tax class II for the mother, has the authority of the municipality or the tax office that is responsible for changing tax class II to tax class I on the father's income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the tax office of the father's residence must be informed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The certificate of tax class II due to the assignment of children to one parent requires the withdrawal of tax class II from the other parent if tax class II has been certified there based on the previous assignment of these children"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Section 39, Paragraph 4 of the Income Tax Act applies; the exception rule contained in Section 39 (4) sentence 1 second half-sentence EStG does not apply to the allocation of children"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a child is registered with the mother and a grandparent, sentences 1 to 7 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Sentences 1 to 7 are also to be applied accordingly if a child is only registered with the father and one grandparent at the same time in the cases under Section 32 (7) sentence 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4a) The tax class II or III certificate on the basis of Section 1a Paragraph 1 No. 2 and 3 EStG for employees who are subject to unlimited income tax and who are citizens of a member state of the European Union or the states of Iceland, Norway or Liechtenstein is reserved for the tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Change of tax class (5) In the case of spouses who both receive wages, the municipality has to change the tax classes entered on the income tax cards at the joint request of the spouses as follows (change of tax class - \u00a7 39 Paragraph 5 Clause 3 and 4 EStG): Is on the income tax cards of both spouses certifies tax class IV, these entries must be changed to tax class III on the income tax card of one spouse and to tax class V on the income tax card of the other spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If tax class III is certified on the income tax card of one spouse and tax class V on the income tax card of the other spouse, these entries on the income tax cards of both spouses must be changed to tax class IV"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If tax class III is certified on the income tax card of one spouse and tax class V on the income tax card of the other spouse, the entry of tax class III on the income tax card of one spouse is in tax class V and the entry of tax class V on the income tax card of the other spouse to change to tax class III"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A change in tax class may take effect at the earliest from the beginning of the calendar month following the application"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The application can only be submitted by November 30 of the calendar year for which the income tax cards are valid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Only one application can be submitted in a calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply if a change in the entry is requested because one spouse no longer receives a taxable wage or has died, because the spouses have separated for a long time or if an employment relationship is resumed after unemployment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A change of tax class made after receipt of the income tax cards, but before the beginning of the calendar year for which the income tax cards apply, is also not a change of tax class, as is the first change of tax class due to the marriage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Change of entries for children by the municipality; Tax life certificate (6) Because of the children of an employee who are subject to unlimited income tax at the beginning of the calendar year, who have not yet reached the age of 18 and who are not registered in the employee's home, a change to the income tax card by the municipality is only permitted if the employee presents a certificate of life for tax purposes issued by the child's municipality of residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Diese darf nicht \u00e4lter als drei Jahre sein (&gt;R 108 Abs 3 Satz 1)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax life certificate for children is to be issued on request to persons who are related to the child in the first degree if the child is not registered in that person's home and has not yet reached the age of 18 at the beginning of the calendar year; the issuance is free of charge in accordance with section 39 (1) sentence 1 of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Statements about a foster child relationship are only to be included in the life certificate if there is a notification from the tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The municipality with which the child is registered with (main) residence is responsible for issuing the certificate of life"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The forms for the life certificate are made available to the municipalities by the tax offices free of charge"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The municipalities can issue the certificate of life in another form at their own expense if it contains the information required in the sample form"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Bei Ausstellung der Lebensbescheinigung hat die Gemeinde festzustellen, ob sie dieses Kind in einer von ihr ausgestellten Lohnsteuerkarte mit dem Z\u00e4hler 1 ber\u00fccksichtigt hat ob eine Mitteilung des Finanzamts \u00fcber die Eintragung des Z\u00e4hlers 1 f\u00fcr dieses Kind vorliegt ( &gt; Absatz 9 Nr 2 Buchstabe b)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If necessary, in the case of number 1, she has to change the income tax card ex officio (Section 39 (4) sentences 3 and 4 EStG) or, in the case of number 2, to inform the tax office about the issue of the life certificate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Changes to the entries for children by the tax office (7) The entries for children are to be changed by the tax office in Section II of the income tax card in accordance with Section 39, Paragraph 3 a EStG for children a) who have reached the age of 18 at the beginning of the calendar year or b) the foster children are, for children who have not yet reached the age of 18 at the beginning of the calendar year and who are not registered in the employee's apartment, if the employee cannot provide a life certificate for this child or if the foster child status is uncertain according to the life certificate, if the employee is entitled to the child allowance according to Section 32 (6) sentence 2 EStG instead of the child allowance according to Section 32 (6) sentence 1 EStG, because a) the domicile or habitual residence of the other parent cannot be determined or the father of the child cannot be officially determined can be ascertained or b) the other parent is unlikely to have unlimited income for the entire calendar year you are liable for taxes or c) the child allowance of the other parent is to be transferred to the employee if the child allowance is to be transferred to the employee as a step-parent or as a grandparent in accordance with Section 32 (6) sentence 6 EStG; in this case number 3 letter c does not apply for children who are not subject to unlimited income tax and for whom the employee is not entitled to reduced child allowances"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If tax class II is to be used because of a child who is to be certified by the tax office in accordance with numbers 1 2 or 4, tax class II must also be entered by the tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, according to Section 39 (6) sentence 3 EStG, the tax office can also register children under the age of 18 who are subject to unlimited income tax, who would have to be certified by the municipality if the employee claims the child is included in his application for a wage tax reduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Reduced child allowances for children who are not subject to unlimited income tax are not required to be certified"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Simplified entry (7a) In the case of an application in accordance with Section 39 (3a) sentence 2 EStG, the tax office should generally refrain from providing individual information, unless there are specific indications that the number of child allowances in the requested amount cannot be considered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Transfer of a child allowance (8) Meter 1 can be certified if the employee demonstrates that the requirements for the transfer are met and a summary check does not reveal any evidence that the information provided by the employee is incorrect or that the requirements will change during the calendar year will change"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax office of the other parent only needs to be notified of the transfer if it has taken place within the scope of the employee's assessment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The other parent is entitled but not obliged to have their income tax card changed in the event of a transfer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Notifications from the tax offices to the municipalities (9) The tax office must notify the municipality where the employee is registered with the main residence if he / she has registered a child in accordance with paragraph 7 sentence 1 no.2 or paragraph 7 sentence 3, the municipalities to whom the child is registered as having an apartment if he a) has recognized or rejected the child as a foster child for the first time in accordance with paragraph 7 sentence 1 no.1 letter b or b) for a child under 18 years old in accordance with paragraph 7 sentence 1 no.3 letters a or b has certified meter 1"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Temporal effect of the entry (10) In the event of a change or amendment to the income tax card, the municipality or the tax office enter the time from which the change or amendment applies (Section 39 (5) sentence 2 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The date must be entered as the date on which all requirements for a change or an addition to the income tax card were met for the first time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, no day may be entered that is before the beginning of the calendar year for which the income tax card is valid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Wegen des bei einer Steuerklassen\u00e4nderung in den F\u00e4llen des \u00a7 32 Abs 7 Satz 2 EStG einzutragenden Zeitpunkts &gt; Absatz 4 Satz 1; der Zeitpunkt, zu dem die Zustimmung zur Zuordnung von Kindern erteilt wird, ist in diesem Zusammenhang unbeachtlich"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Section 39 (5) sentence 1 EStG remains unaffected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Local jurisdiction (11) In the case of changes and additions to the income tax card, the following applies to the local jurisdiction of the municipalities: If the entries on the income tax card deviate from the actual circumstances or if the actual circumstances change up to the beginning of the calendar year for which the income tax card is valid, so the municipality that issued the tax card is responsible for changing the entries"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This does not apply to changes and additions to the income tax card that have to be made because the employee got married after the income tax card was issued or the conditions for the certification of a child have been met; in these cases, the responsibility of the municipality is based on number 2. If the actual circumstances change in the course of the year for which the income tax card was issued, a) for unmarried employees and married employees whose spouse is not subject to unlimited income tax or who Live permanently separated from their spouse, the municipality is locally responsible in whose district the employee is registered at the time of submission of the income tax card for his apartment, in the case of several apartments for his main residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee is not registered for an apartment, the change must be made by the municipality in whose district the employee has his habitual residence at the time the income tax card is presented, b) for married employees whose spouse is unrestrictedly liable to income tax and those of their spouse do not live permanently separated, the municipality is locally responsible in whose district the spouses at the time of submission of the income tax card, aa) if they only have one apartment in total, for this one joint apartment, bb) if they have several apartments, for a common main residence are reported"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the spouses are not registered for a common home in the sense of the double letter aa or in the case of the double letter bb for a common main home, the change must be made by the municipality in whose district the older spouse at the time of submission of the income tax card for his home, in the case of several apartments for his main residence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 110 Subsequent issuance of income tax cards General (1) For employees who only receive wages in the course of the calendar year, the municipality must, upon application, subsequently issue an income tax card for the calendar year and hand it over to the employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "After the end of the calendar year, an income tax card may no longer be issued with effect for the previous calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Sections 38b, 39 Paragraph 2 3 3a and 3b EStG also apply to the subsequent issuance of income tax cards"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Issuance of an income tax card in the event of marriage (2) If the income tax card is issued to an employee who got married during the calendar year, tax class III can, for reasons of simplification, deviate from Section 39 (3) b sentence 1 EStG on the income tax card with effect from the beginning of the calendar year to be certified; The prerequisite is that no income tax card has been issued for the spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Issuance of an income tax card for the spouse (3) If the income tax card is issued to the spouse of an employee whose income tax card is certified as tax class III, the municipality has to certify tax class V."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "At the request of the spouse, tax class IV and the number of child allowances (Sections 32 (1) 3 and 7 39 (3)) can be changed with effect from the beginning of the calendar year and with effect from the day on which the spouse receives wages 3 3 b and 4 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Tax class IV may only be certified if at the same time tax class III is changed to tax IV on the income tax card of the other spouse with effect from the day on which his spouse receives wages and the application is made before the spouse receives wages for the first time relates"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the application is made at a later point in time, tax class V must be entered on the spouse's income tax card with effect from the beginning of the calendar year; the requested change in tax class IV is to be carried out in accordance with the provisions of Section 39 (5) sentences 3 and 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Issuance of an income tax card upon dissolution of the marriage (4) If the income tax card is issued to an employee whose marriage was annulled or divorced in the course of the calendar year, the municipality must certify the tax class and the number of child allowances that are specified in accordance with Section 38 b No. 3 to 5 39 Paragraph 3 3 b and 5 EStG as well as in accordance with Paragraph 2 above would have been decisive without the dissolution of the marriage; the same applies if the spouses caused the permanent separation in the course of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Notwithstanding this, for an employee whose marriage was annulled or divorced in the course of the calendar year, tax class V and, if applicable, the number with effect from the beginning of the calendar year and with effect from the day on which the employee receives wages, tax class III to certify the child allowance if the other spouse remarried in the same calendar year, does not live permanently separated from his new spouse and he and his new spouse are subject to unlimited income tax and if the requirements of \u00a7 38 b No. 3 letter c double letter aa EStG are otherwise met are fulfilled"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Issuance of an income tax card in the event of the death of the spouse (5) If the income tax card is issued to an employee whose spouse died during the calendar year, the municipality has tax class V with effect from the beginning of the calendar year and with effect from the beginning of the first to certify the date of death of the spouse in the following calendar month to tax class III and, if applicable, the number of child allowances"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If no income tax card was issued for the deceased spouse, the municipality must certify tax class III and, if applicable, the number of child allowances"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite is that the employee and his deceased spouse were subject to unlimited income tax at the beginning or during the calendar year and did not live permanently apart"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Replacement tax card (6) If a replacement tax card is issued for an employee (Section 39, Paragraph 1, Clause 3 EStG), it must be marked as a \"replacement tax card\""}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 111 Procedure for entering an exemption on the income tax card General (1) In the case of an application under Section 39a, Paragraph 2, Clause 5 EStG, the tax office should generally refrain from providing individual information, unless there are specific indications that an exemption is included in the requested Height cannot be considered"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(1a) Sind die Pauschbetr\u00e4ge f\u00fcr Behinderte und Hinterbliebene bei der Ausstellung der Lohnsteuerkarte nicht eingetragen worden (&gt;R 108 Abs 6), kann die Eintragung beim \u00f6rtlich zust\u00e4ndigen Finanzamt beantragt werden (\u00a7 39a Abs 2 Satz 2 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) Insofar as the granting of an exemption due to expenses for a child depends on the employee receiving a child allowance or child benefit for this child, this requirement is also met if the employee is entitled to a child allowance in the wage tax deduction procedure, but he or she is entitled to a child allowance according to \u00a7 39 para 3 b sentence 2 EStG has waived the per se possible entry of a child allowance number for this child or there is a claim to a reduced child allowance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Application limit of DM 1200 (3) To determine whether the application limit of DM 1200 is exceeded, the following applies: Insofar as certain amounts apply for income-related expenses, e"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "f\u00fcr Verpflegungsmehraufwendungen bei Dienstreisen, f\u00fcr Fahrten zwischen Wohnung und Arbeitsst\u00e4tte mit eigenem Kraftfahrzeug &gt;R 37 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "and 42 these are decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of special expenses within the meaning of Section 10 Paragraph 1 No. 1 a, 4 and 6 EStG, the actual expenses are to be recognized, even if these expenses are lower than the lump sum"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For special expenses within the meaning of Section 10 Paragraph 1 No. 1 7 to 9 EStG, the maximum expenses that can be taken into account according to these provisions are to be set"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Membership fees and donations to political parties are also to be taken into account as special expenses insofar as a tax reduction according to \u00a7 34g No. 1 EStG is considered, but not membership fees and donations to associations within the meaning of \u00a7 34g No. 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of extraordinary burdens of a general nature (Section 33 EStG) and childcare costs (Section 33c EStG), the expenses to be recognized in terms of reason and amount without a reduction by the reasonable burden must be assumed; In the case of exceptional burdens in special cases (Sections 33a and 33b (6) EStG), on the other hand, it is not the expenses but the amounts that can be deducted due to these expenses that are decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The amounts referred to in Section 39a Paragraph 1 No. 4 and 5 EStG as well as pension expenses (Section 10 Paragraph 1 No. 2 EStG), even if they exceed the flat rate provision (Section 10c Paragraph 2 and 3 EStG), are not taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of applications from spouses who are both subject to unlimited income tax and who do not live permanently apart, the sum of the expenses and deductible amounts for both spouses must be taken as a basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The DM 1200 limit cannot be doubled for spouses (Section 39a (3) sentence 2 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If an exemption has already been entered on the income tax card for expenses that can be submitted to a limited extent, the DM 1200 limit does not have to be checked again if this exemption is changed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) The application limit of DM 1200 does not apply if it involves the entry of the amounts specified in Section 39a (1) No. 4 to 6 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(5) If the application limit of DM 1200 is exceeded or amounts within the meaning of paragraph 4 are to be taken into account, the tax office must determine the annual allowance and enter it in words on the income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the time from which the entry is valid must be noted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When calculating the annual tax allowance, income-related expenses are only to be taken into account insofar as they exceed the employee lump sum of DM 2,000 annually"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "216 DM \u00fcbersteigen, und au\u00dfergew\u00f6hnliche Belastungen (\u00a7\u00a7 33 33c EStG) nur einzubeziehen, soweit sie die zumutbare Belastung (&gt;Absatz 6) \u00fcbersteigen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Membership fees and donations to political parties are also to be taken into account if a tax reduction according to \u00a7 34g No. 1 EStG is possible, but not membership fees and donations to associations within the meaning of \u00a7 34g No. 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Exempt amount due to extraordinary burden (6) The reasonable burden is reduced from the expected annual wages of the employee and, if applicable, his / her spouse who is not permanently separated and who is subject to unlimited income tax, by the retirement benefit amount (\u00a7 24a Income Tax Act), the pension allowance (\u00a7 19 Paragraph 2 Income Tax Act) and to calculate the advertising expenses (\u00a7\u00a7 9 9a EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Tax-free income as well as all payments for which the wage tax is levied at a flat tax rate according to \u00a7\u00a7 40 to 40b EStG, and any other income of the employee and his spouse are excluded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When applying the table in Section 33 (3) EStG, the children of the taxpayer are those children for whom he receives a child allowance according to Section 32 (6) EStG or child benefit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of the reasonable burden, children must also be taken into account, for whom the employee has waived the entry of a child allowance number on the income tax card in accordance with Section 39 (3b) sentence 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(7) For employees with an income tax card on which tax class V is certified, the percentage for calculating the reasonable burden is based on the tax class and the number of child allowances entered on the spouse's income tax card; For employees with an income tax card on which tax class VI is certified, the percentage depends on the tax class and the number of child allowances that are entered on the income tax card for the first employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If different tax brackets or a different number of child allowances are to be taken into account in the calendar year, the more favorable tax bracket or the higher number of child allowances is to be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Conversion of the annual allowance (8) To convert the annual allowance into an allowance for monthly wage payments, the annual allowance must be divided by the number of calendar months in question"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The weekly allowance is to be set at 7/30 and the daily allowance at 1/30 of the monthly amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The resulting monthly amount is to be rounded up to the next full DM amount, the weekly amount to the next divisible by 10 pfennigs and the daily amount to the next divisible by 5 pfennigs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Change of registered allowances (9) If an annual allowance has already been entered on the income tax card and the employee applies for additional expenses or deductible amounts to be taken into account during the calendar year, the annual allowance will be redetermined taking into account the total expenses and deductible amounts of the calendar year and on the income tax card registered; for the calculation of the monthly allowance, weekly allowance, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the exemption is to be reduced by the part of the previous exemption that was to be taken into account according to the entries on the income tax card for the period until the new exemption became effective"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The remaining amount is to be evenly distributed over the period from the beginning of the calendar month following the application to the end of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 112 Tax exemption due to negative income In determining a tax exemption due to negative income, all income from agriculture and forestry, commercial operations, self-employed work, renting and leasing, other income and negative income from capital assets must be included, which the employee and his own are not permanently separated spouses with unlimited income tax liability are expected to achieve"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This means that the amount of negative income of the employee z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "reduced by the positive income of the spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Income from employment and positive income from capital assets are always disregarded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 113 Exemptions for spouses Business expenses (1) Business expenses are determined separately for each spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee lump sum of DM 2,000 must be deducted from the income-related expenses determined for the individual spouses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Special expenses (2) Special expenses within the meaning of Section 10 Paragraph 1 No. 1 1 a, 4 6 to 9 EStG and Section 10b EStG are to be determined uniformly for spouses who are both unrestrictedly subject to income tax and who do not live permanently apart"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A lump sum of DM 216 must be deducted from these special expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Extraordinary burdens (3) In the case of spouses who are both unrestrictedly liable to income tax and who do not live permanently apart, it is sufficient for the application of Sections 33, 33a, 33b (6) and Section 33c of the Income Tax Act (extraordinary burdens) that the requirements for the entry of a Exemption are fulfilled in the person of a spouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Lump sum for the disabled (4) For the granting of a lump sum for the disabled in accordance with Section 33b of the Income Tax Act, it is irrelevant for spouses who are both unrestrictedly liable to income tax and who do not live permanently apart, which of them fulfills the requirements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If both spouses meet the requirements for the granting of a flat-rate allowance for the disabled, the relevant flat-rate amount must be granted for each spouse; this also applies if only one spouse is an employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Distribution of the tax exemption (5) In the case of spouses who are both unrestrictedly liable to income tax and who do not live permanently apart, the tax exemption is to be divided equally between the spouses if an income tax card has been issued for each spouse; However, at the request of the spouses, a different division must be made (Section 39a (3) sentence 3 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An exception applies to an exemption due to increased advertising expenses; this may only be entered on the income tax card of the spouse who incurred the income-related expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In derogation from sentence 1, lump sums that are entered by the municipality in accordance with Section 39a (2) EStG may be entered as an exemption on the income tax card of the spouse who meets the requirements for the lump sum"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 113a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Freistellungsbescheinigung f\u00fcr ein geringf\u00fcgiges Besch\u00e4ftigungsverh\u00e4ltnis (1)Der Arbeitnehmer kann die Bescheinigung zur Freistellung des Arbeitslohns aus einem geringf\u00fcgigen Besch\u00e4ftigungsverh\u00e4ltnis (&gt;R 21d) nur nach amtlich vorgeschriebenem Vordruck bei seinem Wohnsitzfinanzamt beantragen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of employees subject to limited income tax, the employer's tax office is responsible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The application can be submitted up to the end of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee is employed in several marginal employment relationships, the tax office issues several exemption certificates on request if the sum of the wages from all marginal employment relationships does not exceed DM 630 per month"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise the applications must be rejected in their entirety"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The certificate of exemption is effective for the entire calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Exceeding the marginal earnings limit in the course of the calendar year does not mean that the tax exemption for the previous wage payment periods must be reversed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Hier erfolgt die Korrektur gegebenenfalls im Rahmen der Einkommensteuerveranlagung (&gt;\u00a7 46 Abs 2 a EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 114 Safekeeping of the income tax card (1) If the employee requests the temporary transfer of the income tax card, he has to demonstrate to the employer that he needs the income tax card to be presented to the tax office or the municipality"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) Before the end of the calendar year, the employer may only finally surrender the income tax card to the employee if the employment relationship has ended and he no longer pays the employee any wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Before it is handed over, the employer must write out the income tax certificate on the income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Kann die Lohnsteuerbescheinigung erst nach Beendigung des Dienstverh\u00e4ltnisses ausgeschrieben werden, so mu\u00df der Arbeitgeber die Lohnsteuerkarte bis zu diesem Zeitpunkt weiterhin aufbewahren (&gt;\u00a7 41b Abs 1 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) Notwithstanding paragraph 2, the income tax card may also be finally issued if an employee wants to exchange the income tax card kept by the employer for an income tax card previously presented to another employer (tax card change)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In this case, too, the employer must write out the income tax certificate on the income tax card before issuing the income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "After the tax card has been changed, the wage tax deduction is to be made according to the entries on the newly submitted wage tax card; Section 41c EStG does not apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 115 Current wages and other payments (1) Current wages are the wages that the employee receives on a regular basis, in particular: monthly salaries, weekly and daily wages, overtime payments, surcharges and allowances, pecuniary benefits from the permanent provision of company cars for private use, Back payments and advance payments, if they relate exclusively to wage payment periods that end in the calendar year of payment, wages for wage payment periods of the past calendar year, which accrue within the first three weeks of the following calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) Another reference is the wages that are not paid as current wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Other remuneration includes, in particular, one-time wage payments that are paid in addition to the current wages, in particular: thirteenth and fourteenth monthly salaries, one-time severance payments and compensation, gratuities and royalties that are not paid continuously, anniversary bonuses, vacation allowances that are not paid continuously, and Compensation to compensate for vacation not taken, allowances for inventions, Christmas allowances, back payments and advance payments, if the total amount or a partial amount of the additional payment or advance payment relates to wage payment periods that end in a year other than the year of payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Back payments are also made if wages for wage payment periods of the past calendar year are received later than three weeks after the end of this year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 116 pension allowance (1) If pension payments are paid as current wages, then at most the portion of the pension allowance resulting from Section 19 (2) of the EStG remains tax-free for the respective wage payment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This proportion is to be determined as follows: In the case of monthly wage payments, the annual amount is to be set at one twelfth, for weekly wages the monthly amount is to be set at 7/30 and for daily wages the monthly amount is to be set at 1/30"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The resulting monthly amount may be rounded up to the next full Deutsche Mark amount, the weekly amount to the next divisible by 10 pfennigs and the daily amount to the next divisible by 5 pfennigs, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Maximum monthly 500 DM, weekly 11670 DM, daily 1670 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The proportional maximum amount corresponding to the wage payment period may not be exceeded even if a lower amount than the maximum amount was taken into account in earlier wage payment periods in the same calendar year due to the amount of the pension payments at that time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Offsetting the maximum amount not used in one month against the amounts exceeding the maximum amount in another month is not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "S\u00e4tze 1 bis 5 gelten nicht in den F\u00e4llen des \u00a7 39b Abs 2 Satz 7 EStG (permanenter Lohnsteuer-Jahresausgleich; &gt;R 121 Abs 2)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The pension allowance is also to be taken into account when deducting income tax according to tax class VI"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) If pension remuneration is paid as other remuneration, Section 39b (3) EStG shall apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the pension allowance may only be deducted from the other payment insofar as it has not been used up when determining the relevant annual wage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If current pension payments are paid for the first time after pension payments have already been granted as other payments in the same calendar year, the employer may only take into account the tax-free maximum amount of 6,000 DM for current payments insofar as it has not affected the other payments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The pension allowance may not be deducted from wages from which the wage tax is levied according to \u00a7\u00a7 40 to 40b EStG with flat tax rates"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) The provisions of paragraphs 1 and 2 do not affect the tax treatment of pension payments in the case of annual wage tax adjustment by the employer or in the case of an assessment for income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 117 Retirement benefit amount (1) From the current wages, a maximum of the portion of the retirement benefit amount resulting from \u00a7 24a EStG and attributable to the respective wage payment period is to be deducted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This proportion is to be determined as follows: In the case of monthly wage payments, the annual amount is to be set at one twelfth, for weekly wages the monthly amount is to be set at 7/30 and for daily wages the monthly amount is to be set at 1/30"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The resulting monthly amount may be rounded up to the next full Deutsche Mark amount, the weekly amount to the next divisible by 10 pfennigs and the daily amount to the next divisible by 5 pfennigs, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Maximum monthly 310 DM, weekly 7240 DM, daily 1035 DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 116 para 1 sentences 4 to 7 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Bei beschr\u00e4nkt einkommensteuerpflichtigen Arbeitnehmern ist ein Altersentlastungsbetrag nicht abzuziehen (&gt;\u00a7 50 Abs 1 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) If wages are paid as other income, Section 39b (3) EStG shall apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the retirement benefit may only be deducted from the other benefits if it has not been used up when determining the relevant annual wage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If current wages are paid for the first time after a retirement benefit has already been taken into account for other payments in the same calendar year, the employer may only take the tax-free maximum amount of DM 3,720 into account for current payments insofar as it did not affect the other payments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The retirement benefit may not be deducted from wages, from which the wage tax is levied according to \u00a7\u00a7 40 to 40b EStG with flat tax rates"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) The provisions of paragraphs 1 and 2 do not affect the tax treatment of the old-age relief amount in the case of annual income tax adjustment by the employer or in the case of an assessment for income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 118 Einbehaltung der Lohnsteuer vom laufenden Arbeitslohn Allgemeines (1)Der Arbeitgeber hat die Lohnsteuer grunds\u00e4tzlich bei jeder Zahlung vom Arbeitslohn einzubehalten (&gt;\u00a7 38 Abs 3 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the means available to the employer are insufficient to pay the full agreed wage, he must calculate and withhold the wage tax from the lower amount actually paid out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wage tax determination is based on the characteristics entered on the wage tax card that apply to the day on which the wage payment period ends"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Wage payment period (2) The period for which the current wages are paid is the wage payment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Ist ein solcher Zeitraum nicht feststellbar, so tritt an seine Stelle die Summe der tats\u00e4chlichen Arbeitstage oder der tats\u00e4chlichen Arbeitswochen (&gt;\u00a7 39b Abs 5 Satz 4 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "As long as the employment relationship continues, those working days falling within the wage payment period for which the employee has not received any wages must also be counted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) If the wage is paid for a wage payment period for which the tax-free amount cannot be read from the income tax card, the employer must calculate the tax-free amount himself for this wage payment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "He has to start from the tax-free amount entered on the income tax card for the monthly wage payment period - i.e. rounded up"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Nachzahlungen, Vorauszahlungen (4)Stellen Nachzahlungen oder Vorauszahlungen laufenden Arbeitslohn dar (&gt;R 115 Abs 1), so ist die Nachzahlung oder Vorauszahlung f\u00fcr die Berechnung der Lohnsteuer den Lohnzahlungszeitr\u00e4umen zuzurechnen, f\u00fcr die sie geleistet werden"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, there are no concerns about treating these additional payments and advance payments, even if they do not exceed DM 300, as other payments under R 119, unless the employee requests taxation according to sentence 1; the flat rate according to \u00a7 40 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 1 EStG is not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Installment payments (5) If the employer pays the wages for the usual wage payment period only in an approximate amount (installment payment) and he carries out an exact wage accounting for a longer period, he only needs to withhold wage tax in the wage accounting according to Section 39b (5) EStG if the payroll accounting period does not exceed five weeks and the payroll accounting takes place within three weeks of the end of the payroll accounting period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The payroll is considered completed when the payment documents have left the employer's area; the timing of the payment to the employee is irrelevant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the payroll for the last payroll period of the past calendar year is only made in the following calendar year, but still within the 3-week period, then it concerns wages and withheld wage tax for this payroll period; The wages and the wage tax must therefore be recorded in the wage account and in the wage tax documents for the past calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, the withheld wage tax is required for registration and payment as wage tax for the calendar month or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "To be recorded in the calendar quarter in which the billing is actually carried out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 119 Withholding of income tax from other payments General (1) The income tax must always be withheld from other payments at the point in time at which it is received"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wage tax calculation is based on the characteristics entered on the wage tax card that apply to the day of the inflow"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Sonstige Bez\u00fcge bis 300 DM (2)Sonstige Bez\u00fcge, die neben laufendem Arbeitslohn gezahlt werden und innerhalb eines Lohnzahlungszeitraums insgesamt 300 DM nicht \u00fcbersteigen, sind unbeschadet des \u00a7 40 EStG stets als laufender Arbeitslohn zu behandeln (&gt;\u00a7 39b Abs 3 Satz 8 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "They are to be added to the current wages for the wage payment period in which they are paid; instead, they can also be added to the current wages with which they are paid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "F\u00fcr die Feststellung der 300-DM-Grenze sind nur die steuerpflichtigen sonstigen Bez\u00fcge und bei Pauschalierungen (&gt;\u00a7 40 Abs 1 EStG) nur der nicht pauschalierte Teil der sonstigen Bez\u00fcge ma\u00dfgebend"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Estimated annual wages (3) In order to determine the wage tax to be withheld from other payments, the probable annual wages of the calendar year in which the employee receives the other income is to be used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The current wages accrued for the wage payment periods that have already expired in the calendar year and the other remuneration already paid in this calendar year are to be added to the current wages that are expected to result for the remaining time of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Instead, the current wages that are expected to be paid for the remainder of the calendar year can be determined by converting the current wages that have accrued up to now, including the other remuneration treated as current wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The other remuneration paid earlier in the calendar year within the meaning of Section 39b, Paragraph 3, Clause 9 of the Income Tax Act (EStG) is only one fifth"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Other future payments that are expected to be paid by the end of the calendar year are not to be recorded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Other remuneration after the end of the employment relationship (4) If other emoluments are paid after the employee has left the employment relationship and the employee receives wages from another employer at the time of payment of the other remuneration, he has to pay the employer for the taxation of the other remuneration present a second or additional income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The other withdrawal is then to be taxed according to Section 39b (3) EStG using tax class VI"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee does not receive any wages from another employer at the time the other payment is made, the other payment must be taxed on the basis of a first income tax card in accordance with Section 39b (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "To determine the expected annual wage, the wage entered on the first tax card can then be converted into an annual wage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If further wages are not expected to flow in during the calendar year, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "due to old age or incapacity for work, the following applies: If the income tax certificate does not contain an entry on the first income tax card, the expected wage is assumed to be DM 0; in other cases, the wages certified on the first tax card can be used as the probable annual wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the income tax certificate does not contain an entry, but it is nevertheless to be assumed that the employee will receive wages in a more than insignificant amount in the future, the probable annual wages must be estimated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If it is not readily apparent from the wage account, its calculation must be shown in the wage account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Convergence of regular and reduced taxed other earnings (5) If another reference within the meaning of Section 39b (3) sentences 1 to 7 EStG coincides with another reference within the meaning of Section 39b (3) sentence 9 EStG, then the wage tax for the other is first Determine withdrawal within the meaning of Section 39b (3) sentences 1 to 7 EStG and then the wage tax for the other other withdrawals"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 120 Application of the general and special wage tax tables General (1) Which table is decisive depends in principle on whether the employee in the current employment relationship is subject to pension insurance or not"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The general income tax table must always be used for employees who are subject to pension insurance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The special wage tax table is only applicable to employees who are not subject to pension insurance if they belong to the group of people in Section 10c (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "General wage tax table (2) The general wage tax table is particularly applicable to employees who pay a contribution to the statutory pension insurance (employee's share)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Das gilt auch dann, wenn der Arbeitnehmeranteil vom Arbeitgeber \u00fcbernommen wird; Arbeitnehmer, die von der Versicherungspflicht in der gesetzlichen Rentenversicherung auf Antrag gem\u00e4\u00df \u00a7 6 Abs 1 Satz 1 Nr 1 SGB VI befreit worden sind und f\u00fcr die der Arbeitgeber gem\u00e4\u00df \u00a7 172 Abs 2 SGB VI die H\u00e4lfte des Beitrags zu einer berufsst\u00e4ndischen Versorgungseinrichtung tr\u00e4gt; Arbeitnehmer, die von der Versicherungspflicht in der gesetzlichen Rentenversicherung auf Antrag befreit worden sind und die deshalb steuerfreie Arbeitgeberzusch\u00fcsse f\u00fcr eine Lebensversicherung oder f\u00fcr die freiwillige Versicherung in der gesetzlichen Rentenversicherung erhalten k\u00f6nnen (&gt;\u00a7 3 Nr 62 Satz 2 EStG); Arbeitnehmer, die wegen geringf\u00fcgiger Besch\u00e4ftigung, ihres geringen Arbeitslohns oder als Praktikanten keinen Beitragsanteil zur gesetzlichen Rentenversicherung entrichten"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter here that the employer has to pay the entire social security contribution for employees who are subject to social security contributions and with low wages; Employees who only receive pension payments from their employer within the meaning of Section 19 Paragraph 2 Sentence 2 No. 2 EStG (company pensioners)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the sake of simplicity, this also applies to the deduction of income tax if the employer knows that the employee is receiving a retirement pension from the statutory pension insurance, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "because the old-age pension affects the amount of the company pension; In these cases, however, the employer may apply the special income tax table if the employee has applied for it or does not object; Foreign employees who have been exempted from statutory pension insurance with their wages from work for a domestic employer because they are insured in the social security system of their home country; Management board members of stock corporations and controlling shareholders-managing directors of a GmbH whose company pension plan consists only in the payment of employer contributions to a direct insurance taken out for the benefit of the employee or a pension fund"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Special wage tax table (3) The special wage tax table is particularly applicable to civil servants, judges, professional soldiers and temporary soldiers; According to Section 5, Paragraph 1, Clause 1, No. 2 and 3 of SGB VI, non-insurance employees, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Employees at social security agencies, clergymen of religious communities recognized as public bodies; Employees who only receive pension payments from their employer within the meaning of Section 19 Paragraph 2 Sentence 2 No. 1 EStG, e"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Civil servants' pensioners, recipients of widow's or orphan's allowance based on civil service law or corresponding statutory provisions; Employees who do not pay a contribution to the statutory pension scheme because they receive pension payments from a previous employer within the meaning of Section 19 Paragraph 2 Sentence 2 No. 1 EStG, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "civil servant pensioners employed in a private employment relationship; Employees who do not pay a contribution to the statutory pension insurance for a wage from an active activity because they already receive an old-age pension from the statutory pension insurance or because they have reached an age limit according to civil service or church law regulations or according to the regulations of a professional pension institution"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also applies to company retirees who are still employed if their wages are not subject to mandatory pension insurance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For company pension and wages, the wage tax deduction is to be made in total according to the special wage tax table, because there is a uniform employment relationship in terms of wage tax; Employees who have been exempted from statutory pension insurance at the request of the employer, e"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Teachers at non-public schools, for whom a pension is guaranteed according to civil service law or corresponding church law principles; Employees who are not subject to statutory pension insurance and who have been promised a company pension scheme in whole or in part without making their own contributions, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Vorstandsmitglieder von Aktiengesellschaften, beherrschende Gesellschafter-Gesch\u00e4ftsf\u00fchrer einer GmbH; auf Bez\u00fcge im Sinne des \u00a7 19 Abs 2 Satz 2 Nr 2 EStG, die nach dem Eintritt in den Ruhestand gezahlt werden, ist die allgemeine Lohnsteuertabelle anzuwenden (&gt;Absatz 2 Nr 5)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 121 Automatic wage accounting and wage tax determination according to the annual wage tax table General (1) Employers who perform automatic wage accounting may determine wage tax independently of the wage tax tables without special approval"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, it must be ensured that the automatically determined wage tax does not differ or only slightly differs from the wage tax that would have to be levied according to the relevant wage tax table"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Deviations up to the next higher or next lower tax amount in the relevant income tax table are to be regarded as insignificant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Permanent annual wage tax adjustment (2) Pursuant to Section 39b (2) sentence 7 EStG, the regional tax office may allow wage tax to be determined according to the expected annual wages (so-called permanent annual wage tax adjustment)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Voraussetzung f\u00fcr den permanenten Lohnsteuer-Jahresausgleich ist, da\u00df der Arbeitnehmer unbeschr\u00e4nkt einkommensteuerpflichtig ist, dem Arbeitgeber die Lohnsteuerkarte des Arbeitnehmers vorliegt, der Arbeitnehmer seit Beginn des Kalenderjahrs st\u00e4ndig in einem Dienstverh\u00e4ltnis gestanden hat, die zutreffende Jahreslohnsteuer (&gt;\u00a7 38a Abs 2 EStG) nicht unterschritten wird, der Arbeitnehmer kein Kurzarbeiter- oder Winterausfallgeld, keinen Zuschu\u00df zum Mutterschaftsgeld nach dem Mutterschutzgesetz oder \u00a7 4a Mutterschutzverordnung oder einer entsprechenden Landesregelung, keine Entsch\u00e4digung f\u00fcr Verdienstausfall nach dem Bundes-Seuchengesetz, keine Aufstockungsbetr\u00e4ge nach dem Altersteilzeitgesetz und keine Zuschl\u00e4ge auf Grund \u00a7 6 Abs 2 des Bundesbesoldungsgesetzes bezogen hat, im Lohnkonto kein Gro\u00dfbuchstabe U eingetragen ist, kein Wechsel von der allgemeinen zur besonderen Lohnsteuertabelle oder umgekehrt stattfindet und der Arbeitnehmer keinen Arbeitslohn bezogen hat, der nach einem Doppelbesteuerungsabkommen oder nach dem Auslandst\u00e4tigkeitserla\u00df von der deutschen Lohnsteuer freigestellt ist"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It does not depend on the employee's tax class"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the prerequisites specified in sentence 2 are met, the approval of the Oberfinanzdirektion is generally deemed to have been granted, unless it is revoked in individual cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The special wage tax determination based on the expected annual wage is limited to the current wage; Section 39b (3) EStG and R 119 are always to be applied to the determination of income tax for other payments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "To apply the special procedure, the current wages of the wage payment or wage accounting periods that have elapsed must be extrapolated to an annual amount after each wage payment period or - in the cases of Section 39b (5) EStG - wage accounting period, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "der laufende Arbeitslohn f\u00fcr die Monate Januar bis April x 3 Von dem Jahresbetrag sind der Versorgungs-Freibetrag (&gt;\u00a7 19 Abs 2 EStG) und der Altersentlastungsbetrag (&gt;\u00a7 24a EStG), wenn die Voraussetzungen f\u00fcr den Abzug jeweils erf\u00fcllt sind, sowie ein etwaiger Jahresfreibetrag nach Ma\u00dfgabe der Eintragungen auf der Lohnsteuerkarte abzuziehen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the remaining annual wage, the wage tax must be determined from the annual wage tax table or the instructions attached to the annual wage tax table"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax class entered on the income tax card is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Then the partial amount of the annual wage tax is to be determined, which is allotted to the expired wage payment or payroll accounting periods"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "From this tax amount, the wage tax that has already been levied on the current wages of the past wage payment or payroll accounting periods is to be deducted; the remaining amount is the wage tax that is to be levied for the last wage payment or payroll accounting period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In cases in which the relevant tax class has changed during the calendar year, instead of the wage tax that has been levied on the current wages of the past wage payment or payroll accounting periods, the wage tax must be deducted according to the last relevant tax class from the current wage to the penultimate one expired wage payment or payroll accounting period would have to be collected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In cases in which an exemption has not been entered on the wage tax card with effect from the beginning of the calendar year, deviations from the wage tax calculation according to Section 39b (2) EStG must be compensated if the employment relationship ends before the end of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Lohnsteuer-Jahresausgleich (3)Bei Arbeitnehmern, f\u00fcr die der Arbeitgeber nach \u00a7 42b Abs 1 EStG einen Lohnsteuer-Jahresausgleich durchf\u00fchren darf, darf der Arbeitgeber den Jahresausgleich mit der Ermittlung der Lohnsteuer f\u00fcr den letzten im Ausgleichsjahr endenden Lohnzahlungszeitraum zusammenfassen (&gt;\u00a7 42b Abs 3 Satz 1 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The annual wage tax is to be determined in accordance with Section 42b (2) sentences 1 to 3 EStG and compared with the wage tax that has been levied on the annual wage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the annual wage tax determined exceeds the wage tax levied, the difference is the wage tax that is to be withheld for the last wage payment period of the equalization year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the wage tax levied exceeds the annual wage tax determined, the difference is to be reimbursed to the employee; Section 42b (3) sentences 2 and 3 as well as (4) EStG apply here"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 122 Taxation of net wages (1) If the employer wants to pay the wage tax on wages himself, the deductible amounts taken over by him are part of the wages that must be added to the net wage for tax purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wage tax is calculated from the gross wage, which after deduction of the wage tax results in the net amount paid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer does not use a machine method for the net wage accounting, he has to determine the gross wages by scanning from the column of the wage tax table relevant for the tax class of the employee, which, minus the wage tax, results in the net amount paid out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wage tax calculated from the gross wages must be paid by the employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer pays the solidarity surcharge, the church tax and the employee's share of the total social security contribution in addition to the wage tax, these additional deductions must be included when determining the gross wages in addition to the wage tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) For reasons of simplification, before the tax calculation in accordance with paragraph 1, the portion of the pension allowance and the retirement allowance attributable to the wage payment period must be deducted from the net wage if the conditions for the deduction of these amounts are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In addition, a possible tax exemption is to be deducted from the net wage reduced in this way in accordance with the entries on the income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) If the tax deduction can no longer be determined from the wage tax table in question, the gross wages and the wage tax payable thereon are to be calculated using the instructions that are added to the official wage tax tables in accordance with Section 38c, Paragraph 1, last sentence and Paragraph 3, last sentence of the Income Tax Act are"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When calculating, the monthly (weekly, daily) net payments are to be multiplied by 12 (360/7 360)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of weekly or daily wage payments, up to an annual wage of DM 12004399, both the gross annual wage and the annual tax amount must be determined by scanning from the annual wage tax table"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The annual gross wage determined in this way and the annual tax amount determined are divided by 360/7 (weekly wage) or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "360 (daily wage) to share"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In all other cases, the annual net payments calculated in this way must be reduced by the amounts specified in the instructions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the income tax table, in analogous application of paragraph 1, both the annual gross wage and the annual tax amount must be determined according to the instructions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the taxable income determined in this way exceeds DM 120041 in tax classes I, II, IV, V and VI and DM 240084 in tax class III, the rate of 53 percent specified in the instructions corresponds to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "as a result of the net payment the rate of 11276 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, the annual gross wage is the annual net amount plus the unreduced amount of 11,276 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "this reference; the reduction in tax classes I, II and IV by 22843 DM, in tax class III by 45686 DM and in tax classes V and VI by 10757 DM is only to be made to determine the annual tax liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The calculated annual gross wage and the calculated annual tax amount are to be divided by 12 (360/7 360)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The resulting amounts then represent the gross salary that is relevant for taxation and the wage tax to be paid by the employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) Other remuneration that is paid net, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Net gratifications are taxable according to \u00a7 39b Abs 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 119 is to be applied with the following stipulation: When determining the relevant annual wage, the expected current annual wage and previous, net other remuneration must be included with the corresponding gross amounts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the application of the provision of Section 39b (3) sentence 8 EStG, it can be assumed without further examination that the amount of DM 300 specified in this provision will not be exceeded if the other withdrawal paid net 225 Does not exceed DM"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer also pays the solidarity surcharge for the other payment, the church tax and, if applicable, the employee's share of the total social security contribution, then, in addition to wage tax, these additional wage deductions must also be taken into account when determining the gross amount of the other payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The gross remuneration of the other remuneration is in any case the net amount plus the amounts actually paid for wage tax, solidarity surcharge, church tax and employee share of the total social security contribution"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The gross amount determined in this way is to be used as the basis for determining the relevant annual wage, even if other payments are made later in the same calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(5) In all cases of net wage payments, the gross wages determined in accordance with paragraphs 1 to 4 must be stated in the wage account and in the wage tax certificates"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 123 Application of double taxation agreements If the tax exemption under a double taxation agreement is independent of the application, the permanent establishment tax office must nevertheless issue a certificate of exemption upon application"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax office must indicate the period for which it applies in the certificate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This period must not exceed 3 years and should end at the end of a calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer must keep the certificate as a receipt for the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Der Verzicht auf den Lohnsteuerabzug schlie\u00dft die Ber\u00fccksichtigung des Progressionsvorbehalts (&gt;\u00a7 32 b EStG) bei einer Veranlagung des Arbeitnehmers zur Einkommensteuer nicht aus"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 124 Failure to present the income tax card (1) The determination of the income tax according to tax class VI due to non-presentation or non-return of the income tax card requires culpable behavior on the part of the employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "There is culpable behavior if the employee deliberately or negligently delays the presentation or return of the income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The employer can assume that the employee is not at fault if the income tax card for the current calendar year is presented by March 31 or the employee, after changing employers, receives a certificate within the meaning of Section 41b (1) sentence upon entering into the new employment relationship 6 EStG and the duration of the non-submission of the income tax card does not exceed 10 weeks or the employee presents within 6 weeks a) the income tax card after entering the employment relationship, subject to numbers 1 and 2, or b) an income tax card issued to him by the employer during the employment relationship returns"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the specified periods are exceeded, the employee can be assumed to be at fault, unless the employee can prove that he is not responsible for the delay"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The proof of receipt must be added to the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) As long as no fault can be assumed in accordance with paragraph 2, the employer shall, in the event that the income tax card is not presented at the beginning of the calendar year or when entering the employment relationship, the employee's family relationships known to him or proven by official documents, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Marital status and number of child allowances, in the event that a handed out tax card is not returned, the previously entered characteristics of the tax card should be used as a basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "After presenting or returning the income tax card, \u00a7 41c EStG must be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) If the wage tax for the month of January is still calculated according to the entries on the wage tax card for the previous calendar year, a tax-free annual amount entered on the wage tax card for the previous calendar year is 1/12 for monthly wages and 7 / for weekly wages. 36 0 and only to be taken into account with 1/36 0 for daily wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The monthly amount determined in this way is to be rounded up to the next full DM amount, the weekly amount to the next divisible by 10 pfennigs and the daily amount to the next divisible by 5 pfennigs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 124a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Implementation of wage tax deduction in the case of extended unlimited income tax liability - unoccupied - R 125 Implementation of wage tax deduction for employees subject to limited income tax General (1) Employees who are neither domiciled nor habitually resident in Germany are subject to limited income tax, unless they belong to the areas referred to in Section 1 (2) or 3 EStG belong to employees who are subject to unlimited income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite for the limited income tax liability is in accordance with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Section 49, Paragraph 1, No. 4 of the Income Tax Act stipulates that the non-self-employed work is or has been carried out or used in Germany or that wages are paid from domestic public coffers with regard to a current or previous employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The self-employed work is carried out in Germany if the employee is personally active within the scope of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is used in Germany if the employee transfers the result of an activity outside the scope of the Income Tax Act to his employer in Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Employment carried out or employed in Germany does not include self-employed work that is carried out on a German ship during its stay in a foreign territorial sea, in a foreign port, by employees who are neither domiciled nor habitually resident in Germany"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the wages are paid at the expense of a domestic employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Employer within the meaning of sentence 2 is the position in Germany, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "a permanent establishment or the domestic representative of a foreign employer who, irrespective of the formal contractual relationship with a possible foreign employer, actually exercises the essential rights and obligations of an employer; A domestic employer is also a domestic company in relation to employees who are employed by legally dependent permanent establishments, branches or branch offices abroad"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Exemption from the limited income tax liability (3) Income from the exploitation of non-self-employed work carried out outside the scope of the Income Tax Act is not included in the taxation if there is an agreement between the Federal Republic of Germany and the country of residence to avoid double taxation and income tax deduction is not made under R 123 may or in other cases, if it is proven or credible that a tax corresponding to German income tax is actually levied on this income in the state in which the activity was carried out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This proof is to be waived for employees who meet the requirements of the foreign activity decree"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) (dropped out) Artists, professional athletes, writers, journalists, picture reporters and artists (5) Remuneration of artists, professional athletes, writers, journalists and picture reporters who are subject to limited income tax are subject to wage tax deduction in accordance with Section 39d of the Income Tax Act, if they are part of the income from employment and are paid by a domestic employer within the meaning of Section 38 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 1 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Income tax is levied on your remuneration in accordance with \u00a7\u00a7 50a Paragraph 4 and 5 50d EStG if this is not paid by a domestic employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(6) For reasons of simplification, artists who are subject to limited income tax and whose non-self-employed work is carried out or exploited in Germany can be charged the applicable wage tax at a flat rate tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The flat tax rate is 125 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of wages, if the employee bears wage tax, 23333 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of wages if the employer pays wage tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Certification procedure (7) The certificate to be issued in accordance with Section 39d (1) EStG can also be applied for by the employer if the employer submits the application on behalf of the employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If an employee receives wages from several current or previous employment relationships at the same time, with which he is subject to limited tax liability, the tax office must note in the certificate for the second and each further employment relationship that tax class VI is to be applied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the certificate is not presented, the employer must deduct wage tax in accordance with Section 39c Paragraph 1 and 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 124 is to be applied accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(8) Pursuant to Section 39d (2) of the EStG, an allowance is to be distributed evenly over the expected duration of the employment relationship in the calendar year by dividing it into monthly allowances, if necessary into weekly and daily allowances"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If necessary, the periods of the same employment relationship that have already expired in the calendar year must also be included, unless the employee requests that the tax exemption be distributed over the remaining duration of the employment relationship"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Bei beschr\u00e4nkt einkommensteuerpflichtigen Arbeitnehmern, bei denen \u00a7 50 Abs 1 Satz 6 EStG anzuwenden ist, sind Werbungskosten und Sonderausgaben insoweit einzutragen, als sie die zeitanteiligen Pauschbetr\u00e4ge (&gt;\u00a7 50 Abs 1 Satz 7 EStG) \u00fcbersteigen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Arbeitnehmer mit Wohnsitz in der Schweiz (9)Bei Grenzg\u00e4ngern im Sinne von Artikel 15 a des deutsch-schweizerischen Doppelbesteuerungsabkommens in der Fassung des Protokolls vom 21 12 1992 (&gt;BStBl 1993 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "928), who are based in Switzerland and work for a domestic employer, may only pay income tax - including the solidarity surcharge - up to 45%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of taxable wages are charged if the necessary evidence is provided"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 126 Assessment of wage tax according to special flat tax rates (Section 40 (1) EStG) Larger number of cases (1) A larger number of cases can be assumed without further examination if at least 20 employees are included in the flat-rate taxation at the same time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If an application is made for a flat-rate wage tax for fewer than 20 employees, a larger number of cases can be accepted, even with fewer than 20 employees, taking into account the particular circumstances of the employer and the simplification aimed at with flat-rate taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Beachtung der 2000-DM-Grenze (2)Der Arbeitgeber hat anhand der Aufzeichnungen im Lohnkonto (&gt;\u00a7 4 Abs 2 Nr 8 Satz 1 LStDV) vor jedem Pauschalierungsantrag zu pr\u00fcfen, ob die Summe aus den im laufenden Kalenderjahr bereits gezahlten sonstigen Bez\u00fcgen, f\u00fcr die die Lohnsteuer mit einem besonderen Steuersatz erhoben worden ist, und aus dem sonstigen Bezug, der nunmehr an den einzelnen Arbeitnehmer gezahlt werden soll, den Jahresbetrag von 2000 DM \u00fcbersteigt"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the annual amount is exceeded as a result of this other payment, the taxation of this other payment is to be carried out for the employee concerned in accordance with Section 39b (3) EStG, as the amount of 2000 DM is exceeded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer has repeatedly failed to observe the lump sum limit, applications for wage tax lump sums in accordance with Section 40 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 2 EStG are not to be approved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Calculation of the average tax rate (3) The employer can meet the obligation to calculate the average tax rate by dividing the average amount of the flat-rate taxable earnings, the number of employees affected by tax class into the following three groups: a) Employees in the Tax classes I, II and IV, b) employees in tax class III and c) employees in tax classes V and VI as well as the total annual wages of the employees concerned, reduced by the deductible amounts according to Section 39b (3) sentence 2 EStG and the household allowance of tax class II"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the other remuneration is granted both to employees to whom the general income tax table applies and to employees to whom the special income tax table applies, sentence 1 is to be applied separately to both groups; This can be waived for reasons of simplification if the number of employees belonging to a group is of very minor importance in relation to the total number of employees in question"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, a representative selection of the employees concerned can be used as the basis for the investigations according to numbers 2 and 3"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "To determine a flat tax rate for the current calendar year, the conditions of the previous year can also be used as a basis for the determination according to number 3"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "From the amount determined in accordance with number 3, the employer must calculate the average annual wages of the employees recorded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For each of the groups referred to in number 2, the employer must then determine the tax amount to which the average amount of the lump-sum taxable earnings is subject, if it is added to the average annual wage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Tax class I is decisive for the group according to letter a, tax class III for the group according to letter b and tax class V for the group according to letter c; the average amount of the flat-rate taxable income is rounded up to the nearest DM amount divisible by 324"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "By multiplying the tax amounts by the number of employees included in the corresponding group and dividing the resulting sum of the tax amounts by the total number of employees and the rounded average amount of the flat-rate taxable earnings, the average tax burden on which the flat-rate taxable income is to be calculated Payments are subject"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax office has to calculate the flat tax rate according to this tax burden so that, taking into account the assumption of the flat income tax by the employer, not too little income tax is levied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The percentages of the average tax burden and the flat tax rate are to be set with one decimal place, the following decimal places are to be omitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 127 Assessment of wage tax according to a fixed flat rate tax (Section 40 (2) EStG) General (1) The wage tax can be calculated with a flat tax rate of 25%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "erhoben werden nach \u00a7 40 Abs 2 Satz 1 Nr 1 EStG f\u00fcr den Unterschiedsbetrag zwischen dem amtlichen Sachbezugswert und dem niedrigeren Entgelt, das der Arbeitnehmer f\u00fcr die Mahlzeiten entrichtet (&gt;R 31 Abs 7 Nr 1 bis 3); gegebenenfalls ist der nach R 31 Abs 7 Nr 5 ermittelte Durchschnittswert der Besteuerung zugrunde zu legen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Bei der Ausgabe von Essenmarken ist die Pauschalversteuerung nur zul\u00e4ssig, wenn die Mahlzeit mit dem ma\u00dfgebenden Sachbezugswert zu bewerten ist (&gt;R 31 Abs 7 Nr 4 Buchstabe a) oder der Verrechnungswert der Essenmarke nach R 31 Abs 7 Nr 4 Buchstabe b anzusetzen ist; nach \u00a7 40 Abs 2 Satz 1 Nr 2 EStG f\u00fcr Zuwendungen bei Betriebsveranstaltungen, wenn die Betriebsveranstaltung oder die Zuwendung nicht \u00fcblich ist (&gt;R 72); nach \u00a7 40 Abs 2 Satz 1 Nr 3 EStG f\u00fcr Erholungsbeihilfen, soweit sie nicht ausnahmsweise als steuerfreie Unterst\u00fctzungen anzusehen sind und wenn sie nicht die in \u00a7 40 Abs 2 Satz 1 Nr 3 EStG genannten Grenzen \u00fcbersteigen, und nach \u00a7 40 Abs 2 Satz 1 Nr 4 EStG f\u00fcr Verg\u00fctungen f\u00fcr Verpflegungsmehraufwendungen, die anl\u00e4\u00dflich einer Dienstreise, Fahr- oder Einsatzwechselt\u00e4tigkeit mit einer Abwesenheitsdauer von mindestens 8 Stunden gezahlt werden, soweit die Verg\u00fctungen die in \u00a7 4 Abs 5 Satz 1 Nr 5 EStG bezeichneten Pauschbetr\u00e4ge um nicht mehr als 100 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "exceed; Flat rate taxation does not apply to the reimbursement of additional meal expenses due to double housekeeping"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Verh\u00e4ltnis zur Pauschalierung nach \u00a7 40 Abs 1 Satz 1 Nr 1 (2)Die nach \u00a7 40 Abs 2 EStG pauschal besteuerten sonstigen Bez\u00fcge werden nicht auf die Pauschalierungsgrenze von 2000 DM (&gt;R 126 Abs 2) angerechnet"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Recovery allowances (3) When determining whether the recovery allowances granted in the calendar year together with previously granted recovery allowances exceed the amounts specified in Section 40 Paragraph 2 Clause 1 No. 3 EStG, the amount of the allowances must be assumed in each individual case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The maximum annual amounts for the employee, his spouse and his children must be considered separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The recovery allowance must be intended and used for the recovery of these people"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the recovery aid exceeds the relevant annual maximum amount in individual cases, either Section 39b (3) EStG with the exception of sentence 9 or Section 40 (1) sentence 1 No. 1 EStG shall apply to them"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Travel expenses (4) The flat tax with a flat tax rate of 25 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "According to \u00a7 40 Paragraph 2 Clause 1 No. 4 EStG is limited to a remuneration amount up to the sum of the meals per diem due to the external activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Flat-rate taxation with a special flat-rate tax rate in accordance with Section 40 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 1 EStG can also be considered for the remuneration amount exceeding this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Zur Ermittlung des steuerfreien Verg\u00fctungsbetrags d\u00fcrfen die einzelnen Aufwendungsarten zusammengefa\u00dft werden (&gt;R 16 Satz 2)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, there are also no concerns about treating the amount that exceeds the tax-free remuneration amount uniformly as remuneration for additional meal expenses, which within the limits of \u00a7 40 Paragraph 2 Sentence 1 No. 4 EStG with 25 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "can be taxed at a flat rate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Einem Arbeitnehmer mit Einsatzwechselt\u00e4tigkeit oder Fahrt\u00e4tigkeit, der zudem einen beruflich veranla\u00dften doppelten Haushalt f\u00fchrt, kann in den ersten drei Monaten nur eine (die h\u00f6chste) Verpflegungspauschale steuerfrei gezahlt werden (&gt;R 39 Abs 2)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If in this case, because of the double housekeeping z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a meal allowance of 46 DM is paid tax-free, an additional payment can only be made up to the amount of the meal allowance of z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "10 or 20 DM can be taxed at a flat rate according to \u00a7 40 Paragraph 2 Clause 1 No. 4 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Trips between home and work place"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "erhoben werden f\u00fcr den nach R 31 Abs 9 ermittelten Wert der unentgeltlichen oder teilentgeltlichen \u00dcberlassung eines Kraftfahrzeugs zu Fahrten zwischen Wohnung und Arbeitsst\u00e4tte a)bei behinderten Arbeitnehmern im Sinne des \u00a7 9 Abs 2 EStG in vollem Umfang, b)bei allen anderen Arbeitnehmern bis zu einem Teilbetrag des privaten Nutzungswerts von 070 DM je Entfernungskilometer f\u00fcr jeden Arbeitstag, an dem das Kraftfahrzeug zu Fahrten zwischen Wohnung und Arbeitsst\u00e4tte benutzt wird; aus Vereinfachungsgr\u00fcnden kann unterstellt werden, da\u00df das Kraftfahrzeug an 15 Arbeitstagen monatlich zu Fahrten zwischen Wohnung und Arbeitsst\u00e4tte benutzt wird, f\u00fcr den Ersatz von Aufwendungen des Arbeitnehmers f\u00fcr Fahrten zwischen Wohnung und Arbeitsst\u00e4tte (Fahrtkostenzusch\u00fcsse) bis zur H\u00f6he des Betrags, der nach R 42 Abs 4 bis 7 als Werbungskosten angesetzt werden k\u00f6nnte, soweit er nicht nach \u00a7 3 Nr 34 EStG (&gt;R 21b) steuerfrei ist"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Als Fahrten zwischen Wohnung und Arbeitsst\u00e4tte k\u00f6nnen bei einer Einsatzwechselt\u00e4tigkeit auch die Fahrten zwischen Wohnung und Einsatzstelle ber\u00fccksichtigt werden, soweit die Fahrtkosten nicht als Reisekosten angesetzt werden k\u00f6nnen (&gt;R 38 Abs 3)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The flat-rate taxed payments reduce the income-related expenses that are deductible under R 42"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 128 Flat rate wage tax for part-time employees General (1) The flat-rate wage tax according to Section 40a EStG is permissible for both unlimited and part-time employees subject to limited income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When examining the prerequisites for the flat rate, the characteristics that result for the individual employment relationship must be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "There is no need to check whether the part-time employee is still employed by another employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer may catch up on the flat-rate taxation as long as there is no wage tax certificate, a wage tax registration can still be corrected and the statute of limitations has not yet expired"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee cannot deduct expenses associated with the flat-rate taxed wages as income-related expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Unforeseeable point in time (2) Section 40a, Paragraph 1, Clause 2, No. 2 of the Income Tax Act presupposes that the employment relationship serves to replace a lost employee or to meet the acute need for additional workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employment of temporary workers, the time of which is certain in advance, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "at folk festivals or fairs, cannot be viewed as unpredictable and immediately necessary; a different assessment is z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "possible with regard to temporary workers whose recruitment has become necessary contrary to the foreseeable need for workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Bemessungsgrundlage f\u00fcr die pauschale Lohnsteuer (3)Zur Bemessungsgrundlage der pauschalen Lohnsteuer geh\u00f6ren alle Einnahmen, die dem Arbeitnehmer aus der Teilzeitbesch\u00e4ftigung zuflie\u00dfen (&gt;\u00a7 2 LStDV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also includes direct insurance contributions from the employer, provided they are not taxed in accordance with Section 40b of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Tax-free income is not taken into account for wage tax collection"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wages may not be reduced by the old-age relief amount (\u00a7 24a EStG) to determine the flat-rate wage tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Flat-rate limits (4) When examining the flat-rate limits of Section 40a EStG, Paragraph 3 Sentences 1 3 to 4 shall apply accordingly; Flat-rate taxed payments in accordance with Section 40, Paragraph 2, Sentence 2 of the Income Tax Act are excluded from the assessment of the flat-rate limits; direct insurance contributions from the employer must always be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If other remuneration is only paid after the end of the calendar year in which the corresponding work was performed, they are only to be taken into account in the flat-rate limits of the wage payment or payroll accounting period in which they were paid"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the wage limit has been exceeded in a wage payment or wage accounting period with the lump sum payment pursuant to Section 40a (2) EStG, the lump sum method may not be used for this period; the admissibility of the flat rate procedure for other periods is not affected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Period of employment (5) Period of employment also includes periods in which wages are paid due to vacation, illness or public holidays"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Temporary workers in agriculture and forestry (6) A flat rate of wage tax according to \u00a7 40a Abs 3 EStG for temporary workers in agriculture and forestry is only permitted if the temporary workers in a company within the meaning of \u00a7 13 Abs 1 No. 1 to 4 EStG get busy"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For temporary workers who work in a commercial enterprise within the meaning of Section 15 of the Income Tax Act, the flat rate according to Section 40a, Paragraph 3 of the Income Tax Act does not apply, even if they are employed with typical agricultural and forestry work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the temporary workers are employed in an agricultural and forestry company within the meaning of Section 13 (1) No. 1 to 4 EStG, they do not perform any typical agricultural or forestry activity, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Flower binders, salespeople, or are they alternately entrusted with typical agricultural, forestry and other work, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "also active in the business or subsidiary of the same employer, a flat rate of wage tax according to \u00a7 40a Abs 3 EStG is not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Record-keeping obligations (7) The fulfillment of the record-keeping obligations serves as proof of the requirements for the flat-rate wage tax according to \u00a7 40a EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of other payments, their distribution over the period of employment must therefore also be evident from the records"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 129 Pauschalierung der Lohnsteuer bei bestimmten Zukunftssicherungsleistungen Direktversicherung (1)Eine Direktversicherung ist eine Lebensversicherung auf das Leben des Arbeitnehmers, die durch den Arbeitgeber bei einem inl\u00e4ndischen oder ausl\u00e4ndischen Versicherungsunternehmen abgeschlossen worden ist und bei der der Arbeitnehmer oder seine Hinterbliebenen hinsichtlich der Versorgungsleistungen des Versicherers ganz oder teilweise bezugsberechtigt sind (&gt;\u00a7 1 Abs 2 Satz 1 des Gesetzes zur Verbesserung der betrieblichen Altersversorgung)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to life insurance for the employee's life, which was taken over by the employer after the employee had taken out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The conclusion of a life insurance by a group company affiliated with the employer does not exclude the recognition as direct insurance if the claim to the insurance benefits is caused by the employment relationship and the employer bears the burden of contributions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Retirement, disability or survivors' benefits can be considered as pension benefits"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) It is basically irrelevant whether it is capital insurance including risk insurance, annuity insurance or unit-linked life insurance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Endowment life insurances with increasing death benefit are to be recognized as direct insurance if at the beginning of the insurance a death benefit of at least 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the lump-sum payment in the event of survival was agreed and the insurance contract was concluded before August 1, 1994"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of endowment life insurance taken out after 31 7 1994, the prerequisite for recognition is that the death benefit over the entire insurance period is at least 50%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the agreed capital payment for survival"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A capital life insurance taken out after December 31, 1996 is to be recognized as direct insurance if the death benefit is at least 60% for the entire term of the insurance contract"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the sum of the contributions that are to be paid according to the insurance contract for the entire duration of the contract"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Endowment insurance with a contract duration of less than 5 years cannot be recognized unless it has been taken out as part of a group insurance policy based on the principle of equal treatment under labor law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to annuity insurances with a lump-sum option, in which the option can take effect within 5 years after the conclusion of the contract, and to premium increases for existing end-of-life insurance policies with a remaining term of less than 5 years; For reasons of equity, increases in contributions can be recognized if they were made in connection with the increase in the flat rate limits by the Tax Reform Act 1990 or the Annual Tax Act 1996"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Accident insurance is not life insurance, even if a benefit is provided in the event of an accident resulting in death"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "On the other hand, supplementary accident insurance and supplementary occupational disability insurance that is taken out in connection with life insurance, as well as independent occupational disability insurance and accident insurance with a premium refund, for which the employee is entitled to the premium refund, belong to the direct insurance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Die Bezugsberechtigung des Arbeitnehmers oder seiner Hinterbliebenen mu\u00df vom Versicherungsnehmer (Arbeitgeber) der Versicherungsgesellschaft gegen\u00fcber erkl\u00e4rt werden (&gt;\u00a7 166 VVG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The subscription entitlement can be revocable or irrevocable; In the case of revocable subscription entitlement, the conditions of a revocation are irrelevant for tax purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is also irrelevant whether the employee's entitlement is already vested under labor law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Reinsurance (3) For the distinction between direct insurance and reinsurance that is taken out by the employer and which only serves to provide the employer with the means to provide a pension promised to the employee, the agreements made between the employer and the employee (internal relationship ) decisive and not the agreements between employer and insurance company (external relationship)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For this reason, a reinsurance policy can only be recognized for tax purposes if all of the following requirements are met: The employer has promised the employee a pension from his own resources, e"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "a company pension"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "To guarantee the funds for this supply, the employer has taken out insurance, to which the employee does not make any contributions within the meaning of Section 2 (2) No. 2 Sentence 2 LStDV"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Only the employer, but not the employee, has claims against the insurance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, the pledge of the reinsurance claims to the employee is not prejudicial, because the pledge does not currently acquire any rights that would allow him access to the insurance and the assets accumulated therein"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to a suspensive assignment of the reinsurance claim, as the assignment only becomes legally effective when the condition occurs (Section 158 (1) BGB), and for the assignment of the reinsurance claim on account of payment in the event of liquidation or enforcement of the insurance claims by third parties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a claim from a reinsurance policy is transferred to the employee free of charge or an existing reinsurance policy is converted into a direct insurance policy, the employee will receive payment at the time of the transfer or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Umwandlung ein lohnsteuerpflichtiger geldwerter Vorteil zu, der dem gesch\u00e4ftsplanm\u00e4\u00dfigen Deckungskapital oder dem Zeitwert (&gt;\u00a7 176 VVG) der Versicherung entspricht"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Entsprechendes gilt, wenn eine aufschiebend bedingte Abtretung rechtswirksam wird (&gt;Nummer 3)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Pension fund (4) Pension funds are both legally capable pension institutions within the meaning of Section 1 Paragraph 3 Clause 1 of the Act for the Improvement of Company Retirement Provisions and non-legal supplementary pension institutions of the public service within the meaning of Section 18 of the Law for the Improvement of Company Retirement Provisions that provide beneficiaries , in particular employees and their survivors, have a legal right to their pension benefits"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter whether the fund has its seat or its management within or outside the scope of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Paragraph 1 sentence 4 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Salary conversion (5) For the wage tax flat rate according to \u00a7 40b EStG it does not matter whether the contributions or allowances are made in addition to the wages owed anyway or based on agreements with the employees instead of the cash wages owed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the contributions or benefits are financed by a reduction in cash wages, only the reduced cash wages are subject to wage tax deduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Prerequisites for the lump sum (6) In the case of contributions for direct insurance, the wage tax lump sum presupposes that the insurance is not taken out for the event of the employee being older than 60 years of age, the assignment or loan of an irrevocable subscription right granted to the employee in the insurance contract is excluded and an early one is excluded Termination of the insurance contract by the employee has been excluded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The insurance contract must not contain any provision according to which the insurance benefit in the event of survival could become due before the age of 59"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Does the insurance contract z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the possibility of using profit shares to shorten the insurance period, the shortening of the term must be limited to the age of 59"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The exclusion of premature termination of the insurance contract is to be assumed if the following agreement has been made in the insurance contract between the employer as the policyholder and the insurer: \"It is irrevocably agreed that a transfer of the policyholder property and an assignment of Rights under this contract to the insured employee up to the point in time at which the insured employee turns 59 are excluded insofar as the contributions have been paid by the policyholder (employer)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "\"It is not a prerequisite that the future security services are provided in a larger number of cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Basis for assessment of the flat-rate wage tax (7) The flat-rate wage tax is based on the actual services that the employer provides for the individual employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the tariff contribution is offset against surplus shares, the reduced contribution therefore represents the assessment basis for the flat-rate wage tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Wird f\u00fcr mehrere Arbeitnehmer gemeinsam eine pauschale Leistung erbracht, bei der der Teil, der auf den einzelnen Arbeitnehmer entf\u00e4llt, nicht festgestellt werden kann, so ist dem einzelnen Arbeitnehmer der Teil der Leistung zuzurechnen, der sich bei einer Aufteilung der Leistung nach der Zahl der beg\u00fcnstigten Arbeitnehmer ergibt (&gt;\u00a7 2 Abs 2 Nr 3 Satz 3 LStDV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer provides services for the collectively agreed supplementary pension for the employees with a percentage of the gross wages of the company, then the employer's contribution is the assessment basis for the flat-rate wage tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "F\u00fcr die Feststellung der Pauschalierungsgrenze (&gt;Absatz 8) bei zus\u00e4tzlichen pauschalbesteuerungsf\u00e4higen Leistungen f\u00fcr einzelne Arbeitnehmer ist die Arbeitgeberleistung auf die Zahl der durch die tarifvertragliche Zusatzversorgung beg\u00fcnstigten Arbeitnehmer aufzuteilen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Sonderzahlungen an Pensionskassen (&gt;Absatz 4), die der Arbeitgeber zur Finanzierung der Versorgungsleistungen zus\u00e4tzlich leistet, sind den Arbeitnehmern zuzurechnen, die zu dem Arbeitgeber in einem gegenw\u00e4rtigen Dienstverh\u00e4ltnis stehen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Flat-rate limit (8) The flat-rate limit of DM 3408 can also be fully used in cases in which it is certain that the employee has already received flat-rate future security benefits from a previous employment relationship in the same calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "To the extent that services that are subject to lump-sum taxation exceed the limit of DM 3408, they must be subject to normal wage tax deduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Average calculation (9) If several employees are jointly insured in a direct insurance contract or in a pension fund, an average calculation must be made to determine the flat rate limit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Apart from group insurance, a joint direct insurance contract also exists if both the insured persons and the insured risks are specified in a framework contract with one or more insurers and the details are regulated in additional agreements"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A framework agreement that z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "only regulates the collection of premiums and the premium accounting, does not constitute a joint direct insurance contract"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the rest, the procedure is as follows: If employees are insured in direct insurance or in the pension fund for whom flat-rate taxable benefits totaling more than DM 4,200 annually are provided, the benefits for these employees are excluded from the average calculation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This applies e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "even if there are several direct insurance contracts and the contribution shares for the individual employee exceed DM 4,200 in total"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The collection of wage tax on these services is based on paragraph 8, sentence 2. The services for the other employees are to be added together and divided by the number of employees for whom they were provided"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of a group-wide joint direct insurance contract, the average amount is to be determined by dividing the employer's contribution payments over the number of his beneficiaries; it is not permissible to determine the average amount by dividing the group contribution to all employees of the group"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "a) If the average amount determined in this way does not exceed DM 3408, this is to be used as a basis for flat-rate taxation for every employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If additional services that can be taxed at a flat rate are provided for the individual employee, then only DM 3408 in total may be taxed at a flat rate; Otherwise, paragraph 8, sentence 2 applies. b) If the average amount exceeds DM 3408, it cannot be used as a basis for lump-sum taxation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Flat-rate taxation is based on the actual benefits provided that they do not exceed DM 3408 for the individual employee; Otherwise, paragraph 8 sentence 2 applies.If an employee is insured a) in several direct insurance contracts jointly with other employees, b) in several pension funds or c) in direct insurance contracts jointly with other employees and in pension funds, the average amount from the sum of the contributions for several direct insurances, from the sum of the contributions to several pension funds or from the sum of the contributions to direct insurance and the contributions to pension funds"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In diese gemeinsame Durchschnittsbildung d\u00fcrfen jedoch solche Vertr\u00e4ge nicht einbezogen werden, bei denen wegen der 4200-DM-Grenze (&gt;Nummer 1) nur noch ein Arbeitnehmer \u00fcbrig bleibt; in diesen F\u00e4llen liegt eine gemeinsame Versicherung, die in die Durchschnittsberechnung einzubeziehen ist, nicht vor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(10) If the lump-sum taxable services are not provided in an annual amount, the following applies: The inclusion of the services allotted to the individual employee in the average calculation according to Section 40b (2) sentence 2 EStG does not apply from the point in time at which the Benefits for this employee are expected to exceed DM 4,200 in total in the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wage tax flat rate based on the average amount ceases to apply from the point in time at which it emerges that the average amount is expected to exceed DM 3408 in the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The lump-sum limit of DM 3408 must be reduced to the extent that it has already been exhausted in the case of lump-sum taxation of previous services in the same calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the services are provided on an ongoing basis, the flat-rate limit may be taken into account with the proportion attributable to the respective wage payment period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Duplication regulation (11) Duplication of the flat rate limit according to Section 40b (2) sentence 3 EStG is related to the termination of the employment relationship; Such a connection is to be presumed in particular if the direct insurance premium is paid within 3 months prior to the termination date"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Die Vervielf\u00e4ltigungsregelung gilt auch bei der Umwandlung von Arbeitslohn (&gt;Absatz 5), nach Aufl\u00f6sung des Dienstverh\u00e4ltnisses kann sie ohne zeitliche Beschr\u00e4nkung angewendet werden, wenn sie sp\u00e4testens bis zum Zeitpunkt der Aufl\u00f6sung des Dienstverh\u00e4ltnisses vereinbart wird"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The reasons for which the employment relationship is terminated are irrelevant for the duplication of the flat-rate limit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The reproduction rule can therefore also be applied in cases in which an employee leaves the service due to reaching the age limit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The contributions and benefits actually paid for the individual employee in the calendar year in which the employment relationship is terminated and in the six preceding calendar years, which were taxed at a flat rate according to Section 40b (1) of the Income Tax Act, are to be offset against the duplicated flat rate limit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This also includes the personal contributions exceeding DM 3408 if they have been included in the assessment basis for the flat-rate tax in accordance with Section 40b (2) sentence 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If a personal contribution cannot be determined for lump-sum allocations, the average amount from the lump-sum allocation must be assumed as the actual contribution for the individual employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Group accident insurance (12) The flat rate wage tax according to Section 40b (3) EStG is not permitted if the taxable average contribution - excluding insurance tax - exceeds DM 120 per year; in this case the taxable average contribution is subject to the normal wage tax deduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of group-wide group accident insurance, the average premium is to be determined, which results from the distribution of the employer's contribution payments to the number of his beneficiary employees; it is not permissible to determine the average contribution by dividing the group contribution to all employees of the group"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Paragraph 9 sentences 2 and 3 apply accordingly for the definition of joint accident insurance"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Repayment of flat-rate taxable benefits (13) Repayments of wages to the employer (negative income for the employee) are to be assumed, provided that profit shares are accumulated in favor of the employer at the insurance company, offset against due employer contributions during the insurance period or paid out to the employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as interest is subject to capital gains tax pursuant to Section 43 (1) No. 4 EStG, capital gains tax is part of the repayment of wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The point in time at which wages are repaid is determined by the point in time at which the profit shares are credited, offset or paid out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, wage repayments can also be taken into account as negative income if the future security allowance has been deducted from contributions for calendar years prior to 1990"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(14) A wage repayment (negative income) is also to be assumed if the employee benefits from a direct insurance policy (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "in the event of premature termination of the employment relationship) wholly or partially without compensation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The point in time of this wage repayment is determined by the point in time at which the declarations of intent justifying the loss of subscription rights (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Termination or revocation) have become effective"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The lost subscription right is to be set against the corresponding actuarial reserve in accordance with the business plan; Paragraph 13 sentence 4 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Payments by the employee to reacquire the lost subscription right are to be assigned to the property sphere; they do not represent a repayment of wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(15) If, according to paragraphs 13 and 14, reimbursements of wages from lump-sum taxed contributions are to be accepted, they reduce the lump-sum taxable contributions of the employer that are incurred at the same time (in the same calendar year)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the wage repayments exceed the flat-rate taxable contributions of a calendar year, the employer can assert a wage tax reimbursement claim, provided that no unreasonable tax advantages are achieved as a result"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Unreasonable tax advantages exist, in particular, if, on the basis of the contract design, it can be expected that the profit shares paid to the employer or used to reduce contributions are overall higher than the insurance contributions to be raised during the expected term"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wage tax refund claim is 20 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of the difference"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee cannot claim negative income from flat-rate taxed contributions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(16) If wage repayments according to paragraphs 13 and 14 result from contributions that are partly individually and partly flat-rate taxed, the amount must be divided accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For the sake of simplicity, the ratio that results from the contributions in the previous five calendar years can be used as a basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The actual contributions are decisive; Section 40b (2) sentence 2 EStG does not apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wage tax consideration of the wage payment attributable to the employee is based on the following principles: If the employment relationship with the employer who paid the insurance contributions still exists at the time of the wage repayment, the employer can offset the wage repayment with the wages for the calendar year in which the repayment was made and the reduced amount Subject wages to wage tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as the employer does not or cannot make use of the above option, the employee can have the reimbursement of wages such as business expenses - without offsetting the employee lump sum - entered as an exemption on his income tax card or claim it when assessing income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee achieves a loss in his income from employment through the repayment of wages, he can claim the loss deduction under the conditions of \u00a7 10d EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(17) Paragraphs 13 to 16 apply mutatis mutandis to contributions to pension funds"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 130 Facilitation of recording, recording of the religious community (1) The remuneration taxed at a flat rate according to \u00a7\u00a7 40 Paragraph 1 Clause 1 No. 1 and 40b EStG and the flat-rate wage tax due thereon must be recorded in the wages account to be kept for each employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Soweit die Lohnsteuerpauschalierung nach \u00a7 40b EStG auf der Grundlage des Durchschnittsbetrags durchgef\u00fchrt wird (&gt;\u00a7 40b Abs 2 Satz 2 EStG), ist dieser aufzuzeichnen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) According to Section 4 (3) sentence 1 LStDV, the regional finance directorates can allow exceptions to the recording in the payroll account if the possibility of a review is ensured in another way"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the cases mentioned, the possibility of verification is only given if the payment of the remuneration and the way it was recorded is noted in the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3)Das Finanzamt hat Antr\u00e4gen auf Befreiung von der Aufzeichnungspflicht nach \u00a7 4 Abs 3 Satz 2 LStDV im allgemeinen zu entsprechen, wenn es im Hinblick auf die betrieblichen Verh\u00e4ltnisse nach der Lebenserfahrung so gut wie ausgeschlossen ist, da\u00df der Freibetrag von 2400 DM (&gt;\u00a7 8 Abs 3 EStG) oder die Freigrenze von 50 DM (&gt;\u00a7 8 Abs 2 Satz 9 EStG) im Einzelfall \u00fcberschritten wird"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Additional monitoring measures by the employer are not required in these cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) The employer must record the religious community entered on the employee's income tax card or a corresponding certificate in the payroll account (Section 4 (1) No. 1 LStDV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer does not levy church tax on flat-rate taxed payments (Sections 40 to 40b EStG) because the employee does not belong to a religious community for which the church tax is levied by the tax authorities, he must provide the relevant documentation as evidence of the requirements pursuant to Section 4 (2) No. 8 sentences 3 and 4 LStDV to take documents to be kept (Section 4 (2) No. 8 sentence 5 LStDV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A note from the employer stating that the employee has proven his non-membership of a religious community that levies church tax by submitting his income tax card is valid as evidence; the note must contain the issuing municipal authority"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the cases of \u00a7 40a EStG, the employer can also use a declaration of religious affiliation based on the official model as evidence"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 131 Record of the capital letters AND. The entitlement to wages has essentially ceased to exist if z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "only capital-forming benefits or sick pay subsidies are paid, or if during unpaid absences (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Parental leave) an employment with reduced working hours is taken up"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The capital letter U must be entered once in the payroll account for each interruption"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If short-time work allowance, winter loss allowance, the supplement to maternity allowance under the Maternity Protection Act, the allowance under Section 4a of the Maternity Protection Ordinance or a corresponding state regulation, compensation for loss of earnings under the Federal Disease Act or top-up amounts under the Part-Time Employment Act are paid, no capital letter U is to be entered in the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 132 Permanent establishment The permanent establishment for wage tax purposes is the establishment or part of the employer's establishment located in Germany at which the total wages are determined, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "where the individual wage components or, in the case of automatic payroll accounting, the input values \u200b\u200bare summarized for the wages that are decisive for the implementation of the wage tax deduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It does not matter where individual wage components are determined, the wage tax is calculated and the documents relevant for the wage tax deduction are stored"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "An independent service company that works for an employer cannot be regarded as a permanent establishment of this employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Bei einer Arbeitnehmer\u00fcberlassung (&gt;R 146) kann nach \u00a7 41 Abs 2 Satz 2 EStG eine abweichende lohnsteuerliche Betriebsst\u00e4tte in Betracht kommen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 133 Wage tax registration (1) The employer must submit the wage tax registration regardless of the payment of wage tax, even if he has not withheld wage tax during the registration period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the employer must declare in the wage tax registration that he did not have to withhold any wage tax during the registration period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2)F\u00fcr jede Betriebsst\u00e4tte (&gt;\u00a7 41 Abs 2 EStG) und f\u00fcr jeden Lohnsteuer-Anmeldungszeitraum ist eine einheitliche Lohnsteuer-Anmeldung einzureichen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Submitting several wage tax registrations for the same business premises and the same wage tax registration period, for example separately according to the different areas of payroll, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Commercial employees, salaried employees, lump sums according to \u00a7\u00a7 40 to 40b EStG, are not permitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3)Der f\u00fcr den Lohnsteuer-Anmeldungszeitraum ma\u00dfgebende Betrag der abzuf\u00fchrenden Lohnsteuer (&gt;\u00a7 41a Abs 2 EStG) ist die Summe der einbehaltenen und \u00fcbernommenen Lohnsteuer ohne K\u00fcrzung um die der Lohnsteuer entnommenen Bergmannspr\u00e4mien (&gt;\u00a7 3 Abs 1 BergPG) und das ihr entnommene Kindergeld (&gt;\u00a7 72 Abs 8 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) The business premises tax office has to monitor the timely receipt of the income tax registration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the wage tax registration is not received in time, it can set a late surcharge according to \u00a7 152 AO or, if necessary, enforce the submission of the wage tax registration with compulsory means according to \u00a7\u00a7 328 to 335 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Das Finanzamt kann bei Nichtabgabe der Lohnsteuer-Anmeldung die Lohnsteuer im Sch\u00e4tzungswege ermitteln und den Arbeitgeber durch Steuerbescheid in Anspruch nehmen (&gt;\u00a7\u00a7 162 167 Abs 1 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Flat-rate wage tax can be determined using an estimate and set in a tax assessment if the employer agrees with the flat-rate method"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 134 Abf\u00fchrung der Lohnsteuer Der Arbeitgeber hat die Lohnsteuer in einem Betrag an die Kasse des Betriebsst\u00e4ttenfinanzamts (&gt;\u00a7 41 Abs 2 EStG) oder an eine von der obersten Finanzbeh\u00f6rde des Landes bestimmte \u00f6ffentliche Kasse (&gt;\u00a7 41a Abs 3 EStG) abzuf\u00fchren"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer must indicate on the payment slip or have it indicated by his bank: the tax number, the description of the tax and the payroll tax registration period"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Eine Stundung der einzubehaltenden oder einbehaltenen Lohnsteuer ist nicht m\u00f6glich (&gt;\u00a7 222 Satz 3 und 4 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 135 Income tax certificate Income tax certificates on the income tax card (1) The employer is obliged to write out an income tax certificate on the income tax card for that calendar year for employees whose employment relationship ends before the end of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "At the end of each calendar year, the employer must write out the income tax certificate on the income tax cards for that calendar year for all employees whose income tax cards are available to him"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Dabei hat der Arbeitgeber stets die Dauer des Dienstverh\u00e4ltnisses im Kalenderjahr und die Anzahl der im Lohnkonto vermerkten Gro\u00dfbuchstaben U (&gt;R 131) anzugeben"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employee may not change the employer's entries"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Certificate of gross wages (2) When certifying gross wages, the following must be observed: The total amount of gross wages - including the value of remuneration in kind - that the employee received from the employment relationship in the calendar year must be certified"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Gross wages are the sum of the current wages that have been paid for wage payment periods that ended in the calendar year, and the other remuneration that the employee received in the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Net wages paid are to be set at the converted gross amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Der Bruttoarbeitslohn darf nicht um den Versorgungs-Freibetrag (&gt;\u00a7 19 Abs 2 EStG) und den Altersentlastungsbetrag (&gt;\u00a7 24a EStG) gek\u00fcrzt werden"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Exempt amounts entered on the income tax card are also not deductible"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Wages within the meaning of Section 8 (3) EStG are to be reduced by the discount exempt amount according to Section 8 (3) sentence 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When certifying the gross wage, a) reduced taxed compensation and remuneration for a multi-year activity within the meaning of \u00a7 34 EStG, b) remuneration that is not part of the taxable wage, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "tax-free insolvency money, tax-free travel expenses and reimbursement of expenses, tax-free relocation allowances and allowances as well as tax-free surcharges for Sunday, holiday and night work, c) payments that are exempt from wage tax on the basis of an agreement to avoid double taxation or on the basis of the foreign activity waiver, d) Payments for which the wage tax according to \u00a7\u00a7 40 to 40b EStG has been levied"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Separate certificates (3) The following remuneration must be certified separately on the income tax card: the gross amount of the reduced taxed pensions, separately the back payments taxed as other remuneration from pension remuneration that belong to several calendar years, and the other pension remuneration, reduced taxed compensations and remuneration for a multi-year activity within the meaning of \u00a7 34 EStG, remuneration for a foreign activity that is exempt from wage tax due to an agreement to avoid double taxation or due to the foreign activity decree, the sum of the amounts paid out from short-time work allowance, winter loss allowance, a contribution to maternity allowance according to the Maternity Protection Act or according to \u00a7 4a of the Maternity Protection Ordinance and a corresponding state regulation, compensation for loss of earnings according to the Federal Disease Act or an additional amount according to the Partial Retirement Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If amounts paid out by the employee have been reclaimed in full or in part, only the short-time work allowance or winter failure allowance reduced by the amount claimed may be certified"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the offsetting of paid and reclaimed amounts results in a negative amount, this amount - marked as negative - must be certified as the tax-free and flat-rate taxed employer benefits for trips between home and work"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, the capital letter \"F\" can be entered for free or partially paid transport that is tax-free according to Section 3 No. 32 or 34 or Section 8 (3) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Certification of tax deductions (4) The following applies to the certification of tax deductions: The wage tax, the solidarity surcharge and the church tax that the employer has withheld from the certified gross wages must be certified"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The withheld income tax, withheld solidarity surcharge and withheld church tax must always be certified as the amounts that result after offsetting against the tax amounts reimbursed by the employer for the calendar year in the annual income tax adjustment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the reimbursed amounts exceed the tax amounts withheld by the employer, the excess amount must be certified in red as the withheld tax amount or given a clear minus sign"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The wage tax, the solidarity surcharge and the church tax that the employer has withheld from reduced tax compensation and remuneration for a multi-year activity within the meaning of \u00a7 34 EStG must be certified separately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If no income tax, no solidarity surcharge or no church tax has been withheld, the field provided for these entries must be filled in with a horizontal line"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Address and company tax office of the employer (5) The full address of the employer must be entered on the income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Hierbei ist wegen der Zerlegung der Lohnsteuer und der Beteiligung der Gemeinden an der Einkommensteuer die Anschrift der Betriebsst\u00e4tte (&gt;\u00a7 41 Abs 2 EStG) einzutragen; Firmenstempel sind gegebenenfalls zu erg\u00e4nzen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the tax office to which the income tax has been paid and its four-digit tax office number must be specified on the income tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Supplement to the wage tax card (6) If the entry fields provided on the wage tax card for the wage tax certificate are not sufficient, the wage tax certificate must be issued on a special slip which contains all the information provided on the wage tax card in the same order and which is recorded by the employer with the wage tax card is to be connected"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Voluntary certificates (7) In order to avoid queries from the tax offices - without being obliged to do so - the tax-free meal allowances for external activities (business trips, changing assignments, driving), the tax-free employer benefits in the case of double housekeeping, the tax-free employer's allowances for voluntary health insurance should be on the income tax card and for long-term care insurance as well as the employee's share of the total social security contribution (pension insurance, health insurance, unemployment insurance and long-term care insurance) attributable to the taxable wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Basis for the income tax certificate (8) The employer has to provide the information required in the income tax certificate, usually based on the entries in the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer has not kept a wage account for individual employees because no wage tax, no solidarity surcharge or no church tax had to be withheld, he must provide information about the amount of the wages based on the documents otherwise available to him"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Special wage tax certificates (9) If the employer did not have a wage tax card for an employee when the wage account was closed, he must issue a special wage tax certificate according to the officially prescribed form"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This applies to employees who have failed to hand over their income tax card to the employer (Section 39c Paragraph 1 EStG), for employees residing abroad within the meaning of Section 1 Paragraph 2 and 3 EStG, in cases in which the employer Employees who left before the end of the calendar year did not write out the wage tax certificate on the wage tax card contrary to their obligation, on request for employees subject to limited income tax (Section 39d (3) sentence 5 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Machine wage tax certificate (10) Employers with machine payroll can generate the wage tax certificate and the special wage tax certificate automatically"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The prerequisite is that the machine-made income tax certificates contain all the information contained in the official forms in the same order"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Forms have been generally approved for the automated creation of income tax certificates"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A machine-generated income tax certificate must be firmly linked to the income tax card by the employer; It is sufficient if the income tax certificate is stuck to the edge of the back of the income tax card in such a way that the connection can no longer be undone without damaging the income tax card or the income tax certificate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Exceptions (11) The tax office can, upon application, allow employers who employ employees whose employment relationship is only for a short period of time to refrain from advertising the wage tax certificate after the employment relationship has ended for the employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In this case, the wage tax certificate must only be written out after the end of the calendar year for each employee who was employed in the past calendar year and a special wage tax certificate must also be sent to the business premises tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Where the wage tax cards and wage tax certificates remain (12) The employer must immediately hand over the wage tax certificates within the meaning of paragraph 1 and paragraph 9 sentence 1 to the employees who are assessed for income tax according to \u00a7 46 EStG after December 31; The income tax certificates that have not been handed over to the employees must be submitted to the permanent establishment tax office by the end of the following year after the annual income tax settlement to be carried out by the employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(13) Employees who are in possession of their income tax card at the end of the calendar year, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "because they were not employed at the time, they must send the tax card to the tax office in whose district the municipality that issued the tax card is located no later than the end of the following year; this does not apply if the income tax card is to be attached to an income tax return"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Lohnsteuerbescheinigung f\u00fcr ein geringf\u00fcgiges Besch\u00e4ftigungsverh\u00e4ltnis (14)Bei Beendigung des Besch\u00e4ftigungsverh\u00e4ltnisses oder am Ende des Kalenderjahrs hat der Arbeitgeber dem geringf\u00fcgig besch\u00e4ftigten Arbeitnehmer auf der Freistellungsbescheinigung (&gt;R 111a) eine Lohnsteuerbescheinigung zu erteilen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the income tax certificate is generated automatically, paragraph 10 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 136 Lohnsteuerbescheinigungen von \u00f6ffentlichen Kassen Wird ein Arbeitnehmer, der den Arbeitslohn im voraus f\u00fcr einen Lohnzahlungszeitraum erhalten hat, w\u00e4hrend dieser Zeit einer anderen Dienststelle zugewiesen und geht die Zahlung des Arbeitslohns auf die Kasse dieser Dienststelle \u00fcber, so hat die fr\u00fcher zust\u00e4ndige Kasse in der Lohnsteuerbescheinigung (&gt;R 135) den vollen von ihr gezahlten Arbeitslohn und die davon einbehaltene Lohnsteuer auch dann aufzunehmen, wenn ihr ein Teil des Arbeitslohns von der nunmehr zust\u00e4ndigen Kasse erstattet wird; der Arbeitslohn darf nicht um den Versorgungs-Freibetrag (&gt;\u00a7 19 Abs 2 EStG) und den Altersentlastungsbetrag (&gt;\u00a7 24a EStG) gek\u00fcrzt werden"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The now responsible fund does not have to include the part of the wages reimbursed to the previously responsible fund in the income tax certificate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 137 Change in the wage tax deduction (1) Regardless of the employer's obligation to change the wage tax deduction for the month of January in accordance with Section 39c (2) EStG, the employer is responsible for changing the wage tax deduction in the cases specified in Section 41c (1) EStG entitled to the next following wage payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The change is permissible in favor of or to the disadvantage of the employee without the amount of the tax to be reimbursed or subsequently withheld being relevant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The regulation that exists in the event of additional demands by the tax office that amounts of up to 20 DM are not to be demanded, does not apply to subsequent withholding by the employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The employer is only entitled to change the wage tax deduction if the wage tax has been withheld by him or was to be withheld"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Bei Nettol\u00f6hnen (&gt;R 122) gilt dies f\u00fcr die zu \u00fcbernehmende Steuer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Bei Eintragungen auf der Lohnsteuerkarte eines Arbeitnehmers, die auf einen Zeitpunkt vor Beginn des Dienstverh\u00e4ltnisses zur\u00fcckwirken, wird auf die Anzeigepflicht des Arbeitgebers (&gt;R 138) verwiesen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) The change in the wage tax deduction due to retroactive entries on the wage tax card is not limited to cases in which the municipality or the tax office changes or supplements entries on the wage tax card of an employee with effect from a previous point in time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The change in the wage tax deduction is also permitted if the employer has made the wage tax deduction in accordance with Section 39c (1) EStG due to failure to present the wage tax card and the employee submits a wage tax card for the first time or if, in the case of advance payment of wages, the beginning of validity of an entry on the wage tax card in an already settled wage payment period falls"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The content of the certificates issued in accordance with Section 39b (6), 39c (3) and 39d (1) EStG, as well as the entries on the income tax card, must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) If the employer makes use of his authorization to do so, the change in the wage tax deduction is to be made with the next wage payment following the presentation of the wage tax card with the retroactive entries or the recognition of an irregular wage tax withholding"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In cases of subsequent withholding of wage tax, the employer may not distribute the withholding over several wage payments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Subsequent withholding is also permissible insofar as this falls below the seizure exemption limits; if the wage tax to be withheld subsequently exceeds the cash wages to be paid out, the subsequent withholding is to be omitted altogether and a report to be made to the tax office in accordance with Section 41c (4) of the Income Tax Act"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(5) In the case of reimbursement of wage tax, the employer must take the wage tax to be reimbursed from the total amount of wage tax to be paid by him"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "As an application for compensation for any deficit, it is sufficient if the reimbursement amount is indicated in the income tax declaration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer does not make use of his entitlement to reimbursement of income tax under Section 41c Paragraphs 1 and 2 EStG, the employee can apply to the tax office for reimbursement under Section 37 Paragraph 2 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 139 Paragraph 4 Clause 2 applies accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(6) After the end of the calendar year, the wage tax deduction is to be changed in such a way that the annual wage tax is determined and the amount of tax to be subsequently withheld or reimbursed can be determined by comparing it with the total wage tax withheld"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, a reimbursement may only be made in the annual wage tax adjustment under the conditions of \u00a7 42b EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer is not allowed to carry out the annual wage tax adjustment in accordance with Section 42b (1) EStG, it is also not possible to change the wage tax deduction with reimbursement consequences; In these cases, the employee can obtain reimbursement within the framework of an assessment for income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as the employer subsequently withholds wage tax due to a change in the wage tax deduction after the end of the calendar year, this is wage tax for the past calendar year, which must be stated in the wage tax certificate together with the remaining wage tax for the past calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(7) In the case of persons with limited tax liability, a change in the wage tax deduction is only to be made for the wage payment periods to which the changes relate, even after the end of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Eine \u00c4nderung mit Erstattungsfolge kann in diesem Falle nur das Finanzamt durchf\u00fchren (&gt;\u00a7 37 Abs 2 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 138 Notification Obligations of the Employer (1) The employer has to fulfill the notification obligations according to \u00a7\u00a7 38 Abs 4 41c Abs 4 EStG immediately"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "As soon as the employer realizes that the wage tax has been deducted in too low an amount, he has to report this to the business premises tax office if he cannot withhold the wage tax retrospectively or does not make use of his authorization to do so; this also applies to retroactive changes to the law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer has to report the insufficient withholding of the income tax for the past four calendar years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The limitation of additional wage tax claims to amounts of more than DM 20 does not release from the obligation to notify"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The notification must be made in writing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It contains the name and address of the employee, the tax information entered on the income tax card, namely birthday, tax class, number of child allowances, religious community to which the church tax is to be paid and, if applicable, an allowance, as well as the reason for notification and the calculation of a Required information about the amount and type of wages, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Extract from the payroll account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) The business premises tax office must forward the notification to the tax office responsible for income taxation of the employee if it appears expedient not to carry out the additional wage tax claim immediately, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "because the employee is likely to be assessed for income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Das ist auch angebracht in F\u00e4llen, in denen bei Eingang der Anzeige nicht zu \u00fcbersehen ist, ob sich bei \u00c4nderung des Lohnsteuerabzugs nach Ablauf des Kalenderjahrs (&gt;\u00a7 41c Abs 3 Satz 2 EStG) eine Lohnsteuer-Nachforderung ergeben wird"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 139 Nachforderung von Lohnsteuer (1)Zur Erfassung der Nachforderungsf\u00e4lle, die auf einer \u00c4nderung oder Erg\u00e4nzung der Eintragungen auf der Lohnsteuerkarte durch die Gemeinde beruhen, kann das Finanzamt Anweisungen erteilen (&gt;\u00a7 39 Abs 6 Satz 2 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) In the cases of Sections 38 (4) and 41c (4) of the EStG, the permanent establishment tax office is responsible for the additional claim if the insufficiently levied wage tax is to be claimed in the course of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) In the case of Section 41c Paragraph 4 EStG, R 137 Paragraph 6 Clause 1 and Paragraph 7 Clause 1 apply accordingly to the calculation of the wage tax to be claimed after the end of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In all other cases, the income tax that arises for the employee is to be determined as the annual wage tax if he has earned only the income resulting from the annual wage reduced by a possible pension exemption and retirement benefit amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Vom Jahresarbeitslohn sind deshalb noch die Werbungskosten (&gt;\u00a7 2 Abs 2 Nr 2 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7\u00a7 9 und 9a EStG), die Sonderausgaben und au\u00dfergew\u00f6hnlichen Belastungen (&gt;\u00a7 2 Abs 4 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "\u00a7\u00a7 10 10b, 10c, 33 bis 33c EStG) und der Haushaltsfreibetrag (&gt;\u00a7 2 Abs 5 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Section 32 (7) of the Income Tax Act)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The amounts to be taken into account are to be determined independently of the allowances taken into account in the wage tax deduction and independent of the tax class certified on the wage tax card"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The annual wage tax is then to be determined as follows: 1Gross wages2 + reduced taxed compensation and remuneration for multi-year work within the meaning of Section 34 EStG3 + post-tax amounts according to Section 19a (9) No. 4 EStG (Section 7 (4) LStDV) 4 = annual wages5- pension allowance ( \u00a7 19 Paragraph 2 EStG) 6- Business expenses, flat-rate employee fee (\u00a7\u00a7 9 9a EStG) 7- Age relief amount (\u00a7 24 a EStG) 8 = Total amount of income (\u00a7 2 Paragraph 3 EStG) 9- Special expenses (\u00a7\u00a7 10 10 b , 10 c EStG) 10- extraordinary burdens (Sections 33 to 33c EStG) 11 = income (Section 2 Paragraph 4 EStG) 12- child allowance (only for children who are not entitled to child benefit; Section 39a Paragraph 1 No. 6 EStG ) 13- Household allowance (\u00a7 32 Paragraph 7 EStG) 14 = taxable income (\u00a7 2 Paragraph 5 EStG) 15- Remuneration within the meaning of \u00a7 34 Paragraph 3 EStG (line 2) 16 = remaining taxable income17 + one fifth of the remuneration in the sense of of \u00a7 34 EStG (line 218 = sum19 = tax amount for the sum (line 18) according to Grundt abelle / Splittingtabelle20- Tax amount for the remaining taxable income (line 16) according to the basic table / splitting table21 = difference If the employee has not received any remuneration within the meaning of \u00a7 34 EStG, the tax amount for the taxable income (line 14) is from the basic table / splitting table determined tax amount the annual wage tax (collectively agreed income tax - \u00a7 32a Abs 1 5 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employee has received remuneration within the meaning of Section 34 EStG, the tax amount for the remaining taxable income (line 20) plus five times the difference (line 21) is the annual income tax (collectively agreed income tax - Section 32a (1) 5 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) If the tax office wants to demand too little withheld income tax from the employee, it shall issue a tax assessment against the employee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The amount claimed must be entered by the tax office in the wage tax certificate on the wage tax card like the wage tax withheld; this does not apply to additional wage tax claims after the end of the calendar year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "After the end of the calendar year, additional wage tax or income tax claims may also be made through initial or changed assessment of income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(5) Except in the case of Section 38 (4) of the Income Tax Act (EStG), there is no additional demand if the wage tax to be demanded does not exceed DM 20 (small amount limit)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the additional claim relates to several calendar years, it must be determined separately for each calendar year whether the small amount limit is exceeded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If several reasons for additional claims come together in a calendar year, the limit for the small amount applies to the total wage tax to be claimed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 140 - R 142 - unoccupied - R 143 Implementation of the annual wage tax adjustment by the employer (1) The employer may only carry out the annual wage tax adjustment for employees who are subject to unlimited income tax and who have been permanently employed during the adjustment year and on December 31 of Be in his service in the compensation year or receive wages from him from a previous employment relationship at this point in time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In determining whether the requirement of number 1 is met, periods for which the employee received regular wages from a previous employment relationship must also be included"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the unrestricted income tax liability begins or ends in the course of the calendar year, the employer may not carry out the annual income tax adjustment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) If the annual allowance has changed in the course of the calendar year, the annual allowance last certified on the income tax card must be deducted from the annual wages"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) In the annual wage tax table, the relevant pension lump sum is incorporated for the annual wages shown there"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This can lead to the fact that in cases in which the annual wages are reduced by an exemption entered on the income tax card, the pension lump sum due to the employee is not taken into account in the correct amount"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The correct flat rate provision may not be taken into account by the employer, but only by the tax office when assessing income tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Das gilt auch f\u00fcr Arbeitgeber, die f\u00fcr den Lohnsteuer-Jahresausgleich ein maschinelles Verfahren anwenden (&gt;R 121 Abs 2)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4)Beantragt der Arbeitnehmer, Entsch\u00e4digungen oder Verg\u00fctungen f\u00fcr mehrj\u00e4hrige T\u00e4tigkeit im Sinne des \u00a7 34 EStG in den Lohnsteuer-Jahresausgleich einzubeziehen (&gt;\u00a7 42b Abs 2 Satz 2 EStG), so geh\u00f6ren die Entsch\u00e4digungen und Verg\u00fctungen zum Jahresarbeitslohn, f\u00fcr den die Jahreslohnsteuer aus der Jahreslohnsteuertabelle zu ermitteln ist"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 144 - unbesetzt - R 145 Inanspruchnahme des Arbeitgebers Allgemeines (1)Der Arbeitnehmer ist - vorbehaltlich \u00a7 40 Abs 3 EStG - Schuldner der Lohnsteuer (\u00a7 38 Abs 2 EStG); dies gilt auch f\u00fcr den Fall einer Nettolohnvereinbarung (&gt;R 122)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The employer can be held liable for this debt insofar as his liability extends (Section 42d (1) and (2) EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Dies gilt auch bei Lohnzahlung durch Dritte, soweit der Arbeitgeber zur Einbehaltung der Lohnsteuer verpflichtet ist (\u00a7 38 Abs 1 Satz 2 EStG; &gt;R 106 Abs 5)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Liability of other persons (2) As far as third parties can be used for tax payments, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Legal representatives of legal persons, representatives, authorized agents, asset managers, legal successors, they are liable as joint and several debtors in addition to the employer as a further liable party and in addition to the employee as a tax debtor (\u00a7 44 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The liability can z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "from \u00a7\u00a7 69 to 77 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Joint and several debtors (3) Insofar as employers, employees and, if applicable, other persons are jointly and severally liable, everyone owes the entire service (Section 44 (1) sentence 2 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax office must choose which joint and several debtor it wants to adhere to at its dutiful discretion, taking into account the limits set by law and equity and taking reasonable account of the interests of all parties involved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Assessment of discretion (4) The employer's liability is generally not dependent on fault"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, minor negligence or innocent behavior on the part of the employer is to be assessed when considering whether claims against the employer are within the scope of the discretion"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The question of whether the employer may be sued before the employee depends largely on the overall circumstances of the individual case, whereby the legislative purpose of the wage tax procedure is to ensure the rapid receipt of wage tax in a simplified procedure through the deduction at the source is"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Claims against the employer can be excluded if he has made the individual wage tax deduction without taking legal changes into account, insofar as it was unreasonable for him to take the legal changes into account in the short time between the promulgation of the law and the subsequent pay slips when applying a strict standard"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Liability notice (5) If the employer is claimed to be liable under Section 42d EStG, a liability notice is to be issued, subject to Section 42d Paragraph 4 No. 1 and 2 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The reasons for the resolution and selection fair must be stated therein"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the employer has acknowledged a payment obligation in writing after completing an external wage tax audit, the declaration of acknowledgment is equivalent to a wage tax registration (Section 167 (1) sentence 3 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A liability notice does not affect the income tax registrations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Additional claim notice (6) If flat-rate wage tax is levied subsequently, which the employer has to assume (Section 40 (3) EStG), a subsequent claim notice (tax assessment) must be issued; Paragraph 5 sentences 3 and 4 apply accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The notification of additional claims relates to certain taxable matters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The change is only possible with regard to the underlying facts - with the exception of the cases of Sections 172 and 175 AO - due to the change block in Section 173 (2) AO in the event of tax evasion or frivolous tax reduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Zahlungsfrist (7)F\u00fcr die durch Haftungsbescheid (&gt;Absatz 5) oder Nachforderungsbescheid (&gt;Absatz 6) angeforderten Steuerbetr\u00e4ge ist eine Zahlungsfrist von einem Monat zu setzen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 146 Haftung bei Arbeitnehmer\u00fcberlassung Allgemeines (1)Bei Arbeitnehmer\u00fcberlassung ist steuerrechtlich grunds\u00e4tzlich der Verleiher Arbeitgeber der Leiharbeitnehmer (&gt;R 66 Abs 1 Satz 4)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Dies gilt f\u00fcr einen ausl\u00e4ndischen Verleiher (&gt;R 105 Abs 1 Satz 2) selbst dann, wenn der Entleiher Arbeitgeber im Sinne eines Doppelbesteuerungsabkommens ist; die Arbeitgebereigenschaft des Entleihers nach einem Doppelbesteuerungsabkommen hat nur Bedeutung f\u00fcr die Zuweisung des Besteuerungsrechts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If claims are made against the borrower as a liability debtor, due to the different requirements and consequences, a distinction must always be made between whether he is liable as the employer of the temporary workers or as a third party according to Section 42d (6) EStG in addition to the lender as the employer of the temporary workers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Claims against the hirer according to \u00a7 42d Paragraph 6 EStG (2) The hirer is liable according to \u00a7 42d Paragraph 6 EStG like the lender (employer), but limited to the wage tax for the time for which the temporary worker has been made available to him"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The borrower's liability is therefore based on the same principles as the employer's liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is eliminated if the lender would not be liable as an employer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The borrower's liability only applies to commercial leasing according to \u00a7 1 A\u00dcG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The leasing of employees is commercial if the commercial law requirements are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the entrepreneur (lender) who operates temporary staff not only occasionally but on a permanent basis and thus wants to achieve economic advantages acts commercially"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The requirements can e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "not be fulfilled if employees are occasionally loaned out between independent companies to cover short-term additional staffing requirements, are posted to other business premises of their employer or are released to work groups"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Temporary employment does not exist if the temporary employment of employees is to be regarded as an ancillary service to another service, if z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "in the case of renting out machines and leasing the operating personnel, the economic value of the renting outweighs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the cases of Section 1 Paragraph 1 Clause 2 and Paragraph 3 A\u00dcG, no leasing of employees is to be accepted either"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) For the legal assessment of a situation with a third-party activity as a temporary worker and its delimitation, especially in relation to a work contract, the overall picture of the activity is crucial"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "On the description of the legal transaction, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "as a work contract, it does not matter"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "On temporary employment, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the following features: The owner of the third-party company (borrower) essentially exercises the employer's right to issue instructions; the performance purpose pursued with the employment of the employee corresponds to the operational purpose of the third company; the tool to be used is essentially provided by the third party, unless due to safety regulations; the liability risks associated with other types of contract, in particular contracts for work and services, have been excluded or limited; the work of the deployed employee towards the posting employer is remunerated on the basis of time units"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "When examining the question of whether there is a temporary employment contract, the opinion of the Federal Labor Office must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A claim against the hirer is generally not possible if the Federal Employment Agency has expressed the opinion to the hirer that there is no leasing of workers in the actual situation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4) Exceptions to the borrower's liability are contained in Section 42d (6) sentences 2 and 3 EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The transfer is based on a license according to \u00a7 1 A\u00dcG within the meaning of \u00a7 42d (6) sentence 2 EStG if the lender had a license according to \u00a7 1 A\u00dcG at the time of the rental or the license according to \u00a7 2 (4) A\u00dcG during this time is deemed to continue, d"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "up to 12 months after the expiry of the license to process the contracts that have been concluded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, the leasing is not based on a permit if employees are leased commercially to companies in the construction industry for work that is usually performed by workers because this is not permitted under Section 1b A\u00dcG and the permit under Section 1 A\u00dcG does not extend to such leasing, it unless the leasing takes place between companies in the construction industry that are covered by the same framework and social security collective agreements or by general liability"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the case of permitted lending by a domestic lender, the borrower is not liable if he has reported the temporary employment to the responsible health insurance company in accordance with Sections 28a to 28c SGB IV"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It is incumbent on the borrower to demonstrate the fulfillment of the reporting and cooperation obligations and to prove in case of doubt"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The borrower also bears the burden of determination if he claims that he was wrong about the existence of a temporary employment agency through no fault (Section 42d (6) sentence 3 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Paragraph 3 must be taken into account when making use of the hirer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the area of \u200b\u200binadmissible temporary employment, stricter standards are to be applied because of the prohibition in \u00a7 1b A\u00dcG if the hirer claims that he has made an error through no fault of his own"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This applies in particular if the rental fee is significantly cheaper than that of other providers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Whether the lender has a permit according to \u00a7 1 A\u00dcG, the lender must declare in the written leasing contract according to \u00a7 12 paragraph 1 A\u00dcG and the borrower himself or the tax office can find out or check by requesting the state employment office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(5) The amount of the liability is limited to the wage tax which the lender may have to withhold proportionally for the time for which the temporary worker was left to the borrower"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the lender has paid part of the total withheld and registered wage tax for the corresponding wage tax registration period, taking into account the wage tax of the temporary worker hired out to the hirer, the liability amount is reduced in the ratio of registered to paid wage tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(6) The notice of liability can be issued against the borrower if the requirements for liability are met"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "However, payment may only be made after a failed attempt at enforcement against the domestic movable property of the lender or if the enforcement does not promise success (Section 42d (6) sentence 6 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A previous request for payment to the employee or an attempt at enforcement is not required (corresponding application of \u00a7 219 sentence 2 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Claims against the lender according to Section 42d (7) EStG (7) According to Section 42d (7) EStG, the lender, who is not to be treated as an employer under tax law, can be held liable as a borrower according to Section 42d (6) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, payment can only be made after the borrower"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This is to be distinguished from the issuance of the notice of liability, which can be issued beforehand"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The lender cannot therefore successfully plead against the notice of liability that the borrower is to be treated as the employer of all or part of the leased temporary workers due to the actual processing of an unauthorized temporary employment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Security procedure according to \u00a7 42d (8) EStG (8) As a security measure, the tax office can oblige the borrower to withhold and pay a certain DM amount or a percentage of the agreed rental fee"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If the borrower has already paid part of the rental fee owed to the lender, the security amount can be set at a certain DM amount or as a percentage up to the amount of the remaining payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The security measure is only to be ordered in cases in which liability can come into consideration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "It may be taken into account that it can ultimately burden the borrower less than the subsequent liability if he z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "cannot enforce a right of recourse against the lender"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Haftungsverfahren (9)Wird der Entleiher oder Verleiher als Haftungsschuldner in Anspruch genommen, so ist ein Haftungsbescheid zu erlassen (&gt;R 145 Abs 5)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Responsibility (10) The company tax office of the lender is responsible for the notice of liability against the borrower or lender (Section 42d (6) sentence 9 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "If it is established with a borrower that his claim is possible as a liability debtor according to \u00a7 42d (6) EStG, the lender's business premises tax office is to be involved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Bei Verleih durch einen ausl\u00e4ndischen Verleiher (&gt;\u00a7 38 Abs 1 Satz 1 Nr 2 EStG) ist das Betriebsst\u00e4ttenfinanzamt des Entleihers zust\u00e4ndig, wenn dem Finanzamt keine andere \u00dcberlassung des Verleihers im Inland bekannt ist, da es zugleich Betriebsst\u00e4ttenfinanzamt des Verleihers nach \u00a7 41 Abs 2 Satz 2 EStG ist"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In principle, this also applies to a security measure in accordance with Section 42d (8) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In addition, each tax office is responsible for a security measure in whose district the cause of the official act emerges, especially in the case of imminent danger (\u00a7\u00a7 24 29 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 147 Call information (1) Both the employer and the employee are entitled to information"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In both cases, the permanent establishment tax office is responsible for providing the information; however, in the event of an employee's inquiries, he or she should coordinate his information with his or her tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The tax office should provide the information in writing with an explicit reference to Section 42e EStG; this also applies if the person involved has only requested information informally"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "A legal remedy is only given if the tax office refuses to provide information"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) If an employer has several permanent establishments, the tax office should coordinate its information with the other permanent establishment tax offices, insofar as it is a case of some importance and it can be seen that the information is also important for the other permanent establishments"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "As a rule, it is sufficient to contact the tax office of the main branch or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "the group headquarters (management according to \u00a7 10 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "This tax office has to coordinate the call information of the business premises tax offices"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In the event of invocation information of a fundamental nature and in the event of clearly conflicting decisions by the permanent establishment tax offices, the tax office of the main branch or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "of the group headquarters (within the meaning of \u00a7 10 AO) the other tax offices concerned"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 148 external wage tax audit (1) Sections 193 to 207 AO apply to external wage tax audits"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Sections 5 to 12 of the Company Audit Regulations are to be applied accordingly, with the exception of Section 5 (4) sentence 2"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(2) The wage tax field audit is subject to both private and public employers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Audits by an employer under public law by the responsible supervisory and auditing authority do not conflict with the admissibility of an external wage tax audit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(3) The wage tax field audit has to extend mainly to whether all employees, including those not permanently employed, are recorded and all income belonging to wages, regardless of the form in which they are granted, is subject to tax deduction and whether in the calculation the wage tax is based on the correct wage level"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Private households in which only low-wage assistance is employed are generally not to be examined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(4)\u00dcber das Ergebnis der Au\u00dfenpr\u00fcfung ist dem Arbeitgeber ein Pr\u00fcfungsbericht zu \u00fcbersenden (&gt;\u00a7 202 Abs 1 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "F\u00fchrt die Au\u00dfenpr\u00fcfung zu keiner \u00c4nderung der Besteuerungsgrundlagen, so gen\u00fcgt es, wenn dies dem Arbeitgeber schriftlich mitgeteilt wird (&gt;\u00a7 202 Abs 1 Satz 3 AO)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "In den F\u00e4llen, in denen ein Nachforderungsbescheid oder ein Haftungsbescheid nicht zu erteilen ist (&gt;\u00a7 42d Abs 4 EStG), kann der Arbeitgeber auf die \u00dcbersendung eines Pr\u00fcfungsberichts verzichten"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "(5) The right to call information according to \u00a7 42e EStG does not conflict with the right to issue a binding commitment based on an external audit according to \u00a7 204 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "R 149 Assessment according to \u00a7 46 Paragraph 2 No. 8 EStG - unoccupied - R 150 Elimination of hardship in certain cases of \u00a7 46 Paragraph 2 EStG - unoccupied - Article 2 Application of the 1999 wage tax guidelines The 1999 wage tax guidelines of 1 October 1999 (Federal Tax Gazette I special number 1/19 98) are canceled"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "With the deviations resulting from the change in legal provisions for the period up to December 31, 1999, they are to be used for the last time for wage payment periods that end before January 1, 2000, and for other remuneration that the employee receives before January 1, 2000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "The Federal Council has approved"}, {"meta": {"name": "0115351.xml"}, "text": "Berlin, October 29, 1999 income tax income tax / income tax / church taxELWI-LohnSteuer HandbuchELWI-REWEelwi-reweElwi-LohnBundes RepublikTaxrecht"}]